title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat for 3 minutes at medium speed.
Sift together the flour, salt and soda; add to the oil mixture.
Add vanilla.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
Let cool.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter & honey candy
directions: Mix peanut butter and honey until blended.
Stir in the powdered milk until very stiff.
Roll into balls and freeze at least 2 hours.
If desired, dip the balls into melted chocolate almond bark.

title: maryland crab imperial
directions: Saute 1/2 green pepper with 2 tablespoons butter. Mash hard-boiled egg to paste. Add the raw egg. Add all this to the fresh crabmeat or canned crabmeat, Worcestershire, salt and pepper. Grease casserole. Top with 2 tablespoons mayonnaise mixed with 1 tablespoon cream. Bake 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: pot o' gold pork roast
directions: In large heavy pan, brown roast in shortening; pour off fat. Add soup, water, onion and seasonings.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Cook 1 hour more or until meat and vegetables are done.
Remove bay leaf.
Thicken juice for gravy, if desired.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam cooking spray.
Cut bread into cubes and place in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
Mix eggs, half and half and spices.
Pour over hot mixture and refrigerate for at least 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni; set aside.
Brown boneless chicken strips in oil or shortening.
Mix together Rice-A-Roni, chicken broth, cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Pour into greased baking dish. Layer the chicken strips on top and add grated Cheddar cheese on the top of chicken.
Cover lightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin marble cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Reserve 1 cup batter. Add remaining sugar, pumpkin and spices to remaining batter; mix well.
Spoon pumpkin and cream cheese batters alternately over crust; cut through batters with knife several times for marble effect.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim of pan; cool before removing rim of pan.
Chill.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus. Grease medium casserole dish and put layer of asparagus, layer of mushroom soup, layer of grated cheese and lumps of butter or margarine. Repeat. Put layer of bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until top is bubbly and crumbs are brown. Serves 4 to 6. (Cooked eggplant or squash may be substituted for the asparagus.)

title: easy cheesies
directions: Mix in a large bowl by hand: cake mix, melted margarine and egg.
Press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Mix lemon frosting and cream cheese in large bowl by hand. Reserve 1 cup.
Spread rest of frosting mix on top of cake mixture and bake 25 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 20 more minutes or until light brown.
Cool completely.
Spread on reserved cup of frosting mix.
Cut into 2-inch bars.

title: vegetable meat loaf
directions: Chop eggs, onion, garlic, carrots and celery in food processor.
Blend meat and vegetable mix, then add salt, pepper and sage.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cowboy kabobs
directions: You will need 18 (10-inch) skewers.
Soak skewers in water for at least 30 minutes.

title: old fashion gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add molasses and hot water.
Dissolve soda in cold water and add to mixture.
Sift flour with spices, salt and baking powder.
Add to mixture and beat well with rotary egg beater. Bake in large layer pan about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Scald milk; blend sugar, flour and salt and add to hot milk. Cook over double boiler or medium heat until thickened.
Beat egg yolks; add to hot pudding.
Re-cook for 3 minutes; add vanilla and butter.

title: grandma's best baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain.
Heat large ovenproof pot on stove top and sear diced bacon.
Add beans, sugar, molasses, salt (if used), mustard, onion, catsup and water (enough to cover beans).
Cover and bake in a 300° oven for 3 hours.
Stir once each hour and add water if needed.
This recipe will serve 4 to 6 people as a side dish.

title: baked papaya with curry rice
directions: Combine rice, cheese, curry powder, onions, raisins and chutney.
Spoon 1/3 cup rice mixture into hollow of each papaya half.
Combine sugar and cinnamon and drizzle with butter.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake in 450° oven for 15 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Add all other ingredients except spaghetti and let simmer for approximately 2 hours.
Add water if it should get too thick.
Add spaghetti about 30 minutes before serving.

title: deboned chicken breast bake
directions: Roll chicken breast in sour cream, then cover with stuffing mix.
Put in casserole dish.
Drizzle with melted butter; cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake another 15 minutes.

title: mustard
directions: Whiz in blender.
Pour into saucepan and cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Return to blender; add 2 tablespoons of garlic cloves and 1/3 cup of oil.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Pour all ingredients in large stew pan or Dutch oven.
Simmer about 2 hours with 5 to 8 drops of Tabasco sauce.

title: pork and apple casserole
directions: Place apples in a well-greased square baking dish.
Mix next 5 ingredients and combine with apples.
Coat 4 lean pork chop cutlets or steak with Shake 'n Bake.
Arrange pork over apples.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix together crumbs, butter and seed.
Layer bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole with 1/2 of mixture.
Combine chicken, soup and sour cream and place on top of crumb mixture.
Put remainder of crumb mixture on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: bonnie collin's jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: classic truffle
directions: Heat cream in a small saucepan over medium heat.
Stir constantly until it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and pour over chocolate.
Stir until all chocolate is melted and candy is well blended.
Add oil flavoring.
Refrigerate until mixture is firm enough to roll into balls.
Roll truffle mixture into balls using approximately 2 tablespoons of candy.
Refrigerate balls of candy approximately 5 minutes.
Melt another pound of chocolate for dipping in top of double boiler.
Dip balls, one at a time, into chocolate.
Cool on piece of wax paper.

title: german pancakes
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 12-inch or 10 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve with favorite syrup.

title: spicy primavera salad
directions: Cube the ham and cheese.
Cook and drain noodles.
Drain black olives.
Mix all together in large bowl.
Add salad dressing to your taste.
Refrigerate overnight.
Salad tastes better if made a day before.
Before serving, you may wish to add more dressing to make it moist.
Good with burgers or steak.
Makes 15 to 20 servings.

title: bourbon pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a bowl or food processor, mix the eggs, sugar, syrups, butter and bourbon until smooth.
Sprinkle the pastry with the chopped pecans then carefully pour in the filling.
Coat each pecan half by dipping in the filling and then arrange on the top.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Cool until set.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together margarine and sugars until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Add to margarine mixture and mix well.
Stir in oats, chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
(Store in a tightly sealed plastic container with a piece of bread, if you want cookies to stay chewy.)

title: white oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine
dry
ingredients, mix and add shortening, eggs and milk; mix.
Add coconut and nuts, stir.
Add oatmeal last, stir. Bake at 375°.

title: fudge
directions: Do not use an aluminum pie pan and use a wooden spoon to stir. Blend and cook sugar, chocolate, milk and Karo syrup until sugar is dissolved and mixture reaches "soft ball stage".
Immediately add peanut butter and vanilla.

title: eggplant lasagne
directions: Cut eggplant into round slices 1/4-inch thick.
Beat eggs and milk.
Add garlic.
Dip sliced eggplant in egg, then flour.
Shake off excess.
Dip in egg again, then in bread crumbs.
Fry in hot olive oil until golden on both sides.
Drain.
Pour leftover egg mixture into cottage cheese.
Add Parmesan and parsley.
Layer in a casserole dish as follows:
small amount of sauce to coat bottom. Top with single layer of eggplant.
Overlap, if necessary to make solid surface.
Cover with sauce, then cottage cheese mixture and Mozzarella.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
End with cheese on top.
Sprinkle with extra Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let sit for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: apple pecan muffins
directions: In bowl, combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add shredded apples and nuts.
In another bowl, combine sugar, milk, oil, lemon juice, vanilla and egg.
Add to flour mixture.
Spoon into paper lined muffin cup pan and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: mexican crepes
directions: Cook hamburger, green pepper and onion.
Drain.
Add refried beans and taco sauce and olives.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients well, slowly stir in hot milk., Pour quickly into pie shell. Top with nutmeg.
Bake at 475° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 425° for 15 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool on rack, serve cool.

title: broccoli casserole #2
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken divan
directions: Simmer chicken breasts about 1 hour; bone and skin, when fully cooked.
Break into large chunks; place in greased casserole dish. Arrange broccoli over chicken.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and cheese.
Pour over chicken and broccoli. Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grilled eggplant appetizers
directions: Prepare a hot charcoal or gas fire.
Cut eggplants crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Brush both sides with olive oil and sprinkle with salt.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt together.
Stir in bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons depending on the size of cup in hot water.
Nice to give as a gift.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain cooked beans and place in casserole dish.
Add cream of mushroom soup on top of beans.
Bake covered for 30 minutes on 350°.
Place onions on top and slightly brown them.

title: grilled catfish fillet
directions: Melt butter in saucepan or microwave oven.
Mix in seasoning, hot sauce and Worcestershire.
Glaze both sides of fillets with butter mixture.
Sprinkle on paprika.
Grill in skillet over medium fire, about 5 minutes on each side or until tender.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix altogether; refrigerate for 6 hours before serving.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Drain cooked broccoli; mix with cooked rice.
Add mushroom soup; add half of cheese.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese; bake until cheese melts.

title: date-nut cookies
directions: Gradually mix sugar and beaten eggs until light.
Add chopped nuts, broken nuts and flour.
Next, add sifted bread flour with baking powder and salt; resift.
Add spices.
Add the sifted ingredients of the egg mixture with 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat the batter until the ingredients are well blended.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch tin, lined with buttered paper.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: corn dog casserole
directions: In a skillet, saute celery in butter for 5 minutes. Add onions saute for 5 minutes. Place in a large bowl; set aside. Cut hotdogs lengthwise into quarter, the cut into thirds. In the same skillet saute the hot dogs for 5 minutes or until lightly browned: add to vegetables. Set aside 1 cup. In a large bowl, combine eggs, milk, sage and pepper. Add the remaining hot dog mixture. Stir in cornbread mixes. Add 1 1/2 c. oil cheese. Spread into shallow 3 qt. baking dish. Top with reserved got dog mixture and remaining cheese. Bake uncovered at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 12 servings.

title: sausage and egg souffle
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet and brown.
Drain well.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, mustard and cubed bread.
Stir well.
Add sausage and cheese to mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(If using glass dish, set out 30 minutes prior to baking.)
Serves 10.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes. Peel and cut up. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Let set several hours in the refrigerator before serving.

title: aloha cake
directions: Mix
cake
mix	as
directed
on
package
substituting pineapple juice
for water.
If not enough juice complete with water for
required amount.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients and form patties.
Roll in cornmeal and deep fry.

title: vegetable-broccoli parmesan
directions: Cut broccoli into flowerets no longer than 3 inches.
Steam broccoli in steam basket for 10 minutes.
Remove.
Place in heated serving dish.
Cover.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel and remove pit from avocado.
Mash with fork.
In a bowl, combine avocado with remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Crumble breads.
Add all ingredients, except butter.
Pour into crock-pot and dot with butter.
Cover.
Cook on high for 2 hours or on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: poor man's corn chowder
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for about an hour.
Stir occasionally; will thicken as is cooked.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Cook chicken in oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Chop in pieces. Mix sour cream and soup.
Saute onion in skillet.
Add chili powder, chilies, chopped chicken and 4 tablespoons soup mixture. Put shells in Reynolds Wrap; heat in oven 10 minutes.
Put mixture and cheese in each shell and wrap.
Put in casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, covered, 30 to 40 minutes.
Uncover for 15 minutes.

title: "unstuffed" peppers(serves 4)
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion, chili powder, rice, tomato sauce and 1 to 1 1/2 cans water.
Lower heat and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream butter, both sugars and egg.
Then add 1/3 cup peanut butter, baking soda, salt, vanilla and flour; mix well, then add oatmeal and mix with spoon.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
After you remove (cake) sprinkle with chocolate chips (as much as you'd like).
Let cool.
Enjoy.

title: butter cake
directions: French Silk Frosting (recipe follows)

title: magic topping
directions: Combine and cook, stirring constantly until sugar melts. Spread on top of warm cake. Return to 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: bowl cake
directions: Bake cake; let cool.
Prepare pudding.
Crumble cake in bottom of a punch bowl or any clear bowl.
Spread pineapple on top of cake.
Spread pudding on top of pineapple.
Spread pie filling on top of pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: flea-flicker cornbread(makes 12 servings)
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, cook sausage until done, stirring to break up meat; drain on paper towel.
In large bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, baking soda and sugar.

title: festival rice pudding
directions: Add rice and salt to boiling water.
Cover and cook over low heat until water is absorbed.
Add milk and oleo, bring to boil, cover and cook 1 hour or until milk is absorbed.
Add sugar, raisins and vanilla to beaten eggs.
Pour into rice, stirring slowly until rice begins to thicken.

title: maple crunch cookies
directions: Cream oleo, syrup and sugar; add egg and beat until fluffy. Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
If too stiff, add 2 tablespoons milk.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Frost with icing.

title: cheese spinach squares
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, oleo, cheese and onion. Drain spinach and add to mixture.
Grease 9 x 13 pan and spread mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Do not add extra salt or pepper.
Cook onions and celery in skillet with 1 stick butter.
Be careful, don't burn.
Add bread, chicken and all other ingredients.
Make your dressing fairly thin so it won't be dry.
Pour in pan and put butter on top before baking.
Cook about 1 hour.

title: oatmeal spice cake
directions: Pour water over oats.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in oatmeal and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into large cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into container and chill until set.
Spread on sour cream.
Add the rest of the mixture and chill again.
Chopped nuts may be added in the second pouring.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Combine with the sugar, milk, vanilla and salt along with cornstarch.
Cook in a double boiler until mixture thickens.
Mix powdered sugar with peanut butter until crumbly. Sprinkle 1/2 of this mixture in bottom of pie crust.
Pour pudding mixture over the peanut butter mixture.

title: crumb-coated potato halves
directions: To prepare collard Greens, wash well and drain.
Place 1/2 to 1 pound of Ham Hock to every 5 pounds of collards in a large pot with 2 quarts of water.
Simmer 45 minutes and then add collards, a pinch of sugar, 1 tablespoon of crushed red peppers, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook and additional 45 minutes or until collards are tender.
It's best to cook the meat for the collards first before adding them to the pot.

title: gary's cookies
directions: Mix sugars, pudding, vanilla and butter until smooth.
Add eggs; beat until smooth and gradually add flour, soda, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake at 375° until slightly brown on top.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream together the margarine and peanut butter.
Add the powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix together until you can form small balls.
Melt the wax and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Dip one ball at a time into mix with a toothpick.
Lay on waxed paper until dry.

title: lipton onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. In 13 X 9-inch baking pan combine all ingredients until evenly coated. Bake uncovered, stirring occasionally for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown. Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except kisses. Blend with mixer. Shape into balls. Roll in additional sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from oven. Top with chocolate kiss; press down. Makes 3 dozen.

title: zucchini soup
directions: In heavy skillet, melt 1 tablespoon butter or margarine.
Add ground beef and cook, stirring to break into small pieces.
Drain well and set aside.

title: blueberry pudding
directions: Cook berries, sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Butter bread and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Arrange in loaf pan bread and berries in layers.
Chill several hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: easy corn relish
directions: Mix and cook over medium heat for one hour.
Seal in jars.

title: oregano garlic potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prick potatoes with a fork and bake on a cookie sheet for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove potatoes from oven, cut in quarters and place in bowl.
While hot, toss with oil, salt, pepper, garlic, and oregano.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well. Heat oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat. To the oil, add cumin mixture, chicken, onion and garlic; saut 5 minutes. Add broth and next 6 ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve with tortillas and top with cheese. Serving size: 1 1/2 cups. Serves 10.

title: german pancakes
directions: Preheat oven for 25 minutes to 425°.
In small bowl combine flour and baking powder.
Beat in eggs and milk leaving the batter a bit lumpy.
In a 10-inch skillet or pie pan, melt butter.
When butter is very hot, pour in batter all at once.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes until pancake is golden.
Serve sprinkled with powdered sugar.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix together sugar, crisco, and eggs. Add flour and milk alternately a little at a time mixing constantly. Add vanilla and mix. Pour mixture into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked vidalia onions
directions: Peel onions; core 3/4 deep.
Place in hollow baking dish.
Put approximately 1 teaspoon bouillon buds.
Add a pat of butter or margarine on top of bouillon.
Wrap or cover in foil; bake at 400° for 1 to 2 hours, until tender.
If you enjoy French onion soup, you'll love this recipe.

title: cloverleaf rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Heat the milk until lukewarm. Pour into large bowl and stir in sugar, butter and yeast. Leave 15 minutes to dissolve. Stir the egg and salt into the yeast mixture. Gradually stir in 3 1/2 cups of flour. Add just enough extra flour to obtain a rough dough. Transfer to a floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic. Place in greased bowl and cover. Put in a warm place until volume doubles. Grease 2 (12-cup) muffin pans. Punch down the dough. Cut into 4 equal pieces. Roll each piece into a rope 14-inches long. Cut each rope into 18 pieces. Roll each into a ball. Place 3 balls, side by side, in each muffin cup. Cover loosely and leave to rise until doubled in volume, 1 1/2 hours. Brush with glaze. Bake until lightly browned, about 20 minutes. Cool slightly before serving.

title: picnic salad
directions: Boil and cool the following: oil, sugar, white vinegar and salt.
Pour this mixture over vegetables. Marinate at least 24 hours (covered in the refrigerator). Drain and serve cold.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine flour and salt in a mixing bowl; add cheese and mix well.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Mix with hands until dough is smooth and ball out in a small roll. Chill.
Cut in slices and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: In a large skillet or slow cooker with browning unit, cook bacon several minutes.
Remove bacon and set aside.
Coat beef with flour and brown on all sides in bacon mixture.
Combine steak, bacon drippings, cooked bacon, seasonings, bouillon and burgundy wine in slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low for 6-8 hours or until meat is tender.
Turn control to high.
Add mushrooms; cook on high 15 min.
To thicken sauce, if desired add cornstarch (dissolved in 2 tbsp. cold water) with mushrooms.
Makes 6 servings.

title: daddy's favorite chicken
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, celery, salt, paprika, garlic salt and pepper.
Marinate chicken breasts in this mixture for several hours or overnight.
Dredge marinated breasts in bread crumbs.
Place in a casserole dish.
Melt margarine and oil together.
Pour half of this over breasts.
Bake, uncovered, about 45 minutes at 350°.
Pour remaining half of margarine mixture over chicken.
Cook for about another 15 minutes.
(To reduce fat in recipe, you may substitute plain yogurt for sour cream.)

title: broccoli bread
directions: Cook broccoli until tender, then drain.
Mix together with the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mash cranberry sauce and mix with remaining ingredients. Freeze.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Place broccoli on bottom of casserole.
Chop chicken for next layer.
Mix soup and mayonnaise; pour over chicken.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: gram's chili sauce
directions: Cook 1/2 hour.
Add spices and cook another 2 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Stir all ingredients well to blend.
Bake in two greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325° to 350°.
Cook rice according to directions.
Mix everything together.
Bake in oven 1 1/4 hours, give or take to how hot the oven is.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer, covered, until onion is cooked, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: honey rabbit
directions: Brown rabbit in a little oil.
In a 4 or 2-quart pot, mix the margarine or butter, honey, mustard, curry powder and pepper. Heat and mix, then put browned rabbit into pot.
Cover and cook on low heat about 1 hour.
Can be thickened with cornstarch, mixed into cold water.
Can be doubled.
Good over rice.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients well.
Put half of cake batter in a 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until done and de-bone.
Mix soup and Veg-All into deboned chicken.
Pour mixture into a frozen pie crust. Carefully place second frozen pie crust on top of mixture in pie crust and crimp the two pie crusts together.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 20 to 30 minutes, until pie crust is lightly brown and flaky.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: nut bread
directions: Let raise 1/2 hour.
Bake 40 or more minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together with mixer until creamy.
Layer shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes and shredded cheese.

title: baked french toast casserole with maple syrup
directions: Slice French bread into 20 (1-inch) slices.
Arrange dices in a generously buttered 9 x 13-inch flat baking dish in 2 rows, overlapping the slices.

In a large bowl, combine the eggs, half and half, milk, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt and beat with a rotary beater or whisk until blended but not to bubbly. Pour mixture over bread slices making sure all are covered evenly with the milk-egg mixture.
Spoon some of the mixture in between the slices.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, preheat oven to 350°.
Spread Praline Topping evenly over the bread and bake for 40 minutes until puffed and lightly golden. Serve with maple syrup.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: carol's pink-tomato sauce over rigatoni(enough for 1 pound of rigatoni)
directions: Place tomatoes in a strainer and rinse well under cold water. Dice tomatoes.
In a large saucepan, combine heavy cream, tomatoes, garlic, basil and salt.
Bring mixture to a simmer and cook until reduced by half.
While sauce is cooking, cook mezzani in rapidly boiling salted water, about 10 minutes.
Drain rigatoni and place on serving platter.
Pour sauce over rigatoni; sprinkle grated cheese on top.

title: tex-mex chicken and peppers
directions: In a medium frying pan, heat 2 tablespoons of the oil over high heat.
Add chicken and cook, stirring frequently, until no longer pink, about 5 minutes.
With a slotted spoon, remove the chicken to a plate.
Add remaining oil to the pan; add peppers, garlic, onion, oregano and salt.
Cook, stirring frequently, until the veggies are tender-crisp, about 5 minutes.
Return the chicken to frying pan; add salsa and black beans and heat through. Sprinkle with coriander.
Garnish with tortilla chips if desired. Alternately serve rolled up inside soft tortilla or over rice.

title: pineapple parfait
directions: In large bowl, combine sour cream, pineapple, sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice. Mix well. Layer with nuts in parfait glasses. Garnish with cherries. Chill.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Crumble bread; add eggs and chicken, removing all bones.
Mix well.
Add 3 cups of broth to this.
Saute oleo, onion and celery; add to the mixture.
Butter the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put ingredients in and pour a can of cream of mushroom soup on top. Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar in large bowl; stir in pumpkin, spice, salt, and flour.
Then gradually stir in evaporated milk.

title: scalloped chicken casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery until tender.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake in a casserole dish at 350°.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup pecans.
Make into a ball; refrigerate until firm.
Roll ball in remainder of pecans.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Peel carrots and slice.
Cook until tender.
Add green pepper. Cook 3 more minutes; drain (reserve water).
Drain pineapple; add water to juice to make 1 cup.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, vinegar and soy sauce to liquid.
Cook until bubbly.
Stir in vegetables and heat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: french dressing
directions: Pour vinegar and onion in blender and blend.
Add remaining ingredients and blend very well in blender.
Store in refrigerator.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In large skillet over medium-high heat, cook and stir steak, mushrooms and onion in margarine until steak is browned and vegetables are tender.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add flour; cook and stir 1 minute.
Add water and bouillon; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in sour cream; heat through (do not boil).
Cook noodles as directed on package; drain and serve beef mixture on top.

title: t. j.'s favorite no peek chicken
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken on top of mixture and sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Cover and seal with foil.
Bake at 350° for approximately 2 hours. (But don't peek!)

title: cranberry mold
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Mix cranberries until there's no lumps.
Add juice and chill until slightly stiffened.
Fold in crushed pineapple and celery.
Cover with Saran Wrap, then foil. Use Pyrex dish, 9 x 13 x 2 1/2-inch.
Put in refrigerator until set.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion; drain well.
Add soup, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and sugar.
Simmer on low heat. Stir frequently, about 1 hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and chop meat; set aside.
Spread out Tater Tots in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs.
Add salt and pepper; set aside.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, bacon, cheese and onion in 13 x 9-inch glass dish.

title: fresh frozen coconut cake(the longer it stays in the refrigerator, the better it is)
directions: Make frosting first and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in pan; bring to boil.
Boil on medium heat 5 minutes.
Stir constantly to keep from burning. Remove from heat and stir in good chocolate chips, marshmallow, nuts and vanilla.
Grease 9 x 13 pan and cool to room temperature.

title: bible cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to butter with milk.
Beat well and bake in steeple pan 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: ricotta cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Add Ricotta cheese and mix well.
Add lemon and vanilla extracts.
Add all dry ingredients until a stiff dough forms.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool and glaze or frost lightly.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: diabetic delight
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, crumble the cake in bottom. Pour over the crumbs the pineapple and juice.
Then mix instant pudding mix according to directions on package.
Pour over pineapple.
Slice bananas on top of pudding mix and top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cloud nine biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in Crisco.
Beat egg and milk. Add to dry
mix.
Turn
on
floured
board and knead 5 times. Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Use frozen orange juice can as cutter or 1 1/2-inch cutter.
Freeze.
(Best
when frozen.) When needed, remove from freezer and
place on ungreased pan.
Bake in 425° oven for 13 to 15 minutes until brown.
Makes about 30.

title: tuna mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin into tomato soup; heat slowly until dissolved.
Beat in cream cheese.
Add onion, pepper, mayonnaise, tuna and Tabasco sauce.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart oiled mold and chill.
Great party appetizer.
Serve with Town House or Ritz type crackers.

title: oriental turkey salad
directions: Place frozen vegetables in a colander; run hot water over vegetables just until thawed.
Drain well.
For salad, in a large salad bowl, combine torn romaine or spinach, chopped turkey and thawed vegetables; set aside.

title: smoked oyster dip
directions: Whip together the ingredients with a fork until light and fluffy.
Fold in one tin of smoked oysters (drained and chopped). Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with grahams.
Make pudding using 3 1/2 cups milk.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
Pour half of mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of grahams and pour remaining mixture over these grahams.
Add top layer of grahams and spread frosting over them.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: honey-grilled pork tenderloins
directions: Trim fat from tenderloins.
Butterfly tenderloins by making a lengthwise cut in each, cutting to within 1/4 inch of the other side.
Place in a Ziploc bag with soy sauce, ginger and garlic. Refrigerate at least 3 hours, turning occasionally.
Combine sugar, honey and oil in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Coat grill rack with cooking spray.

title: moma neel's cornbread dressing
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Pour into a well greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes or until brown. Immediately chop into pieces in a mixing bowl.
Add other five ingredients.
Generously grease a 13 x 9-inch pan and pour mixture.
Bake until bubbly, about 20 minutes.
Serve with egg gravy.

title: texas taco soup
directions: In a large saucepan, brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Bring to a boil, then let simmer for about one hour.
Serve with grated cheese and/or a small amount of sour cream.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Combine juice and rind with beaten egg.
Pour into dry ingredients, mixing just enough to dampen.
Fold in nuts and chopped berries.
Spoon into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Spread sides and corners slightly higher than center.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, until crust is golden and toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Store overnight for easy slicing (16 slices).

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo real well.
Then add eggs, one at a time. Fold in flour along with the cream.
Add extract and bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
When cool, eat plain or frost with vanilla or lemon frosting.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown green pepper in margarine in skillet.
Set aside.
Brown steak.
Put garlic in (do not drain drippings).
Add oregano, catsup, sherry, mushroom soup and 1 tomato.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender.
Add remaining 2 tomatoes, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Cook until just heated.
Serve with rice.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan or a Bundt pan (if a Bundt pan is used, use excess batter to make 6 muffins).
Sift flour, salt and sugar together; cream into shortening, adding eggs, one at a time. Stir in buttermilk, mixing well.

Dissolve baking soda in the boiling water and add, with vanilla, to the batter, mixing well. Pour into baking pan and bake at 320° for approximately 1 hour. Cake should spring back to the touch when done.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Coat steak strips with mixture of flour, salt and pepper. Brown meat and onion in 1/3 cup butter.
Add beef bouillon and red wine and allow to simmer for 30 minutes.
While meat is simmering, cook sliced mushrooms in 3 tablespoons butter until soft.
When meat is tender, remove from heat.
Add mushrooms and stir. Combine sour cream, tomato paste and Worcestershire sauce and gradually add to meat and mushrooms.
Put back on heat and simmer. Do not boil.
Serve with rice.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender at one time.
Mix well.
Pour into 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.
Pineapple may be omitted and use whole can of coconut if desired.

title: cinnamon dough
directions: Mix flour, salt and cinnamon in bowl, making a well in the center.
Pour in water.
Mix with hands until dough forms a ball (may need to add flour or water).
Knead on lightly floured board until smooth and satiny (about 5 minutes).
Wrap and refrigerate 20 minutes before using.
Model with it (3/4 inch thick for ornaments).
To add small pieces, moisten with water and press on. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until hard.
Sandpaper and varnish when cool.
This dough smells good, but it's not for eating.

title: asparagus supreme
directions: Cook asparagus, starting with potato chips.
Layer chips, asparagus, sliced eggs and soup.
Cover with cheese and bake until cheese is melted.

title: soy cheese balls
directions: Mix thoroughly together.
Shape into 24 balls, then roll each in wheat germ or bread crumbs.
Place on sprayed cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: corn relish
directions: In a 3-quart casserole dish, combine first 6 ingredients. Gradually add vinegar and water, stirring well.
Cover and microwave 15 to 17 minutes, stirring after 7 minutes.
Stir when finished cooking.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Shape beef into a patty, place in center of foil with potato, carrot and onion.
Sprinkle with seasoning if desired.
Fold foil over and seal well;
place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. One serving.

title: sauerkraut-kielbasa with onions, potatoes and apples
directions: Open sauerkraut and put in pot.
Add potatoes and onions, quartered.
Let boil for about 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, cut up kielbasa in 1/4-inch pieces.
Fry until brown in oil in skillet. Take meat and set aside.

title: microwave sweet potato
directions: Scrub potato and poke several times with a fork.
Place on paper plate and cover with another paper plate.
Microwave for 3 to 4 minutes or until tender and done.
Turn potato after 2 minutes of cooking.

title: hummus with tomato relish
directions: Drain the chickpeas, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Squeeze the juice from the lemon.
Mince the garlic.
Puree the chickpeas and reserved liquid, lemon juice, garlic, tahini, oil and salt in a food processor until very smooth.
Chop the onion and tomato and toss with parsley.
Put the hummus on a plate and arrange the relish next to it.
Drizzle the hummus with additional olive oil if you like.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together except chocolate chips.
After thoroughly mixed, add chocolate chips. Bake on ungreased cookie pan.
Drop mix by spoonfuls into pan, about 2 inches apart.
Bake until golden brown, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together in one bowl and beat.
Spread evenly on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix salt, sugars, spices and sweet potatoes.
Beat eggs slightly; add milk.
Combine sweet potato and milk mixture.
Add melted butter.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake 10 minutes at 450°, then 35 minutes at 350° until browned and puffy.

title: apricot carrot loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Chop apricots finely.
Sift the dry ingredients into a bowl; set aside. In another larger bowl, beat together the oil, eggs and sugar until fluffy and lemon colored.
Add vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients and mix until smooth.
Blend in the carrots and apricots.
Pour into the prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour or until a skewer inserted in center comes out clean.
Invert onto a wire rack to cool.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Toast chopped pecans or walnuts in 350° oven.
Mix flour, butter and toasted nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and margarine.
Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually add white sugar.
Stir pumpkin and lemon juice into the egg mixture.
Mix together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt. Fold into pumpkin mixture.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix both cans of soup together with the milk.
Add this mixture to your potatoes.
Mix until all potato slices are covered.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add dabs of oleo onto the top of potatoes.
When potatoes have 10 minutes left to cook, cover with shredded cheese.
Put back into oven.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cool cherry salad
directions: Combine milk and Cool Whip in a large bowl.
Fold in cherries until color is consistent.
Smooth top and decorate with mandarin oranges.
Serves 12.

title: chicken pie
directions: Bone
chicken
and
put
in bottom of baking dish.
Put broth, soup,
salt and pepper in pan and bring to boil.
Pour over chicken.
Mix
flour,
milk
and margarine together (mix well). Pour over top and bake at 400° until brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well until smooth, then add enough maraschino cherry juice to make pink.

title: layered banana pineapple dessert
directions: Mix crackers, sugar and margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press firmly on bottom.
Layer with sliced bananas.

title: hamburger balls
directions: Roll hamburger into balls.
Poke a hole in middle and put stuffing in.
Cover stuffing back up; brown.
Put into casserole dish.
Mix soups and pour on top.
Serve with egg noodles.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Boil broth and add tortellini; add next 5 ingredients. Simmer all for 10 minutes.
Garnish with fresh parmesan cheese or any flavored shredded cheese.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Sift together into a mixing bowl, flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add vinegar, vanilla, salad oil and cold water.
Beat until smooth.

title: fruit sherbet
directions: Combine fruits and sugar in food processor or blender.
Pour into freezer can and add water and Pet milk.
Freeze according to freezer directions.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: diabetic golden spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Have eggs at room temperature for best volume when beaten.
In small mixing bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, spices and salt.
Make a well in the center. Add oil, egg yolks, pumpkin and Sucaryl; beat until smooth.
In larger mixing bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar; beat until very stiff peaks form.
Gently fold batter into stiffly beaten egg whites until just blended; do not stir.
Turn into greased 9-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until firm to touch.
Invert cake to cool.

title: spicy buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Dredge chicken in dry salad dressing mix.
Dip in mixture of butter, pepper sauce and vinegar.
Arrange in baking pan and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 25-30 minutes. Turn, sprinkle with paprika and bake at 450° for 20-25 minutes, or until brown.
Serve with chunky blue cheese salad dressing/dip and celery sticks.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Place warm water into a mixing bowl.
Stir in yeast to soften. Stir in sugar and salt.
Stir in Bisquick a little at a time, mixing well to form a soft dough.
Knead on a lightly floured surface 2 to 3 minutes, until smooth.
Pat or roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with 1 1/2-inch small biscuit cutter.
Place on a baking sheet; cover with wet paper towel (cloth is too heavy). Let rise in a warm place about 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes until done and golden brown.
Can be baked ahead and reheated 2 or 3 minutes, just before serving.
Makes about 36 (1 1/2-inch) biscuits.
Great yeast-bread aroma without all the work.

title: chicken and asparagus pasta
directions: Melt butter in
a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add onions; cook 5 minutes.
Add asparagus, chicken broth, salt and pepper; cook 3 minutes.
Stir in heavy cream and orange peel; boil until slightly thickened, 3 minutes.
Stir in chicken; heat through.
Toss with cooked linguine.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream peanut butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar and milk. Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour in 9-inch graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: rich and creamy slaw
directions: Pour over vegetables.
Mix gently and chill for several hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream shortening well.
Add sugar and beat.
Add eggs; beat again.
Add flour and bananas alternately.
Cook in bread pan (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch) in a moderate oven (350°) for about 70 minutes.

title: barbecued fish
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan. Add all other ingredients except fish; stir well. Place fish on a sheet of heavy foil and pour sauce over fish. Seal foil making sure there is no leakage. Place on a grill; turn every 20 minutes, being careful not to tear foil. Cook for 1 1/2 hours. Remove from foil (reserving the sauce) and place on grill for 10 minutes. Turn and cook another 10 minutes basting with sauce. Serves 6.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Beat egg white until foamy.
Add coffee, sugar and cinnamon and beat until stiff.
Add pecans and spread on buttered sheet. Bake at 300° to 325° for 20 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese deluxe
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Rinse macaroni and set aside.
Combine next 6 ingredients.
Add macaroni and stir well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oven baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut them into chunks. In a plastic food bag or a bowl, put all ingredients and shake or stir until potatoes are well coated.
Place potatoes into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400°, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes or until golden brown and cooked through.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
(If using glass pan, reduce temperature to 325°.)
Flour and grease pans.
Sift flour and spices together. Beat eggs and add to sugar and oil.
Add buttermilk and vanilla. Add flour and mashed bananas to mixture, starting and finishing with flour.
Bake for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Mixture makes 2 loaves of bread.

title: garlic cheese ball
directions: Let cheese sit at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Blend both cheeses, green onions and garlic until completely mixed.
Set mixture in refrigerator for 20 minutes.
When firm, roll cheese in chopped nuts.
Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours.
Serve with a variety of crackers.

title: apple crunch
directions: Arrange sliced apples in baking dish.
Sprinkle about 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 teaspoon nutmeg over the top of apples.

title: barb's beef tenderloin
directions: Wash tenderloin and pat dry.
Rub with minced garlic and press black pepper onto sides.
Combine Worcestershire and soy sauce. Marinate 2 to 3 hours at room temperature.

title: lemony grilled chicken
directions: Combine lemon juice, butter, thyme and pepper sauce in a small bowl.
Sprinkle chicken with pepper.
Place chicken, bone side down, on grill over hot coals.
Brush with basting sauce.
Grill for 40 minutes, turning once.
Baste frequently with sauce.
Serve with remaining basting sauce.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: the best corn bread this side of...monroe(foolproof!  can't mess this one up.)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lime-cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in a medium bowl, stirring well.
Stir in cold water.
Chill until mixture is the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold mayonnaise into gelatin mixture.
Add cottage cheese and pineapple, stir well. Pour gelatin mixture into a 6-cup mold coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Chill gelatin mixture until firm.
Unmold salad onto lettuce leaves, if desired.

title: meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except Micro Shake and half of the can of tomato sauce.
Blend well.
Shape meat mixture into loaf pan.
Pour leftover tomato sauce over meat and sprinkle with Micro Shake.
Microwave covered with wax paper on High for 14 to 18 minutes or until meat thermometer registers 145°.
Let stand, covered with wax paper, for 3 to 5 minutes before served. Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Baste ribs while baking slowly.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle on top, large amount of Parmesan cheese and 2/3 cup chopped walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: czarist chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken with water and bouillon; cool and remove from bone.
Cut into thin strips.
In large bowl, place chicken, potatoes, pickles, onion and celery.
Put pepper and salt with mayonnaise, sour cream and Worcestershire sauce.
Gently add to chicken mixture.
Cover and chill.
Garnish with boiled egg quarter and tomato wedges.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Mix all ingredients.

title: grilled pork chops with pineapple
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Marinate pork chops for 2 hours in the sauce.
Cook chops 8 inches from heat, basting often with sauce.
Turn chops frequently until done.
Heat pineapple slices on the grill.
Brush with butter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cloves.
Continue to heat pineapple until sugar dissolves.
Serve with pork chops.
Serves 6.

title: simple punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water, then add juice and punch. Freeze half of mixture to slush.
Add to mixture and before serving, add ginger ale.
Yield: 2 gallons.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cook bacon until crisp - set aside.
Remove stems from mushrooms and reserve for another use.
Heat butter in large skillet.
Saute mushroom caps on each side for 1-2 minutes. Mushrooms will still be firm.
Set aside to drain, open side down. Combine cream cheese, bacon (crumbled) and chives.	Fill mushroom caps with cream cheese mixture.
Place caps under broiler until lightly browned.
Cool slightly before serving.

title: creamy lemon chicken
directions: Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice and lemon pepper seasoning together.
Dip chicken in mixture, then place in pan or crock-pot.
Put onions and green pepper on top of chicken.
Pour remainder of sauce over chicken mixture.
Cook until chicken is done or "all day" in crockpot.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: mom's fudge
directions: Combine chocolate chips, walnuts, marshmallows, butter and vanilla in large bowl. Grease large cookie sheet (with sides) with Crisco or margarine. Combine sugar and evaporated milk in large pot. While stirring constantly, bring sugar and milk to a boil (approx. 7 - 8 minutes); continue stirring while it boils for 6 minutes. (It is very important to stir continuously for the allotted time!). Pour sugar and milk mixture into the chocolate chips and marshmallow bowl; stir vigorously until chocolate chips, marshmallows and butter have melted. Pour combined mixture onto large cookie sheet and refrigerate overnight or until slightly hardened. Cut into bite size pieces. Can be refrigerated for immediate use or frozen. Not good for mailing as it is soft fudge.

title: pepper steak verde(low-fat style)
directions: Cut steak into thin 1 1/2-inch strips. Combine soy sauce, lemon juice and Kitchen Bouquet.
Add steak pieces to sauce mixture and stir to coat.
Sprinkle with flour and saute steak pieces in butter (diet).
Add green pepper and water.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until meat is fork-tender.
(Serve with salad and fruit, for a delicious meal.)
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients in large container. For a cup of hot chocolate, put 1/3 cup of mix and 2/3 cup hot water in a mug. Makes 4 gallons.

title: lime pickles
directions: In crock, combine cucumbers, lime and 1 gallon water.
Let soak for 24 hours.
Rinse well and cover with cold water.
Let stand 3 hours; drain.
Heat remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand overnight.
The next day, boil cucumbers with brine for 35 minutes or until transparent.
Pack into hot jars.
Green food coloring may be added, if desired.
Process 15 minutes in hot water bath to assure that jars seal.
Makes 10 to 12 pints.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Grease baking sheet heavily.
Combine sugar, corn syrup and salt in a 3-quart baking dish.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave at High until light brown, 10 to 13 minutes.
Stir 1 or 2 times. Stir in remaining ingredients until light and foamy.
Quickly spread on greased baking sheet as thin as possible for brittle candy.
When cool, crush into pieces.
Enjoy.

title: buffet carrots
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add flour, seasonings and milk; cook until thick.
Parboil carrots 10 minutes.

title: stuffed shrimp
directions: Saute celery, onion and bell pepper in butter.
Mix in crab, cracker crumbs, salt, parsley, dry mustard and cayenne pepper to taste.
If dry, add a little milk to moisten.
Place a heaping tablespoonful of stuffing on top of each shrimp, then wrap with bacon.
Broil shrimp, basting with butter, lemon juice and dash of garlic powder.
Broil until shrimp are done.

title: simple bread
directions: Measure water into large mixing bowl. Sprinkle yeast over water. Add dry milk, sugar, salt, oil and about 3 1/2 cups flour to make a thick batter. Blend well. Beat 3 minutes at medium speed of mixer. By hand, gradually add remaining flour to form a stiff dough. Toss dough on floured surface. Knead until smooth, 1 to 2 minutes. Divide in half. Using a rolling pin, shape dough into a 6 x 12-inch rectangle. Seal edges and ends. Place seam side down into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 pan. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in size, about 1 hour. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from pans. Brush with butter. Cool on racks. Makes 2 loaves.

title: spiced crackers
directions: In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with a tight-fitting lid, place crackers in layers, sprinkling Ranch dressing mix and crushed red pepper flakes between layers; drizzle canola oil over each layer. Use remaining spices and oil before covering pan. Flip pan. When you think about it or walking through the kitchen, flip the pan for 24 hours to distribute seasonings and oil.

title: new year's cheese ball
directions: Allow cream cheese to come to room temperature.
Mix in all ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into a ball.
A brick shape is a good idea, as it is easily sliced.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Sift together in a large bowl the first 5 ingredients.
Beat together the remaining ingredients.
Combine wet and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in buttered pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zesty grilled chops
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, add chops.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 3 to 6 hours.
Grill.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together; simmer for 1 hour.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all except lemon juice and butter.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice and butter.
Makes 2 1/2 cups sauce.
Good over chicken, pork or beef.

title: lemon cake pudding
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in rind, well beaten egg yolks, milk and lemon juice.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into casserole; set in a pan of hot water.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot or cold with or without whipped cream.

title: hershey bar pound cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and blend.
Blend in Hershey's syrup.
Mix dry ingredients (cake flour, salt and baking soda) together.
Add half of the dry ingredients and half of the buttermilk into mixture.
Mix well.
Add remaining half of dry ingredients, buttermilk, nuts, vanilla and Hershey bars.
Blend well.
Grease and flour a large tube pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour to one hour and 15 minutes.

title: patty's mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cook the potatoes.
With electric hand mixer, mash potatoes.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, salt and garlic; mix well.
Put mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Use fork to make strokes on top of mixture.
Pour melted butter on top; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Place 1 layer of cake in punch bowl.
Layer pudding, pineapple, strawberries, bananas and Cool Whip.
Repeat with other layer, ending with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: fantasy angel cake
directions: Cut angel food cake in half horizontally.
Scoop out a trough in bottom layer.
Fill trough with cherry pie filling.
Put on top half of cake.
Cover cake with Dream Whip (follow directions on package).
Pour remainder of pie filling around edge of cake. Chill about 2 hours.
Serve cold.

title: greek salad with shrimp
directions: Gently toss shrimp, Feta cheese, tomatoes and scallions in a bowl.
Shake remaining ingredients together in a jar until well mixed.

title: apricot coconut balls
directions: Blend apricots, coconut and milk.
Shape into balls and roll in sugar.
Let stand until firm.

title: american chop suey
directions: Saute onions and pepper in oil until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes and salt and pepper.
Saute ground beef in frying pan. Drain and add to tomatoes.
Cook about 1/2 hour.
Cook macaroni. Drain and add to sauce.
Mix thoroughly and serve.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cover and cook 1 hour.
One-half hour before serving, add 2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce.
Serve over rice.

title: aunt donna's scotch shortbread
directions: Grease and flour 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
In a large bowl, mix butter with fingers.
Add powdered sugar 1 tablespoon at a time until creamed.
Work flour in 1/2 cup at a time.
When mixed well, pat into cake pan.
Fun for kids to mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in small squares while slightly warm.

title: jane's trifle
directions: Slice angel food cake in trifle bowl.
Pour crushed pineapple over cake.
Make Jell-O as on box.
Pour over pineapple.
Jell in refrigerator.
After Jell-O is jelled, make instant pudding as directed on box.
Pour over Jell-O.
Spread Cool Whip over instant pudding.
Cover with coconut.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until firm.

title: combico salad
directions: Cut all vegetables into bite-sized pieces.
Mix Good Seasons Dressing with oil and vinegar and shake well.
Toss dressing with all vegetables and marinate overnite.
This will keep for 2 weeks. Use a Tupperware container to seal well.
Makes a large quantity.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: easy banana cake
directions: *Do not use cake mix with pudding added.
It will fail.

title: chocolate lover's bundt cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well; add chips.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Tap pan on counter several times to release any bubbles.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes and remove cake to cooling rack.
Cool completely and frost.

title: peacocks sollys dressing
directions: Blend all in blender.

title: brandy steaks
directions: Using a wooden mallet on the flat side of a broad knife blade, pound the steak
between
pieces
of
wax
paper
until they're about 1/4-inch thick.
Set them aside.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in bowl, then add wet ingredients all at once.
Stir by hand.
Put in 9 x 12-inch pan in preheated oven of 375° for 30 minutes.
Frost with Chocolate Chip Frosting, if desired.

title: linda poor's spaghetti pie
directions: While spaghetti is still warm, combine with eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Put spaghetti in well-greased 10-inch pie plate.
With back of spoon, press it up around the sides and bottom of plate to form a crust.

title: zucchini and summer squash
directions: Cook squash 10 minutes; drain.
Combine sour cream, butter and sharp cheese; melt.
Put squash in casserole dish.
Pour on cheese mixture.
Top with grated cheese and croutons.
Bake at 375° until it bubbles.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix well and pour into a graham cracker crust.
Put in refrigerator until set.
Top with a can of cherry pie filling and return to refrigerator until set firmly.

title: spoon bread
directions: Add boiling water to meal and stir until mixed.
Allow to cool, then add melted butter, well beaten eggs, milk, salt and baking powder.
Blend well, beating with mixer or rotary egg beater.
Pour into well-greased baking dish and bake in moderate oven for about 30 minutes.

title: homemade shake 'n bake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then cut in shortening.
This may be stored in a jar or sealed and stored in freezer.
When ready to use Shake 'n Bake, dip chicken or pork chops in milk, then shake in a plastic bag with small amount of Shake 'n Bake.
Bake in a 400° oven until meat is tender, 50 to 60 minutes.

title: ooey-gooey butter bars
directions: Mix 1 egg and melted butter with cake mix.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Whip 1 pound, less 2 tablespoons powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Pour over first layer.
Mix 2 tablespoons powdered sugar with chopped nuts and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Boil the rice.
When the rice is cooked, put it away.
Get a frying pan, put it on the stove on medium heat and put the 4 tablespoons cooking oil in the pan.
When the oil is getting hot, put the garlic in.
Stir it with the cooking oil, then put the onion in.
Keep stirring, then put in the ham.
Stir for 1 minute, then add the carrots and sweet peas.
Stir well, cover and simmer for 2 minutes, or until carrots are cooked.
Add the cooked rice, then sprinkle with soy sauce.
Stir or mix it with the other ingredients.
Last thing to do is fry the eggs.
Slice them lengthwise.
Put on the top of the fried rice; sprinkle the spring onion on the top.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: mousse
directions: Stir pudding mix and milk until thick. Fold in whipped topping. Add nuts or bananas if desired. May vary by using different pudding flavors or fruits.

title: nette's chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugars together.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla to butter and sugars.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and dry oats.
Mix well.
Add Toll House chips and nuts, as desired.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Let cool.

title: green bean salad
directions: Steam beans until crisp-tender.
Rinse until cold.
Drain well and pat dry with paper towel.
Combine olive oil, lemon juice, pepper, dill, onion, brown sugar and salt.
Stir in green beans and toss.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Toss again, then chill up to 4 hours.
Serve at room temperature.
Just before serving, sprinkle on Feta cheese and toss.

title: guiltless french fries
directions: Preheat the oven at 450°.
Slice the potatoes into standard size fries, steak fries or wedges.
Coat a 10 x 13 baking pan with the no-stick cooking spray.
Place the potatoes in the baking pan in a single layer.
Spray the potatoes with the cooking spray. Bake 30 minutes, or until brown, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.
Less than 1 fat gram per serving.

title: mom's lemon cake
directions: Mix ingredients together for 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven.
Let cool about 10 minutes.
Ice while still warm.

title: holiday cheese tree
directions: Combine cold pack cheese food and cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add 1 tablespoon pimento, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce and juice; mix well.
Chill.
Drop six 1/3-cup measures of mixture into triangle shape on serving platter.
Drop remaining mixture at base of triangle.
Smooth to form tree.
Top with parsley, nuts and remaining pimento.
Serve with Triscuits wafers.

title: home fries
directions: Put Crisco in frying pan. Slice potatoes into thin slices or 1/2-inch square cubes.
Sprinkle on seasoned salt.
Cover. Fry on medium-low heat, turning occasionally, until soft and lightly browned. Great for breakfast, lunch or dinner.

title: easy dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon into boiling stew.
Cook for 15 minutes in a tightly covered pot.

title: apple pie
directions: Use a large, deep dish pie dish.
Put bottom crust in pie plate.
Peel and slice apples and put in a large bowl; add sugars, cinnamon and flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Put into pie shell. Sprinkle with a little more cinnamon.
Put butter (cut in small pieces) on top.
Put other pie crust on top.
Make holes with fork or cut circle.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with cheese or vanilla ice cream.

title: onion-herb batter bread
directions: Scald milk; remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, salt and butter until dissolved.
Cool.
In large bowl, dissolve yeast in water. Add cooled milk mixture.
Stir flour into yeast mixture.
Add onions and herbs.
Stir together until well blended.
Cover and let rise in warm place until tripled in bulk (45 minutes).

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion and drain.
Add Prego sauce and simmer 1/2 hour.
Cook noodles as directed.
Layer in a 13 x 9-inch dish the noodles and meat mixture.
Spread cottage cheese along top of meat with fork.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers once more.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix flour and powdered sugar; cut butter into mixture.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate fudge cookies
directions: In a double boiler, melt margarine and chocolate together. Remove from heat.
Stir in condensed milk and flour; mix well. Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Cover; chill for at least 4 hours.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook vegetables, then drain well. Mix with soup and sour cream. Cover with cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: holiday crescents
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
In another bowl stir together evaporated milk, vanilla and softened butter; add to flour mixture.
Stir well and add finely chopped nuts.
Take a teaspoon of dough and shape into 2 1/2 inch strip, forming half moon or crescent.
Place an inch apart on ungreased pan.
Bake on top shelf of oven at 370° for 12 minutes.
Roll at once in powdered sugar or colored sprinkles.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Combine beef and onions in skillet. Cook until meat is lightly browned.
Drain. Add salt and pepper.
Stir in catsup and tomato sauce.
Heat thoroughly. Turn into casserole (8-inch square) sprayed with Pam. Cut cheese into thin strips and sprinkle over meat.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spiced white beans
directions: Brown onion and celery in butter.
Put soaked beans, celery, onion, thyme, basil, ginger, garlic and ham in crock-pot and cook for 12 hours on low.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: sweet kugel *
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
While still warm, stir in butter to melt, then add all ingredients except for dry cereal.
Grease 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan and pour contents in.
Top with crushed cereal. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage peas and corn
directions: Parboil sausages for approximately 10 minutes.
Cut sausages into small (1/2 to 1/4-inch) pieces.
Mix with peas and creamed corn in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine milk and cornstarch in a small pan.
Stir until smooth.
Add salt, pepper and butter.
Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Heat until boiling.
Let boil for 1 minute.
Mix with sausage.
Heat in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with rice, mashed potatoes or alone.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients
in
a	large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil,
stirring	until
dry ingredients are moistened. Do not beat.
Stir
in
vanilla,
pineapple,
cup
nuts and bananas. Pour in three 9-inch pans greased and floured.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: red cabbage
directions: Wash red cabbage and slice very fine in large pot.
Mix cabbage, apples, vinegar, water and butter plus red food color (about 1 teaspoon).
Cover pot.
After 1/2 hour, add sugar; mix well, cover and simmer for the rest of time, another 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until cabbage is tender.
When cabbage is done, add red currant jelly and cook for 10 more minutes.
The flavor should be sweet and sour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan or two 9 x 9-inch pans.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Fix cake mix as directed on box for 2 round cakes.
Put one cake mix in bottom of punch bowl.
Put holes in this cake.
On top of this, put 1/2 of pineapple, then a layer of pudding and strawberries.
On top of strawberries, put other cake and repeat all of the layers.
On the top, put your Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and strawberries.
Chill.
Spoon to serve.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve the juice.
Mix the pineapple, carrots, nuts and raisins together; set aside.
Take the pineapple juice and cream cheese and blend them together, add the brown sugar and mix well.
Pour over the salad and mix well.

title: red hot salad
directions: In one bowl, mix red hots and boiling water.
In another bowl, mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Mix the 2 mixtures together and let set slightly in refrigerator.
Add applesauce, diced apples, celery and chopped pecans.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish and chill until set.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: In a large saucepan, combine chili sauce, ketchup, grape jelly, brown sugar, onion and lemon juice and warm over medium-low heat. Meanwhile, in a large bowl, mix beef, salt, tomato sauce and bread crumbs together and roll into small meatballs.
Add meatballs to sauce gradually and cook over medium heat for 35 to 40 minutes or until done, turning carefully from time to time so they don't break up.
Refrigerate overnight to let flavors mix; skim off any fat from top.
When ready to serve, just rewarm.

title: potatoes ala verna
directions: Slice potatoes like thick potato chips.
Slice onions and separate into rings or cut into large chunks.
Put in microwavable casserole; salt and pepper to taste.
Use just enough oil to coat vegetables or dot lightly with butter.
Add water to bowl and cook in microwave until potatoes are tender.
Cover dish while cooking. Potatoes will cook in 10 to 15 minutes.

title: holiday mincemeat bread
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Combine beaten egg, milk, brown sugar, melted shortening and mincemeat.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until the flour is moistened.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for one hour.
Let stand 24 hours before slicing.
Makes one loaf.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, and chill for 1 hour. After chilling, add flour and pecans to first mixture.
Shape into balls, about the size of a small marble.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 250° 1 hour.
Roll in powdered sugar immediately after removing from oven.
Yield: 90-100 small cookies.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions until tender.
Spread in greased casserole pan.
Mix onion, celery, cheese and mayonnaise; spread over vegetables.
Melt oleo; mix with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: big five
directions: In a large greased casserole, place all potatoes, then meat, salt (lightly), then onion, then beef soup and then celery soup. Cover and bake at 400° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are done.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken until done. Reserve 2 cups chicken stock.
Remove meat from chicken and put in stock.
Lightly saute onion and rice in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add to chicken and stock.
Add the chopped tomatoes.
Add Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Boil all together for a few minutes.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: grilled duck breasts
directions: Cut duck breasts into strips 1/2-inch wide and wash well. Marinate duck breasts in soy sauce, salt, ginger and vinegar in sealed container in refrigerator for 4 hours.
Remove from marinade sauce and wash well.
Pat dry.
Slice jalapeno peppers into 1/4-inch strings and remove seeds.
Wrap slice of duck breast around jalapeno strip.
Secure with toothpick.
Cut bacon strips in half.
Wrap bacon strips around duck breast and secure on toothpick.
Grill until bacon is crisp and duck is tender and slightly pink.
(Tastes better if duck is not overcooked.)

title: sloppy joes
directions: Saute ground beef in oil.
Cook until all red is gone.
Add onion and bell pepper and saute until soft.
Then add mustard, vinegar and ketchup to taste.
Add enough water to cook and dilute down ketchup.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes on medium heat or until done. Use covered skillet.

title: mouth waterin' chili
directions: *You may substitute another pound or two of meat for the beans.

title: whipped pudding frosting
directions: Cook the flour and milk in a small saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until very thick.
Be careful not to let the mixture scorch.
Cool completely.
Cream sugar, margarine, shortening and vanilla until fluffy.
Add the flour mixture and continue beating until consistency of whipped cream.
Clean bowl and beaters often to be sure sugar is dissolved.
Mixture should be smooth, with no grainy taste of sugar.
Makes about 3 cups.
May be used as a filling or frosting.

title: cold peach soup
directions: Put all ingredients (except sour cream and nutmeg) into a blender or food processor and blend until smooth.
Then garnish with sour cream and nutmeg.

title: reception salad
directions: Drain the juice from the pineapple and bring to a boil.
Pour over the Jell-O and mix well.
When it begins to thicken, add the other ingredients in order given.
Let stand until set.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla together.
Roll into balls (about 1 inch).
Place on a large cookie sheet and chill in freezer a few minutes.
Melt chocolate and paraffin wax in a double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate and put on waxed paper.
Keep chocolate on low temperature while dipping. These freeze well.

title: beef roast with winter fruit
directions: Pour water over apricots and prunes; reserve.
Mix salt, ginger and pepper; rub over beef roast.
Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Cook beef in oil until brown on all sides; drain.
Add onions, wine and garlic.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover tightly and simmer on top of range or in 325° oven 2 hours.
Drain apricots and prunes. Add apricots, prunes and mushrooms to Dutch oven.
Cover and cook about 1 hour or until beef is tender.

title: grits souffle
directions: Bring water to a boil with 1 teaspoon salt.
Cook grits and add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup(lighter eating - 2 points)
directions: Remove tough ends from broccoli, chop stems and florets. Put onion and garlic in a 2-quart saucepan with 1/4 c. water and simmer until onion is soft, about 10 minutes; spoon into large pot. Add broccoli and broth to onion mixture and bring to a boil over high heat. Once boiling, turn down and simmer until broccoli is soft but still green, about 8 minutes. Do not cover pot while broccoli is cooking or it will turn gray. Remove soup from heat and puree in batches in a blender until smooth. (Note: Be careful not to overfill blender, the hot liquid can splatter.) Add evaporated milk and hot pepper sauce, and season with salt and pepper. Yields about 1 3/4 c. per serving.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar, salad oil and salt for five minutes; cool and add to remaining ingredients.
Let set overnight.

title: gazpacho
directions: Heat tomato juice to boiling; dissolve bouillon cube in juice. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill for several hours.

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients (flour, cocoa and baking soda).
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch square pan at 350° for 25 to 40 minutes.
Cool and top with your favorite frosting.

title: rum punch
directions: Mix all together. Stir well and serve.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Fill a 9 x 13-inch pan with sliced peaches.
Sprinkle almond extract into peaches.
Mix flour, butter and 1 cup brown sugar into a crumbly texture.
Crumble over peaches.
With fingers, add another 1 cup brown sugar and sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve warm with cream.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage, carrots and onion.
Mix together.

title: old-time peppermint cake
directions: Grease and dust with cocoa 2 (9-inch) layer pans.

title: easy noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown beef with onion and garlic.
Drain well.
Mix in tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mix in zucchini; cook for additional 10 minutes.
Blend in noodles.

title: shrimp dip
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Let chill several hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Boil water and melt butter, then add flour, cheese, salt and paprika.
Stir and cook 3 minutes.
Add egg.
Beat with wooden spoon until stiff.
Place by 1/2 teaspoonful on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Reduce to 350° and bake until puffs are dry, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Fry hamburger in a large pot.
Add chicken broth, water, onion soup mix, celery, tomatoes and frozen vegetables.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add the macaroni and simmer 10 minutes.
Salt and pepper may be added to taste.
(I do not add salt or pepper; onion soup gives it enough flavor).

title: herbed corn-on-the-cob
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a small bowl.
Stir well. Spread herb mixture over corn and place each ear on a piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Wrap tightly.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes, turning occasionally.
Yields 4 servings.

title: smoked sausage and pinto beans
