directions: Fry in 2 tablespoons oil your onions and sliced up sausage. Place in saucepan 1 cup water and one bouillon cube and bring to boil.
Take off heat and add instant rice.
Set aside and let rice swell.
Then add to rice the chili peppers, sausage and onion and pinto beans; then top with shredded cheese.
Let stand until cheese melts.
(Can place in oven for a minute.)

title: "sunday morning breakfast casserole"(cooks while you get ready!)
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch cake pan with Pam.
Spread croutons evenly across bottom of pan.
Sprinkle cooked sausage over croutons.
Mix eggs and milk together and pour over sausage and croutons.
Spread mushroom pieces and cheese over top.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Freezes (cooked) very well.

title: white overnight salad
directions: Beat eggs and sugar and put in double boiler; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice.
Beat whipping cream and fold cooled, cooked mixture into the cream.
Fold in fruit and put in refrigerator overnight and eat.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill for 1 hour.
Shape and bake at 400°.

title: fancy sweet bread
directions: Melt butter in Bundt pan.
Add cinnamon, sugar and allspice. Stir until blended.
Sprinkle chopped nuts in bottom of Bundt pan. Drag each biscuit through the melted butter mixture.
Stand each biscuit on its side and push them together, end to end, in the Bundt pan.
It will be tight, but continue pushing until all is in the pan.
Cook 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and turn onto plate.

title: blackened swordfish
directions: Fry in lemon butter 3 minutes per side, uncovered.
Apply or shake Pacifica blackened seasoning on both sides and cook for approximately 1 minute each side. Serve with rice pilaf and salad of your choice or vegetable.
For those Cajun cooks, you can shake blackened seasoning on your rice and salad, if you have a spicy tooth.

title: weight watchers strawberry pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thick.
Cool about 20 minutes. Place strawberries in a baked graham cracker crust. Pour filling over strawberries.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese dinner according to directions.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: soft tacos
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain well.
Add taco seasoning mix and water.
Stir.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally until liquid is reduced.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine enchilada sauce and soups.
Set aside.
Spoon meat mixture into taco shells.
Arrange shells in two 9 x 9-inch square pans, in upright position by leaning them against each other.
Pour combined sauces over the shells evenly.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Makes 18 tacos.

title: savory spaghetti sauce
directions: Slice pineapple lengthwise into quarters through stem end to crown.
Remove each quarter in one piece from rind.
Cut crosswise into 1/2-inch thick pieces.
Stir together sugar, pineapple juice, vinegar, cinnamon stick, cloves and red pepper flakes in medium size nonaluminum saucepan.
Bring to boiling.
Lower heat; simmer 15 minutes.
Add pineapple pieces to saucepan.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until pineapple is tender.

title: cranberry-apple mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and salt in boiling water.
Break up cranberry sauce with fork.
Add gelatin mix.
Chill, until very thick. Fold in apples.
Chill until firm.

title: graham bread
directions: Mix all together. Put in bread tins. Let rise for 1 hour. Bake slowly about 1 hour.

title: pear jello salad
directions: First Layer:
Dissolve 1 package of jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Pour in an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan. Cool until partially set.

title: old world noodles
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Combine noodles with remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased large flat baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: party potatoes
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a blender and blend.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with paprika and chives.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
May substitute onion salt for garlic.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put popped corn in a very large bowl.
Bring to a boil the butter, corn syrup, white and brown sugars and salt.
Lower temperature to simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over popcorn and stir well.
Place on 2 greased cookie sheets and put in a 250° oven for 1 hour. Stir each 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: peanut butter thumbprints
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, beat butter, brown sugar and peanut butter until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together flour, baking powder and baking soda. Gradually add to peanut butter mixture.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in peanuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until cookies are just set.
Press thumb gently in center of each cookie; cool slightly.
Remove cookies from sheet.
Cool completely.
Prepare filling.
Spoon or pipe about 1/2 teaspoon filling into each thumbprint.

title: orange slush
directions: Boil sugar and 1 c. water for 3 minutes.
Pour over orange juice.
Stir until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze. Remove from freezer 45 minutes before serving and "chunk" with spoon until slushy.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spread mixture in large dish or bowl and refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: winter vegetables
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Add Brussels sprouts.
Cook for 10 additional minutes.
Drain and reserve 1/4 cup of water.
Place vegetables in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in bowl. Add mayonnaise, vinegar, salt and pepper.

title: leaf lettuce greek salad
directions: Use a large bowl (not wooden).
Wash and dry lettuce.
Tear into small pieces and refrigerate.
In small bowl, mix remaining ingredients; cover and refrigerate.
Toss greens with dressing just before serving.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake the salmon.
Add the crumbs, milk, eggs, butter, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Mix and bake in a buttered bread pan in 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Serve plain or with cream of mushroom soup.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Add flour until dough is soft.
Turn on floured board and leave for 15 minutes.
Roll and let sit.
Cut into small squares and drop into chicken broth.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken breasts in casserole.
Add cheese on chicken breasts.
Pour soup over chicken and cheese.
Make stuffing. Spread over top and put in oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Delicious and easy.

title: quick cheeseburger bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook meat and onion in a 10-inch skillet until the meat is brown; drain.
Stir in soup, vegetables and milk.
Stir Bisquick and water in a dish until moistened; spread evenly into baking dish.
Spread meat mixture over batter.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: brownies
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Spread into shallow 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Add 2 tablespoons salt to the 4 quarts of cucumbers.
Add the 1 tablespoon salt to the onions.
Let set 2 hours; drain and dry real well.
I use a towel.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and boil.
Pour over cucumbers and onions and boil all together for 5 minutes and seal.
Good on sandwiches, salads and vegetables.

title: spinach cheese bake
directions: Drain spinach thoroughly, squeezing out liquid.
In skillet, cook sausage until brown; drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce; set aside.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit together.
It is ready and great and good for you.
Keep refrigerated.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add 1/4 cup of the milk and bananas.
Mix 2 minutes with mixer on low speed.
Add eggs, 1/4 cup milk and nuts.
Beat 1 minute.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken salad sandwiches(for a crowd!)
directions: Season boiled chicken to taste and cool in refrigerator. Chop well in food processor.
Chop eggs and mix with mayonnaise and seasoning.
Makes 100 sandwiches.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Saute onion in bacon grease and drain.
Combine all ingredients and pour over beans.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: cheese bacon puffs
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, drain and crumble.
Combine with rest of ingredients.
Season to taste.
Chill overnight.
Spread on Melba rounds.
Broil until bubbly.
Makes 50 puffs.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients together.
Combine all ingredients and add to strawberry mixture.
Stir together and mix thoroughly. Fold in nuts.
Pour into two 9 x 5-inch greased and floured pans. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth.
Pour into ice cream freezer. Fill rest of the way with whole milk.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except marshmallows and nuts.
Mix until smooth.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes, then top each cookie with marshmallow half and return to oven for one minute. Remove.
Cool, then frost with chocolate icing and decorate with nuts, etc.

title: low-fat chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add all other ingredients. Beat together for 3 minutes.
Pour into pan (approximately 8 x 2 1/2 x 5-inch).
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Turn onto wire rack and allow to cool.
Frost as desired.

title: mazetti
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add celery, onion, garlic salt and water.
Cover and steam until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Add noodles to beef mixture.
Mix in soup, undrained mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Spread mixture in 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
(Dish may be refrigerated up to 24 hours.)
Place in cold oven; set at slow 250°.
Bake, uncovered, until bubbly, about 1 hour.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into crusts.
Serve chilled.

title: ham, broccoli bake
directions: In large bowl, blend cheese, soup and milk.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain; cook onions in butter until tender.
Add onions, broccoli, ham, uncooked rice and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix all together.
Turn into 2 (1 1/2-quart) casseroles.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry butter
directions: In a large stainless steel or enamel kettle, combine cranberries and juice; cook until cranberries have popped and are soft, about 20 minutes.
Puree cranberries in a food processor. Return cranberries to kettle.
Add maple syrup, honey and cinnamon; cook until thick, 10 to 15 minutes.
Spoon into clean hot half-pint jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace; seal.
Process for 10 minutes in a simmering water bath.
Makes six half-pint jars.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Get cheese, sausage, dough and tomato sauce.
Slice the sausage into small bits.
Shape the dough into a circle.
On the dough put tomato sauce.
Then the cheese will go on.
You put on sausage and bake.
You bake it at 425° for 10 minutes.
That is how you make pizza.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes.
Pare thinly and remove eyes. Heat 1-inch salted water to boiling.
Add potatoes.
Cover tightly.
Heat to boiling and cook 30 to 35 minutes or until tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat
eggs, add sugar and milk.
Place in double boiler and cook, stirring constantly until mixture coats spoon.

title: hot peppers
directions: Boil peppers for 3 minutes.
Drain and pack in jars.
Boil Wesson oil, ketchup, sugar, vinegar and salt for 30 minutes.
Pour over peppers; cover and seal.

title: barbecued chicken wings
directions: Cut off tips of wings and cut remainder of wing in half.
Wash and place in shallow baking dish.

title: grandma's one-bowl applesauce cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Cut in butter and add molasses and applesauce.
Blend well.
Stir in raisins.
Bake in greased and floured 8-inch square pans at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: self-frosting date cake
directions: Mix dates, boiling water and baking soda.
Let cool.
Cream margarine, sugar and eggs; add to date mixture.
Sift flour, salt and soda; add to the mixture. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread chocolate chips, brown sugar and chopped nuts on top.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Spread dressing over top.
Sprinkle few more bacon bits on top of that.

title: roast of any kind
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour over roast and bake in 350 degree oven until roast is done.
Approx. 2-3 hours.
(You have roast and gravy.)

title: tostado casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain and pour over Doritos in casserole dish.
In saucepan, mix and heat soups, milk, taco sauce, chilies and 1 soup can of water.
Heat until warm and pour over meat.
Top with cheese and bake until cheese melts, about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Sift sugar, flour, nutmeg and cinnamon together.
Stir into beaten eggs.
Fold in rhubarb.
Pour into deep shell and dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Cut in slits near center for steam.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake 30 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in saucepan and bring to a boil. Cook 1 1/2 minutes, remove from heat. Add vanilla and oats. Beat mixture until it starts to get stiff. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper. Let cool.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Cook hen in salted water until tender.
Combine eggs, water and flour as for dumplings.
Roll thin; cut into small strips. Cut strips into squares.
Add pepper.
Bring broth mixture to a boil; drop in dumplings.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: mexican dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Serve with Doritos.

title: cheesy chicken fajitas
directions: Pour combined lime juice and jalapeno peppers over chicken; cover.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Drain.
Cook and stir onion and pepper in oil over medium-high heat until tender.
Add chicken; cook 5 to 7 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Add remaining ingredients except tortillas, stirring until Velveeta cheese is melted.
Serve with warm tortillas.

title: sour cream chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and egg.
Sift the dry ingredients, and add together along with the sour cream.
Fold in the nuts, chips and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: german style blueberry crumb cake
directions: Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, dash of salt and butter.
Mix with pastry blender or fork until crumbs are formed.
Measure 3/4 cup of this mixture and set aside.
Press remaining crumbs over bottom and about 3/4 inch up the side of a 9-inch spring-form pan. Combine blueberries, lemon juice, 1/2 cup sugar, tapioca, salt and the cinnamon.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Spoon blueberry mixture on to the crumb-lined pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Then sprinkle with 3/4 cup reserved crumbs.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes longer or until crumbs brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Drain kidney beans.
Mix beef, kidney beans, cheese, lettuce, onion and tomato together.
Add dressing and chips right before serving.

title: pressed chicken
directions: Cook hen and let cool.
Take chicken from bone, being careful to remove all bones.
(I don't grind all the skin, it makes the chicken too greasy.)
Grind chicken, celery and onion fine.
Add gelatin to cold water, then add hot chicken broth.
When gelatin is dissolved, add to the chicken.
Add salt, a dash of red pepper and a little black pepper.
Mix well.
Chop pimento and add to chicken mixture just to scatter through chicken.
Put into a pan that will make the chicken about 1 1/2-inches thick.
Pack down firm and smooth and cover with wax paper or foil.
Place in icebox.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook 20 minutes after it starts to boil.
Makes about 6 pints. Seal to keep.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Remove from heat, add sugar and cool.
Then add the egg, mixing well.
Add the dry ingredients and nuts.
Pour in greased pie pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Cool, then cut into small pieces.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Wash, peel, slice, and rinse potatoes. Melt crisco in large heavy skillet, place potatoes in skillet. Add salt, white sugar, cinnamon, and water. Cover and cook until tender. Add more water if needed. Add brown sugar and butter cover until sugar and butter melts. Take cover off and cook until water becomes a heavy syrup. Watch carefully, it will burn easily at this point.

title: butterscotch log
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over hot water (not boiling).
Stir in the condensed milk and vanilla.
Add chopped pecans; mix well. Chill until firm enough to handle.
Form into 12-inch roll on waxed paper.
Roll tightly in waxed paper; unroll and mark surface lengthwise with a fork.
Now brush with egg white.
Press pecans in the roll to completely cover surface.
Wrap again in waxed paper.
Chill completely.
Cut it in 1/2-inch slices with a sharp knife.
Makes about 2 dozen slices.

title: crab puffs
directions: Mix first five ingredients well and set aside.
Combine water and butter in a large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and immediately add flour, beating until mixture forms a ball.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each one. Stir in crab mixture.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoons onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes more.
Unbaked puffs can be frozen on baking sheet and transferred to plastic bags.
Heat without thawing at 375° until crisp.
Makes 60 puffs.

title: mom's old fashioned strawberry shortcake
directions: In medium bowl, slice fresh strawberries and sweeten with sugar; set aside.
In large bowl, cream sugar and shortening together.
Add milk and stir.
Mix in flour until it has a thin consistency like pancake mix.
Pour in large pan and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove cake from pan and let cool.
Use thread to split cake lengthwise to form 2 layers.
Use strawberry mixture between 2 layers and spread over the top.
Chill and serve.

title: cool lemon chicken salad
directions: Mix dressing, basil and juice and put in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce-lined platter.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mmmpossible taco pie(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.

title: fish sauce
directions: In pan, saute garlic and parsley in a little olive oil over medium heat.
Put in tomatoes and tomato paste and cook for about 1 hour.
Start to cook linguine about 15 minutes before the hour is up.
Do not put fish into sauce until linguine is nearly cooked.
Then put fish into sauce and cook about 10 -15 minutes. Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain pasta (do not rinse)
and put in serving bowl.
Pour fish sauce over it and serve.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Prepare on hot griddle or pan.

title: picante sauce
directions: Blend in blender; boil in saucepan approximately 15 minutes. Mix 1 teaspoon cornstarch in 1/8 cup water.
Add to boiling sauce after it has boiled 10 minutes.
Makes 1 quart.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chili
directions: In Dutch oven, gently cook onions in bacon grease and vegetable oil until softened but not brown.
Add garlic and hot peppers; continue cooking until soft but not brown.
Add beef, crumbling with fork.
Cook gently until beef loses its red color.

Over low heat, stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, chilies, Worcestershire sauce, Pickapeppa sauce, salt, black pepper, oregano, celery salt, celery seed, coriander seed, cumin, red pepper and chili powder. Cover; cook over low heat for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Stir in beans; stir often.
Cook 1 more hour.
Refrigerate 24 hours to allow flavors to blend.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: all-in-one chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients, all at one time.
Beat with mixer for 4 minutes.
Pour batter into greased and floured pans (1 oblong pan or 2 round pans).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Test for doneness with a toothpick. Makes a very moist, rich cake.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a mixing bowl; beat until creamy.
Stir in pineapple and coconut.
Pour mixture in a lightly greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with topping.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add to stuffing mix the melted butter.
Divide in half. Combine squash with next three ingredients and 1/2 of the stuffing mix.
Pour into casserole.
Place in a 350° oven until mixture is hot through.
Add remaining 1/2 crumbs to the top of casserole. Cook until crumbs are golden brown.

title: easy cabbage roll dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; stir in rice.
Layer cabbage and ground beef mixture in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart baking dish.

title: sausage and corn casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion and peppers.
Mix in a large bowl with eggs, crackers and corn.
Mix thoroughly.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: caramel brownies
directions: In double boiler, mix caramels with 1/3 c. evaporated milk. Combine cake mix, butter, nuts and remaining milk.
Press 1/2 of mixture into a 13 x 9 inch casserole dish.
Bake 6 minutes at 325°.
Layer chocolate chips and melted caramels over first layer, then press on remaining cake mix.
Bake 18 minutes at 325°.
Cool completely, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until firm. Brownies may be sliced into squares and removed from the pan for serving.

title: macaroni-cheese-ham salad
directions: Prepare macaroni.
Dice ham and cheese.
Cook peas and drain. Place all in large bowl and toss to mix well.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Spread onions in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pyrex dish.
Mix all other ingredients except butter and crumbs.
Spread on top of onions. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Toss crumbs in melted butter. Spread over top.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: skillet hominy
directions: About 5 minutes before serving, melt butter in skillet.
Add well drained hominy and heat.
Then toss with cheese, salt and pepper.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, then sprinkle cheese on top with little butter dropped in.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
A good supper casserole served with a tossed green salad and French bread.

title: vanilla custard ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in saucepan.
Add 2 cups cream. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Cook 2 additional minutes.
Add small amount of hot mixture to eggs, then return all to pan; cook, stirring, 1 minute more.
Remove from heat, add remaining 2 cups cream and vanilla.
Chill thoroughly.
You can add chopped fresh fruit when it goes into the freezer.

title: fix-ahead breakfast casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in 9 x 13-inch glass oven pan.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cream chicken
directions: Mix soups and water together.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle both sides of chicken with garlic salt.
Place chicken in bottom of baking pan.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon, onion and hamburger.
Mix everything and pour into a large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no-cholesterol orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except egg whites.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into flour mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan. Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove and cool.

title: famous squash souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender. Grease an 8 x 11-inch casserole dish (can use Pam cooking spray). Pour the mixture into the dish and sprinkle with cinnamon. Pass a knife through to make a design on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into a ball and refrigerate for about 10 minutes or until firm.
Roll in chopped parsley or chopped nuts.

title: tortilla chicken soup
directions: Mix cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soup.
Add 3/4 of chicken broth.
Add rotel (amount) depending on how spicy you like it.
Usually a full can is just right.
Shred chicken into soup. Add salt and pepper.
Top off with a sprinkle of parsley and basil. Serve with tortilla chips or bread.

title: kathy's christmas candy
directions: Combine butter, sugar, almonds and Karo syrup.
Boil over medium heat until candy thermometer reaches 325° to 335°.
Have 2 cookie sheets greased and ready!
Spread quickly, as thin as possible.
You must work fast.
(It might be a good idea to have someone work with you, at least, the first time.)
Set aside.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in boiling water. Melt cheese and margarine together add to hot grits. Beat eggs and put in measuring cup and fill cup to full, one cup, with milk. Add to grits and cheese and put into buttered casserole. top with cracker crumbs and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until firm.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs well. Sift dry ingredients and add to fruit mixture. Fold apples, nuts and flour into eggs. Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 375°. Leave in pan. Combine 1 stick butter, 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup milk. Cook in microwave 2 1/2 minutes. Pour over cake while still warm. Cool completely and remove from pan.

title: lemon icing
directions: Cook syrup until it spins thread.
Add lemon; cook 10 more minutes.
Let cool before spreading.
Yields enough for 5 to 6 layers.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel avocados.
Remove seeds and mash the fruit.
Add remaining ingredients.
Garnish with ripe olive rings and two tomato wedges.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown meat in fat, then add onion and brown.
Add all other ingredients; stir well.
Then simmer until tender, about 2 hours. Thicken, if desired, and serve on fine noodles.

title: country cheese snacks
directions: In a small bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Spread on bread.
Place on baking sheet.
Broil for 1 to 2 minutes about 4 inches under broiler.
Garnish with a slice of olive on top.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Mix well and place in baking dish.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Add all other ingredients.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Place buttermilk and soda in a kettle.
Let set for 3 minutes. Add sugar and butter.
Cook to soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Cool and beat until creamy.
Stir in vanilla and nuts. Turn out into buttered pan.

title: cherry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Drain cherries and save juice. Heat 3/4 cup cherry juice in a saucepan. Then blend together flour and cold cherry juice. Slowly add flour mixture to the heated cherry juice and cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly. Slowly add sugar and cook another 3 to 4 minutes; then remove from heat. Stir in lemon juice, butter, salt and red food coloring. Pour mixture over cherries and blend carefully but thoroughly. Allow to cool while making pastry. Line a 9-inch pie plate with the rolled pastry. Build up the edge as this makes a deep pie. Roll out pastry for top crust. Cut into strips for lattice top. Add cherry filling to the pastry lined pie plate. Arrange pastry strips on top, lattice fashion. Moisten and seal at edge and where strips cross. Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350° and continue to bake another 25 to 30 minutes.

title: linguine with crabmeat
directions: In a saute pan, heat oil; add garlic and saute until golden. Add parsley, red pepper, crabmeat and wine.
Saute until wine is reduced.
Add clam juice, salt and pepper.
Cook linguine in salted water.
When al dente, strain pasta and toss with clam mixture and butter over high heat for 2 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken honolulu(contains approximately 250 calories per serving)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Dissolve bouillon cube in water.
Add lemon juice, soy sauce, onion powder, garlic powder, ginger and pepper; mix well.
Pour over chicken, turning to coat all sides. Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours, turning once.
Arrange chicken on a rack in a broiler pan.
Broil until chicken is tender, about 45 minutes, turning and brushing frequently with marinade.
Makes 4 servings.

title: girdle buster pie
directions: Mix cookie crumbs and oleo.
Place in pie pan and freeze. Place ice cream on frozen crust, return to freezer. Put milk, butter, sugar, chocolate and vanilla in saucepan.
Cook until smooth.
Let cool.
Pour over ice cream, return to freezer.
Thaw slightly before serving.
Can be topped with whipped topping and slivered almonds.

title: crock-pot ranch beans
directions: Cook beans, water, monosodium glutamate (food enhancer), pepper, salt and garlic powder in crock-pot for about 2 hours on high; reduce to low and cook about 8 more hours, then add remaining ingredients and cook for about 10 more hours on low.

title: easy chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients well until mixture has no lumps.
Pour into freezer can and follow freezer directions.

title: yankee salad
directions: Blend together the orange jello and cottage cheese.
Add the oranges and fruit cocktail.
Blend in the Cool Whip and chill.

title: top of the range baked beans
directions: Melt Crisco in a large pot.
Add green peppers and onions; saute for 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in pork and beans, pineapples, catsup, molasses, brown sugar and mustard.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until mixture comes just to a boil, stirring frequently.

title: cheese puff squares
directions: Remove crusts from bread, cut into cubes approximately 1 1/4 to 1 1/2-inch square.
Mix egg whites, cheese and butter together. Beat very well (about 5 to 6 minutes) until very fluffy.
Spread 5 sides of cubes with mix (not too thick).
Put on cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: pickled beets
directions: Select small young beets or cut larger beets; cook until tender.
Dip in cold water and peel off skins.
Make the syrup; pour over beets and boil 10 minutes.
Pack into sterilized jars and seal with hot sterilized lids.

title: old-fashion egg pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and milk.
Mix flour, nutmeg and salt together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until pie is set firm and light brown.

title: pineapple coconut pie(by gracie plunkett)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, then other ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup
chopped
pecans,
if
desired.
Pour into two pastry shells and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: beef and bean homemade burritos(quick and easy)
directions: In skillet brown ground beef. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add can of refried beans.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Simmer.
Heat tortillas individually.
Add meat mixture and toppings.

title: tallarina
directions: Brown meat and drain off excess fat.
Chop onions and bell pepper; saute until tender.
Cut up tomatoes and chilies; add to meat.
Add onion, pepper and creamed corn.
Simmer on low heat. Boil and drain noodles; add to meat mixture.
In a casserole dish, layer meat mixture, cheese slices, etc., ending with cheese on top.
Put in oven at 350° until cheese melts.
Serves 6 to 8.
Can freeze leftovers.

title: breast of chicken cherokee
directions: Marinate chicken in cream for 24 hours in refrigerator. Drain, reserving cream. Roll chicken in flour mixed with salt and pepper. Pan fry in oil and butter combination until golden brown. Remove. Mix flour into chicken drippings. Stir in cream left from marinating chicken. Cook until mixture is thickened. Mix in chopped almonds. Serve on rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually while creaming.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla extract.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill overnight.
Roll a small amount of dough at a time to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut out and decorate with colored sugar.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sherried fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in a separate bowl, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Pour over fruit mixture, tossing lightly.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate dump cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed, then fold cherry pie filling in.

title: lo-cal dream salad
directions: Drain fruit well; mix with cottage cheese. Sprinkle dry Jell-O over this and mix well. Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: chicken pizzacante
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and the bouillon concentrate.
Saute in heavy skillet until slightly browned.
Add minced garlic, parsley and bay leaf; stir well.
Add lemon juice, water and mushrooms.
Simmer 45 minutes.
I add 1/2 pound sliced mushrooms.

title: artichoke and cheese squares
directions: Saute onion in small amount of cooking oil such as Wesson, Crisco, etc.
Mix all ingredients. Pour into 8 x 10-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° until brown. Cut into one-inch squares.
Keep hot for serving.
Can be frozen.
Reheat for 20 minutes at 300°.

title: sour cream squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and spoon into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: louise's quiche
directions: Beat eggs lightly and add biscuit mix, melted butter, milk and salt.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle grated cheese and any of the optional ingredients on top.
Bake at 350°
for approximately 45 minutes.
Let set for 10 minutes before serving.

title: carolyn's chocolate-coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add eggs, beaten, then milk and flavoring.
Add melted margarine.
Add coconut last.
Bake in a 350° oven about 40 minutes or until filling is firm.
(Can make 3 frozen pie crusts.)
Makes enough filling for 2 homemade pie crusts or frozen deep dish pie crusts.

title: orange pineapple ice cream
directions: Drained pineapple may be pureed slightly in blender with part of milk if desired, to eliminate prominent pieces of pineapple in ice cream.

title: meadow mist mellows
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Blend in shortening with dry ingredients.
Combine milk with yeast and add flour to make stiff dough.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Make biscuits as needed. Put in cold oven; turn oven to 450°.
Mix will keep in refrigerator up to two weeks.

title: broiled on cake frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients and sprinkle over white or spiced cake.
Broil in hot oven.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Slit each frank and insert a piece of cheese.
Divide each biscuit into 3 pieces.
Wrap one piece around each frank.
Lightly butter tops and sprinkle with seed.
Butter cookie sheets lightly. Bake in 375° to 400° oven for about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Can be frozen, thawed and cooked 5 or 10 minutes.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients
except 1/2 c. corned beef. Form into ball and roll in remaining corned beef. Serve with your choice of crackers.

title: candied pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until stiff. Mix with nuts. Combine remaining ingredients. Mix with coated nuts. Bake on buttered cookie sheet for 1 hour at 250°.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Peel tomatoes, remove seeds from onions and chop fine.
Stir tomatoes, onions and peppers together and add salt, sugar, cinnamon, cloves and vinegar.
Cook slowly for 45-60 minutes or until thick.
Stirring occasionally.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 4 pints.
Also good with vegetables.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Cut in oleo until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add buttermilk all at once. Stir just until blended. Knead 1/2 minute on floured surface. Roll out to 1/2 inch thickness. Cut with 2 inch cutter. Place on cookie sheet, prick with a fork. brush with buttermilk. Bake at 450 degrees for 12-15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: sweet-n-sour meatballs
directions: Mix hamburg, bread crumbs, milk, chopped onion, salt, Worcestershire sauce and egg.
Shape into 20 (1 1/2-inch) balls. Cook meatballs in skillet; remove and drain fat.
Mix brown sugar and cornstarch in skillet.
Stir in pineapple (with syrup), vinegar and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling, stirring.
Reduce heat; add meatballs.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes.
Stir in green pepper and cherries (without syrup). Cover and simmer until crisp-tender, 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate waffle drops
directions: Cream butter and
sugar.
Add
eggs
and
vanilla. Beat well. Mix dry ingredients
and stir into butter mixture.	Drop by teaspoonfuls 2-inches
apart
onto	preheated
waffle iron. Bake (as you would a waffle) until done (about 1 1/2 minutes). Remove to rack to cool.
Sift powdered sugar over cookies.

title: scrambled eggs
directions: Break eggs into bowl.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Beat with a fork.
Put butter or margarine into a 6-inch skillet.
Put skillet on burner.
Turn burner to medium-low heat.
Cook about 1 minute without stirring.
Stir eggs with spoon.
Cook just until eggs are dry, stirring a few times.
Do not stir too much or eggs will be mushy.
Spoon eggs onto plates.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut squash into 1/4-inch slices.
Alternate layers of squash and onion rings in casserole dish, sprinkling each layer with pimentos.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan and bake 35 minutes in a 350° preheated oven.

title: golden california chicken
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Add soup, onion, concentrated orange juice and ginger.
Cover and cook over low heat 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir occasionally. Uncover and cook to desired consistency. Garnish with avocado and orange slices.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rice-veggie-shrimp dish
directions: While yellow rice is cooking: saute all other ingredients in olive oil.
Sprinkle lemon juice over them.
Combine all ingredients for a healthy, hardy meal.

title: fudge cake
directions: Mix oleo, cocoa, shortening and water and bring mixture to boil.
Pour boiling mixture over combination of flour and sugar. Mix.
Beat buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla into a mixture.
Pour this into previous "chocolate" mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: corn flake snack
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and peanut butter in 2-quart pan.
Bring to a boil until peanut butter and sugar are melted.
Pour over corn flakes and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper to cool. Store in an airtight container.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add alternately the flour and eggs, beating well after each addition.
Add nutmeg and eggs.
Pour in 3 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 320°.
Enjoy!

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla.
Beat over boiling water until mixture stands in soft peaks, 7 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla; beat until thick enough for 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix as you do a meat loaf.
Put in loaf pan, 9 x 11-inch or 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix water, vinegar, brown sugar and mustard; mix well.
Pour over loaf.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and flavoring.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Bake cookies for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cake with coffee
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and oil.
Mix in eggs well.
Add coffee and mix well.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 (8-inch or 9-inch) round pans or 1 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pan.

title: egg roll filling
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Add the mixture of the Accent, sugar, soy sauce and salt; blend thoroughly.
Refrigerate a couple of hours until cold.
Makes around 20 egg rolls.
I use skins from the store.

title: chili beans
directions: Fry bacon; remove from pan.
Add chopped onion.
When onion is cooked, add ground beef and brown.
Add tomatoes, soup, chili powder, paprika and bay leaf.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add beans, salt and bacon crumbs.
Heat and serve.
Makes enough for a crowd.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean and stem mushrooms.
Reserve stems.
Saute sausage, onion and garlic.
Add chopped mushroom stems.
Let cool a little before adding cream cheese.
Let cool completely.
Spoon sausage mixture into the mushroom caps.
Place on microwave-safe plate and place in microwave oven.
Heat until thoroughly heated.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix and bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Punch holes in cake to allow the sauce to soak in cake better.
Pour over hot cake.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: In large bowl blend together flour and baking powder.
Add shortening; cut in with pastry blender or 2 knives.
Add milk and sugar, mix well.
Generously grease square baking pan.
Pat mixture flat on bottom.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar and salt in pan and heat over medium heat to boiling.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until marshmallows melt.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square pan.

title: dirt cake
directions: Finely crush the entire package of cookies.
Crush until the creamy middle disappears.
Cream the margarine and cream cheese together.
Add the sugar and Cool Whip, mixing well.
Combine the milk, vanilla pudding and vanilla; mix well.
When set, add this to the margarine and cream cheese.
Put 1/2 cookie crumbs on bottom of oblong cake pan.
Pour filling on top.
Top with remaining cookie crumbs.
Chill 10 to 12 hours before serving.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix all liquid ingredients together.
Drop fish into liquid ingredients, then roll in dry ingredients.
Deep fry in hot peanut oil.
Fish will float when fully cooked.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion, garlic and green pepper in oil.
Add meat and salt.
Brown the meat until cooked thoroughly.
Add tomato paste and tomatoes.
If needed, add water if sauce is too thick.
Add oregano.
Simmer on low heat for several hours.
Serve with spaghetti or other types of pasta.

title: florida orange fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add soda and buttermilk.
Sift flour 3 times.
Add alternately flour and milk, beating after each addition.
Add 1 teaspoon orange rind.
Dust nuts and dates with flour.
Stir in cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan. When cool mix 1 cup sugar and 1 1/2 cups orange juice.
Pour over cake a little at a time.

title: pork adobo
directions: Clean the pork and cut into serving pieces.
In a skillet, place the water, soy sauce, vinegar, pork, crushed garlic and peppercorns.
Simmer the mixture until the pork is done.

title: quick rolls
directions: Put eggs in ice cream bucket and beat with a fork.
Mix the other ingredients with eggs.
Mix well with fork/spoon.
Drop in muffin tins/loaf pan.
Bake at 400° until done.
Put margarine on top after bread starts to brown.
Do this about twice.
May be kept in refrigerator for 1 week covered tightly.

title: german potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into 1/8-inch slices.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, horseradish, celery seed and salt; set aside.
In another bowl, arrange layer of potatoes, salt lightly and cover with mayonnaise-sour cream mixture.
Then layer of onion mixture. Continue layering, ending with parsley and onion.
Do not stir. Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours before using.

title: warm cider
directions: Boil cider and cinnamon sticks together for 5 minutes; add remaining ingredients and bring back to a boil.
Serve warm.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Mix in a saucepan syrup, eggs, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Cook over low heat stirring constantly until thickened (about 20 minutes).
Cool, then fold in mayonnaise.
Combine pineapple, diced apples, celery, nuts and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Beat whipped cream until it peaks.
Fold whipped cream into cooled egg mixture.
Combine fruit and egg mixture.
Turn into mold.
Garnish with apple wedges.
Freeze until serving time.

title: anyone "can" soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain thoroughly.
Open and drain sliced potatoes and mix with contents of all remaining cans.
Add the drained ground beef and simmer for two hours or more.
You'll think it's "homemade!"

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onions.
Add spices and stir until well blended.
Add beans and chopped tomatoes and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer at least 1 1/2 hours, stirring frequently.
Leftover chili freezes well.
Makes about 2 gallons.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken; tear off bone.
Combine soups, Ro-Tel and 1/2 cup chicken broth in saucepan.
In a baking pan layer 1/2 package chips, 1/2 of chicken, 1/2 of soup mixture and onion, then add 2nd layer.
Top with chips and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; let partly set.
Whip cream cheese and Dream Whip.
Fold in Jell-O with apricots and nuts. Spoon in mold and chill.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook real slow 45 minutes.

title: corn pone
directions: Sift cornmeal with soda and salt.
Work the lard into the dry ingredients and blend well.
Add the boiling water and continue blending.
Slowly add the buttermilk until a soft dough is formed. The buttermilk should be added very slowly to ensure the dough contains enough consistency to be molded into small cakes.
Grease a skillet, heat it and place the cake in the skillet.
Flatten and bake them in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until lightly brown and done.

title: baked ziti
directions: *Optional:
Cook 1 package ground meat in pan and add to plain spaghetti sauce.

title: fall apart meat
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line a baking dish with enough aluminum foil to completely cover dish and roast.
Place roast in center; shake Lipton onion soup mix over roast.
Spread the cream of mushroom soup over roast, also.
Depending on what size roast you get will tell you how long to cook it.
For a 3 1/2 to 4-pound roast, cook for approximately 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
The meat will fall apart.
Makes gravy.

title: moussaka
directions: Cube and saute eggplant and onion, add browned meat.
Add seasoning, tomatoes and wine; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Cool Spread 4 tablespoons crumbs on bottom of baking dish and add mixture.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar and beat well.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt two or three times.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add carrots, a small amount at a time.
Bake in three 8 or 9 inch floured and greased pans at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, soda, cinnamon, salt, sugar and nuts in large bowl.
Add oil, pineapple, vanilla, eggs and bananas.
Do not beat.
Just stir together.
Pour into greased tube pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour plus or until tests done with toothpick.
(Cake will crack slightly on top.)
Cool in pan on rack.
Cake is moist.
Keeps well.
Turn out tube pan cake and frost.
Can frost in 9 x 13-inch pan without taking out of pan.

title: beef barley soup(dutch oven)
directions: Put all ingredients together and slow cook until done.
Can substitute 3/4 cup beef broth instead of wine.
One cup equals 156 calories.

title: hidden cupcakes
directions: Mix cream cheese, egg, sugar and salt until creamy.
Stir in chocolate chips; set aside.
Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Mix dry ingredients with water, vinegar, oil and vanilla.
Divide cocoa mixture evenly into cupcake tins with liners.
Put a spoonful of cream cheese mixture in the center of cocoa mixture.
Garnish with 1/2 cherry.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Pour creams directly into ice cream freezer can.
Add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Stir with a plastic or wooden spoon until the sugar dissolves.
Freeze in
homemade ice cream freezer.

title: chocolate-covered strawberry pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Add 1/2 cup chocolate pieces (melted) and 1 egg. Pour mixture into pie crust. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Chill.
Combine remaining chocolate pieces and butter; melt over low heat until smooth. Cool. Cut washed strawberries in half and arrange on pie. Drizzle chocolate mixture over berries. Chill. Serves 8.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and put into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Mix in the order given and bake in muffin tins or in a shallow pan in a moderate to hot oven (400° to 425°) for 20 minutes.
To be a real Southern bread, this should be made of white cornmeal made from the whole grain.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 1/4-inch pieces and place in large bowl. Roll in 1 cup sugar mixed with 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Put in large Bundt pan.
Melt oleo, brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon together.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Invert onto plate.
Serve while warm.

title: meat loaf casserole
directions: Mix together and place into greased pan.
Cover and bake in low oven at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes or until baked through, but not dried out.
Drain off excess grease.

title: spiced pecans
directions: In a saucepan, heat all ingredients except pecans.
Let it boil 5 minutes.
Add pecans.
Pour on cookie sheet. Cool and separate.

title: cranberry glazed pork roast
directions: In a small saucepan, mix together all ingredients, except pork, stirring over medium heat until thickened.
Set aside. Place roast in shallow baking dish.
Roast at 325° for 45 minutes. Spoon on 1/2 cup of glaze.
Roast 45 minutes more, or until meat thermometer reaches 160°.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Slice and serve with remaining sauce.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Add milk, cookies, coconut and pecans.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop chicken into bite size pieces. Mix the mayonnaise and the chicken soup.
Mix all ingredients. Transfer to 9 x 13-inch casserole (3 quart).
Sprinkle crushed potato chips.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake 45 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Serves 10 to 12.
Top with crushed potato chips.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Blend at medium speed with electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Top with Fluffy Pistachio Frosting.

title: aunt fanny's summer squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding only about 1/4 of the melted butter.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle with additional herb dressing crumbs.
Pour remaining butter over all.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet; drain grease.
Open can of crescent rolls; unroll and put in bottom of greased pizza pan to form crust.
Sprinkle sausage over crescent roll crust.
Crack eggs in a small bowl and add water; scramble.
Pour over sausage, tilting pan so that egg mixture covers entire crust. Top with cheese.

title: zucchini oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, mix first 7 ingredients. In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly; stir in zucchini and salad oil.
Stir egg mixture into flour mixture just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Spoon batter into muffin pan. Bake 25 minutes or until golden and toothpick inserted in center of muffin comes out clean.
Immediately remove muffins from pan; serve warm or cool on wire rack to serve later; reheat if desired.

title: fancy hamburger hot dish
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, egg and oatmeal.
Pat down in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the two soups.
Pour 1/4 over the hamburger mixture.
Mix stuffing according to directions on package.
Put on top of hamburger and soup mixture.
Pour rest of soup on top of dressing.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Wipe meat dry and brown in oil on all sides in a heavy pot. Push meat aside; add onions and more oil if needed.
Saute until tender.
Stir in paprika and cook 1 minute.
Add enough water to cover; cook very slowly, tightly covered, for 1 hour.
Add tomatoes and potatoes.
Continue to cook another 30 minutes or until beef and potatoes are tender.
It may be necessary to add a little more water during cooking, but final gravy should be thick.

title: caramelettos
directions: Press cookie dough mix in 9x9 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels and milk in pan.
Set aside. Remove cookie dough from oven.
Sprinkle immediately with chocolate chips. Spread caramel mixture over chocolate chips. Cool. Cut into 1 inch squares. Top each square with a pecan half.

title: cheese soup
directions: Make a white sauce by melting 8 Tbsp. oleo, adding flour and slowly adding milk.
Stir until thickened.
Add
cheese.
Saute vegetables in 2 Tbsp. butter.
Stir often and combine with chicken stock.
Mix with white sauce and cheese mixture.
Serve hot with bread sticks.
Serves 8.

title: turtle bars
directions: Place cake mix, melted butter, and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in large mixing bowl.
Beat at high speed until well mixed.
Place 1/2 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan and press well into bottom.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool to room temperature.
Place caramels and remaining 1/3 cup evaporated milk in heavy saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until smooth.
Pour evenly over baked and cooled chocolate mixture.
Spread with spatula to cover all of chocolate mixture. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.

title: banana cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixing bowl, combine flour, 1/2 teaspoon baking soda, cream of tartar, cinnamon and nutmeg. Set aside.
In medium bowl, mix honey, maple syrup, vanilla, egg whites, pureed banana and sliced banana.
Stir into flour mixture and mix until just blended.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet, drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, catsup and pepper, heat through.
Alternate meat mixture and cheese slices in a 1 1/2-quart ungreased casserole and arrange biscuits around the edge of dish.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until the biscuits are golden brown.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck and sausage and drain well.
In a separate pan, saute onion; add green pepper, followed by sliced mushrooms.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first six ingredients together.
Put into a baking dish; mix brown sugar, flour, pecans and butter together and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix vegetables in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables; cover. Refrigerate.

title: zucchini and squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place zucchini in a 9 x 13-inch dish, top with onion.
Sprinkle uncooked rice over the onion.
Cut 1 tablespoon margarine into pieces and dot over casserole; top with yellow squash.
Add tomatoes, spices and juice.
Dot with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 50 minutes.
Remove from oven, remove foil, top with cheeses and bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Enjoy!!

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar in bowl until light and fluffy. Add peanut butter and milk and beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping; pour into crust and chill for 5 to 6 hours.

title: shredded pork with golden cap
directions: Mix pork with 1/2 teaspoon of salt and cornstarch.
Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in wok.
Stir-fry pork until color changes, about 1 minute.
Add sherry and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce. Stir-fry 1 minute more.
Remove to plate.

title: nene's crunchy cucumber sticks
directions: Day #1 A.M.:
Peel and halve the cukes.
Remove seeds.
Cut into lengthwise strips.
Soak in 2 gallons of water with lime stirred in.
Soak for 24 hours.

title: steve's five spice beef
directions: Slice mushrooms and onion thinly.
Set aside.
Slice steak thinly across the grain.
Set aside.
Heat wok or heavy frypan without oil until quite hot.
Add 2 tablespoons of peanut oil. When it smokes, add veggie.
Stir until half done, 2 to 3 minutes. Remove with slotted spoon.
Add 1 tablespoon oil; heat.
Add meat until brown.
Add veggie and 5 spice sauce.
Mix.
Stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove.
Add sesame oil, if desired.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix everything together until it holds together.
Shape into small balls, about 1-inch.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes.

title: almond butter crunch
directions: *Toasted Almonds:
Sprinkle chopped nuts on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 6 to 8 minutes, turning almonds about every minute.

title: kesari
directions: Heat the butter in the dish and fry cashews and raisins until the nuts are golden brown.
Add the milk, water and salt.
Bring it to a boil.
(Optional:
You might add food coloring.)
Stir in Cream of Wheat little by little to avoid lumps.
Add sugar and keep stirring for 2 minutes.

title: baked stuffed lobster green lake
directions: Split live lobsters from the chest to the tail, carefully avoiding the stomach.
Remove innards, setting aside the green tamale.
Rinse and place on a cookie sheet.
Combine crushed crackers with melted butter, tamale and Worcestershire sauce to taste until stuffing is easily workable.
Stuff lobsters from chest through tail and bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes, depending upon size.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serves 50.

title: mushroom salad italiano
directions: To make dressing, combine lemon juice and next 3 ingredients. Beat in oil.
Reserve.
Up to 2 hours before serving, toss mushrooms, celery, parsley and cheese with reserved dressing. Serves 6.

title: door prize punch
directions: Mix and serve.
Some of the Kool-Aid may be put in ice trays and frozen.
This keeps the punch from being watered down from using so many regular ice cubes.

title: our favorite guatemala (kekchi) meal
directions: Soak the beans overnight and cook the next day until soft or soak 1 hour and cook in pressure cooker.
While in the cooking process, add remaining ingredients.
Cook until real soft. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: banana bread
directions: In a small bowl, sift dry ingredients.
In a separate bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Blend in eggs and mix well.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients, then fold in bananas and nuts.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Push batter up in corners, leaving center slightly hollow for a well rounded loaf.
Allow to stand for 20 minutes before baking.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 60 to 70 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool.

title: low calorie lemon chicken
directions: Lay cut up chicken in broiling pan, skin side down.
Pour lemon juice over chicken.
Add salad oil, making sure all pieces are moistened.
Lightly sprinkle oregano, garlic powder and salt on chicken.
(May vary according to taste.)
Broil over lowest rack in oven.
(May not be suitable for gas oven.)
Check after 25 minutes.
Turn chicken over, skin side up.
Spoon juices over all pieces.
Return to broiler and continue cooking another 30 minutes.
Make sure chicken doesn't burn.
Serve with white or fried rice; spoon juice from chicken over rice.
Cooking time 1 hour. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage and set aside. Take at least 12 slices of bread cut into half and trim the outsides off.

Lay bread in bottom of 9 x 12 x 2 baking pan with high sides on it. Sprinkle cooked sausage on top of bread, sprinkle grated cheese over top of sausage, do not use all of the cheese save some for topping. Beat eggs, milk, half and half, salt, and pepper together and pour over sausage, bread, and cheese layers.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake for 25-30 minutes in oven at 350 degree.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Combine butter, shortening and sugar.
Cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and food coloring.
Combine flour and salt; add to cream mixture alternately with milk, beating well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° about one hour and 20 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: buster bars
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and mix
with
oil.
Press
in
x 13-inch pan. Freeze until set.
Soften ice cream and spread on top.
Crush peanuts and spread 1/3
cup
on
top of ice cream. Freeze
until set.
Boil
chocolate
chips,
evaporated
milk, powdered sugar and margarine for 8 minutes, stirring constantly. Cool 1 hour.
Spread on top with 1/2 cup peanuts.
Freeze until set.

title: mincemeat salad
directions: Break the mincemeat into small pieces and put in small pot. Cover with 1 cup water.
Place over medium heat and boil 1 minute. Cool.
Prepare gelatin using 3 cups hot water.
When gelatin is slightly thickened, add mincemeat mixture and nuts.
Put in refrigerator until set.

title: butterscotch chee-chees
directions: In double boiler, melt morsels.
Add nuts and noodles.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool.
Serve.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Saute garlic in butter, add other ingredients, except shrimp, and simmer until blended.
Add shrimp and toss gently until pink. Serve over rice.
May sprinkle with chopped parsley and/or Parmesan cheese.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Blend all other ingredients and pour over carrots in a glass bowl.
Cover and marinate overnight.

title: peach schnapps cake
directions: Add all ingredients to cake mix and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush cookies.
Mix into Cool Whip and chill.
Serve as is or a topping.

title: beef and pecan spread
directions: Saute the pecans in butter 3 to 5 minutes; set aside.

Using scissors, cut the dried beef into small pieces. Blend with the rest of the ingredients. Pour into a glass baking dish and top with sauteed pecans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve hot with crackers. Serves 10 to 12.

title: hershey's disappearing cake
directions: Generously grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans. Cream butter,
shortening,
sugar
and
vanilla until fluffy; blend
in eggs.
Combine
cocoa, flour, baking powder, baking soda and
salt in
bowl; add alternately with milk to batter. Blend well.
Pour into pans; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan and use cocoa in your favorite frosting recipe.

title: turtle cake bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Pour half the mix in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 16 minutes at 350°.

title: crazy corn bread
directions: Mix all together. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rosemary's feather rolls
directions: Put the warm milk and package of yeast in a mixing bowl and let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir well.
Add butter or oleo, sugar and salt.
Beat with beater until thoroughly blended.
Add flour and continue to beat as long as possible, then mix with spoon. Cover bowl; set in warm place.
Let rise about 45 minutes.
Stir down batter and fill greased muffin tins a little more than half full.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle nuts in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Divide dough into 24 pieces.
Shape into balls. Place in baking pan; sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into four pieces (kitchen shears work well). Roll each piece in the mixture of sugar, cinnamon and ground pecans.
Place in a large buttered tube pan.

title: caesar salad lite
directions: Coat bread with Pam and sprinkle with garlic powder.
Bake in 300° oven until bread is golden brown.
Coddle the 2 eggs.
Rub large bowl with garlic.
Place lettuce in bowl.
Combine eggs, mustard, lemon juice, water, oil and Worcestershire, stirring well.
Add to lettuce and drizzle eggs over it.
Add cheese and croutons.
Contains 62 calories per 1/2 cup, 70 chol, 87 sod., 3.3 fat.

title: simple sauerkraut soup
directions: Empty sauerkraut (including juice) into 6 quart pot.
Add tomatoes and onions.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and cook slowly about 2 hours.
Stir occasionally and sweeten to taste as it cooks.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Stir all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Try, they are great!

title: noodle pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Butter large Pyrex dish.
Pour in mixture.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Bake in oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Sprinkle with sliced green onions and chopped tomato, if desired. Serve with tortilla chips or crackers (better).

title: chicken with lemon sauce
directions: Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken.

title: yule log cake
directions: Grease bottom and sides of loaf pan (16 x 5 x 5).
Line bottom of pan with waxed paper.
Grease paper.

title: apple strudel
directions: Filling:
Wash, quarter, core and pare apples; slice approximately 1/8-inch thick.
Put into bowl containing vanilla and brown sugar.
Toss so apples are coated.
Let stand 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in 4 cups unsalted water.	Melt
butter in 9-inch square ovenware.
Discard
bone
and
skin	from cooked chicken. Cut chicken
into bite size pieces.
Layer stuffing, chicken, mushroom
soup,
stuffing,	chicken and chicken soup. Top with stuffing.
Pour 2 cans of broth over and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: party mints
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a large bowl.
Beat at high speed of mixer until well blended.
Knead until smooth. Separate and add food coloring to make assorted colors.
Shape mints into candy molds and place on cookie sheets.
Cover with paper towels and let set overnight.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage until done, breaking into bits as it cooks. Drain and set aside.
Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and mustard. Layer bread in a greased 2-quart baking dish and layer sausage and cheese over bread.
Pour egg mixture over this.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.
Nice to have for breakfast when you have a guest.

title: deviled ham puff
directions: Grease shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Blend Tabasco and Worcestershire with ham.
Spread evenly on each slice of bread. Cut into 1-inch squares.
Place one layer (close together) on bottom of dish and sprinkle with half of the cheese.
Place remaining squares on top and sprinkle with remainder of cheese. Blend eggs, milk and pimento (season with salt and pepper) and pour over bread.

title: hot diggety dog
directions: Layer in a casserole dish the pork and beans, sauteed onions and peppers, 1/2 of the ketchup, honey and Worcestershire sauce mixture, wieners, sauerkraut and the other half of the sauce mixture. Top with cheese. Bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: easy low-fat chili
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in half cup water until tender.
Add beans, tomato paste and tomatoes. Stir in chili powder, salt (if desired), pepper and remaining water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Yields 7 servings.
Diabetic exchanges:
One 1 cup serving prepared without added salt equals 2 starch and 1 1/2 vegetables.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients.
Make into ball or balls.
Roll in chopped nuts and parsley flakes if desired.

title: american chop suey
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
In a large skillet, brown the meat and onion in butter.
Add cooked macaroni to browned meat and onion along with tomato soup and sauce.
Allow this mixture to simmer a while to improve flavor.

title: browned rice
directions: Mix together and bake in a 1-quart casserole at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4.
(Double recipe to serve more.)

title: sesame chicken wings
directions: Remove tips of chicken wings; save for making soup.
Cut each wing into two sections.
Combine sesame seed, bread crumbs, paprika and salt in shallow dish.
Dip chicken pieces in cream, using brush to coat completely; roll in crumb mixture.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Place butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Melt in oven while oven preheats to 375°.
Remove from oven; turn chicken pieces in butter to coat completely.
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 40 minutes.
Serve with Polynesian Glaze or bottled duck sauce.
Makes about 36 appetizers.

title: 3-cities of spain cheesecake
directions: Mix graham crackers, sugar and butter together until well blended. Press into pie pan.

title: scallop pie
directions: Quarter clove of garlic and saute in butter until soft. Remove from butter and discard.
Add chopped onion to garlic butter and saute lightly. Add scallops and cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add milk, thickened with flour.
Add Chablis.
Take entire mixture and pour into casserole.
Cover with crumbs and sprinkle melted butter on top lightly. Bake at 400° until bubbly.

title: barbecue
directions: Put the meat in a large pan.
Combine remaining ingredients to make the sauce.
Pour the sauce over the meat.
Simmer for 3 hours.

title: easy whole wheat bread
directions: Combine flour (whole wheat), sugar, salt and yeast in a large mixer bowl.
Heat milk and oil in saucepan over low heat until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add egg and warm liquid to flour mixture.
Beat 1/2 minute at low speed, then 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, gradually add 1 cup whole wheat flour and 3 to 4 cups of all-purpose flour to form soft dough.
Grease on all sides.
Cover dough and let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size, 45 to 60 minutes.
Punch down dough. Shape into loaves.
Place in greased pans, cover and let rise in warm place until light, 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake loaves at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until loaves sound hollow when lightly tapped.
Remove from pans immediately.
Cool on rack.
Brush top with butter.

title: half-hour spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef with first 3 ingredients.
Add next 4 ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple and sugar to boiling, then add jello.
Remove from heat and stir well.
Add cold water and lemon juice. Chill until partially set.
Add cheese, nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix well and refrigerate until set.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat water and margarine or butter to a rolling boil in a 2 1/2 quart saucepan.
Stir in flour until mixture forms a ball.
Beat eggs in one at a time until smooth. Drop dough by 1/4 cup full about 3 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until puffed and brown.
Cool away from drafts for about 25 to 40 minutes.
Cut off tops and fill puffs with vanilla pudding and cool whip.
Replace top and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: stuffed squash
directions: With an apple corer or small spoon, scoop out inside of squash, reserving neck to slice into bottom of pot.
Mix raw beef, tomatoes, salt, pepper, rice and onion together.
Stuff this mixture into the squash cavity.
Stand squash upright in pot with slices of squash in bottom.
(If you have meat mixture leftover, form into balls and place between the squash.)
Add tomato sauce and water to the top of squash.
Slice oleo over the top and cook on top of stove 1 hour or longer, if desired.

title: polish sausage
directions: Mix and roll into 3 rolls and put in refrigerator 24 hours. Then put on rack and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beggar's apple pudding
directions: Mix bread with enough cider to moisten and soften.
Combine cinnamon, sugar and raisins in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Cover with layer of bread cubes.
Dot top with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits until thick.
Add butter and cheese.
Beat eggs and add Pet milk to make 1 cup.
Put into grits mixture.
Combine and bake in buttered dish for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: beef bonaparte
directions: Season and brown meat; boil noodles and drain.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and hot noodles.
Add Mozzarella cheese, meat and sauce.
Bake uncovered 25 minutes at 350°.
Then top with Cheddar and return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese melts and bubbles.

title: angel delight
directions: Then prepare pudding and pie filling; use only 3 cups milk. Spread pudding mixture on top of cheese mix.
Refrigerate;
spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle nuts or coconut over all before serving.

title: raisin cake
directions: Place sugar, butter, water, soda, raisins, cinnamon, salt, cloves, nutmeg and ginger in larger pot and heat until boiling and butter has melted.
Let cool overnight.
Sift baking powder and flour together and stir into raisin mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in 2 medium loaf pans with bottom lined with wax paper, greased and floured.
Brush tops of loaves with jam while still hot.

title: blue cheese mousse
directions: Combine gelatin and water in top of double boiler. Stir until gelatin dissolves. In blender, combine gelatin, sour cream, cottage cheese and Blue cheese. Process until smooth. Pour into lightly oiled mold or loaf pan. Chill until firm. Unmold and garnish with grapes. Serve with crackers.

title: sweet muffins
directions: Combine all dry ingredients and add egg, milk, and vanilla. Combine all ingredients until just moistened.
Place into greased muffin pans and bake at 350 degrees for 10-15 minutes.

title: pear bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine oil, sugar and eggs; blend well.
Stir in pears, pecans and vanilla. In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add dry ingredients into the pear mixture.
Pour the batter into 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pans.
This can be baked in 4 wide mouth pint canning jars.
Place jars on baking sheet.
Bake loaf pans 1 hour; the glass jars 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Very moist.

title: tangy lima bake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon in a shallow 1 qt. baking dish. Cover and bake 30 minutes in a 325 degree oven. Near end of baking time, remove cover and crumble bacon over top and finish baking.

title: rice croquettes
directions: Heat broth in small saucepan over medium heat, to simmering. Keep hot over low heat.
Heat butter in heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat.
When foam subsides, add onion.
Saute until onion is soft.
Stir in rice, cook and stir 2 minutes.
Stir half the broth, the wine, salt and pepper into rice; reduce heat to medium-low.
Cook uncovered, stirring frequently, until liquid is absorbed, 5 to 8 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Tear angel food cake into pieces and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese and spread over cake.
Put sliced strawberries over cream cheese mixture and spread package of strawberry glaze on top.

title: chewy bars
directions: Mix together (mixture will be thick).
Spread in a greased jelly roll pan (cookie sheet).
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Beat together cake mix, sugar, nectar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, oleo and milk in saucepan.
Heat until bubbles appear.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Take off heat and add peanut butter, vanilla, oatmeal and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: fruit whipped cream dressing
directions: Melt the butter in the top of a double boiler and stir in flour, sugar and salt.

Add fruit juices gradually and cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until the mixture thickens. Stir a little of the hot mixture into the egg yolks, then stir the egg yolks into the rest of the hot mixture.
Cook about 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Chill covered.
Whip the cream until stiff. Add the chilled dressing to the whipped cream and beat slightly to blend.
Makes 1 cup.

title: fruited pot roast
directions: Brown pot roast in oil and drain.
Add water, soy sauce, pepper and onion.
Cover tightly and cook slowly for 2 1/2 to 3 hours on top of stove.
Cook until meat is almost tender.
Add green peppers, apples, raisins and brown sugar.
Continue cooking until meat is tender, about 30 minutes.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, flavorings and carrots; mix well.
Add dry ingredients.

title: leafy green salad with parmesan
directions: About 1 hour before serving, combine in a glass salad bowl the olive or salad oil, lemon juice, garlic and pepper.
Cover bowl and let stand 50 minutes.
Discard garlic.

title: squash quiche
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch casserole. Blend all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese apples
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt; cut in butter until coarse crumbs form.
Mix in grated cheese; set aside.
Combine water and lemon juice.
Pour over apples and place in lightly greased baking dish.
Sprinkle dry ingredients over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: polenta con queso
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and generously butter a shallow 2-quart baking dish.

title: green beans with mushrooms
directions: Saute onion in oil until transparent; stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over medium heat 10 minutes or
until thoroughly heated.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Pack apples in jars.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil. Pour over apples in jars.
Cook or process 20 minutes in hot water bath.
Do not let syrup sit, it will be too thick and will not pour down through apples very good.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes in boiling, salted water.
Cool slightly; dice coarsely and set aside.

title: taco burgers
directions: Cook ground beef until brown. Drain off fat.
