Add tomatoes and their liquid, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, sugar and garlic salt to the skillet.
Stir with a wooden spoon to break up tomatoes.
Turn burner to high heat and cook mixture until it boils, stirring a few times.
Return heat to low and simmer the meat mixture until thick (about 10 minutes).
Stir mixture a few times to keep from sticking and burning.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saut onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Add meat and brown.	Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.	Cook for 5 minutes.
Add soup and simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat thorough.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Serve Hamburger Stroganoff over cooked noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: granny beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in large casserole or small roasting pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, until thick and brown.

title: wacky cake(prize winner, troy fair)
directions: Combine above ingredients.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Pour into prepared pans (greased and floured).
Use 3 layer pans or one sheet pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°, until done.

title: church windows
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Line foil with wax paper.
Cover wax paper with coconut.
In heavy saucepan, melt chocolate and oleo, stirring often.
Cool 5 minutes.
Add marshmallows and stir.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix together cracker and oleo.
Reserve 3/4 c. Lightly grease 9x13 glass dish.
Pat mixture into dish and chill while making the rest of the dish.
Mix together pudding and milk. When mixed, beat in softened ice cream.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk. Beat until thick.
In separate bowl, beat cream until thick. Fold cream mixture into pudding.
Stir in the coconut.
Put into cooled baked pie shell.
Sprinkle some coconut on a cookie sheet and bake until lightly browned (5 minutes at the most). Sprinkle that on top of the pie. Refrigerate.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: In large skillet, fry bacon until crisp. Add vinegar; heat through. Remove from heat. Shred lettuce with knife. Add lettuce and onion to skillet. Season with salt, pepper and sugar. Toss 1 to 2 minutes until lettuce has wilted.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Melt first four ingredients in double boiler.
After melted, add chopped nuts.
Cream together butter, eggs and sugar.
Mix together next 4 ingredients.
Mix creamed mixture and oatmeal together.
Save 1 cup of mixture.
Spread the rest on a cookie sheet.
Spread chocolate mixture over batter.
Sprinkle remaining 1 cup of batter on top of combined mixtures.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 2 minute microwave fudge
directions: Put powdered sugar and cocoa in a bowl and mix.
Get the butter and slice in into three sections. Then put it in the bowl. Put the bowl in the microwave for 2 minutes.
When you take it out, add 3 to 4 tablespoons of milk.
Stir.
Pour it into a pan and put it into the refrigerator for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Get it out and enjoy.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: To Serve:
Mix 1/4 cup of chocolate mix with 1 cup water.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Let Cool Whip get soft, then stir in pudding.
Add rest of ingredients.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash sweet potatoes.
Add egg, vanilla and sugar; mix well. Shape mixture around large marshmallow.
Roll balls in crushed corn flakes.

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Clean mushrooms; remove centers and stems.
Put caps aside and chop up insides.
Chop onion to taste and brown in melted margarine, approximately 1 stick, until soft.
Add bacon, grated cheese, bread crumbs and Mozzarella cheese.
Add more margarine as needed to keep mixture soft.
Stuff mushroom caps with mixture and saute in butter.
May also be cooked in microwave.

title: chicken marsala with muenster cheese
directions: Soak chicken in eggs for one hour.
Roll in breadcrumbs then brown in a mixture of oil and butter in frying pan.
Remove to a baking pan, add wine and mushrooms (pour over the chicken).
Top each breast with a slice of Muenster cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: italian hamburgers
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Add onion, ketchup, water and oregano, simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Spread mixture on split, toasted buns, top with cheese and broil until cheese melts.
Makes 12 open-faced sandwiches.

title: eggs fantastic
directions: If you don't like hot dishes, use salsa that's mild.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in Bundt pan.
Cool on wire rack.

title: caraway crisps
directions: Combine all ingredients until mixture is smooth (can use food processor).
Spread on crackers and place under broiler until bubbly.

title: ham glaze
directions: Cook all ingredients together to make a syrup.
Cook slow.
If too sweet, add a little orange juice.
If too sour, add a little sugar.

title: banana coconut pudding
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Place in dish.
Bake at 300° until brown.
Stir often.

title: streamlined texas caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix lightly.
Cover; chill, stirring occasionally.
Drain and serve with tortilla chips for "scoopin' it up."
Makes 7 cups.

title: coconut caramel dessert
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 11 pan and bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: chili-cheese bean dip
directions: Place all ingredients in a large microwave-safe baking dish. Blend well. Cover with wax paper and heat on High power for 3 minutes. Stir; cover and continue heating for 2 to 3 minutes, until cheese has melted. Serve with chips.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Put nuts in a long, shallow (microwave-safe) dish.
Put salt over nuts; dot them with margarine.
Microwave on High for 2 1/2 minutes; stir.
Microwave 2 1/2 minutes more.
Remove from oven; let cool.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add milk and vanilla; beat well.
Drop by tablespoon 2 1/2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in a preheated oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate ricotta cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Mix together Ricotta cheese, sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and eggs.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour cake mix into pan.
Pour cheese mix on top.
Bake approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes at oven temperature according to cake mix directions (but watch).

title: molded lime salad with cucumbers
directions: Make gelatin according to directions on package.
Cool until syrupy.
Combine other ingredients and add to gelatin.
Pour into ring.
Decorate with cherries after salad is unmolded.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all together and bake in loaf pans. You can also add raisins. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Makes 2 large loaf pans.

title: make ahead breakfast
directions: Cook crumbled sausage over medium heat until brown; drain well.
Spread bread cubes in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Top with sausage and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Beat well and pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: chicken cooler indienni
directions: In saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Brown almonds with curry powder.
Stir in soup and water.
Serve in chilled bowls. Garnish with slivered almonds, if desired.

title: jalapeno chicken breasts
directions: Flatten chicken between 2 pieces of heavy-duty plastic wrap to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet.
Sprinkle with flour. Coat large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; over medium-high heat, brown chicken on both sides.
Coat a small saucepan with cooking spray; over medium-high heat, saute garlic until tender, add jelly and soy sauce.
Reduce heat and cook until jelly melts, stirring constantly.
Spoon jelly mixture over chicken, simmer, uncovered 5 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Transfer to serving platter.
Spoon sauce over chicken and sprinkle with olives.

title: kahlua
directions: Break up vanilla bean in gallon jar.
Dissolve coffee in boiling water and sugar; cool.
Put in gallon jar.
Add vodka and let stand in cool place for 30 days, then drink.

title: chili con queso(hot cheese dip)
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in hot oil until onions are translucent.
Add in spices, jalapenos, stewed tomatoes and pimentos.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese slowly.
Serve immediately in bowls along with corn or tortilla chips.
Great with beer!

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Lightly brown ground beef. Drain off fat. Combine all ingredients in a large pot. Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.

title: parker house rolls
directions: To milk, add sugar and salt.
To water, add the yeast and let it set until yeast is dissolved.
Mix the water and milk mixture. Add 3 cups of flour and beat until smooth.
Add melted shortening. Add some flour and beat until smooth.
Place remaining flour onto board.
Dump dough into flour and knead until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes).
Place dough in a greased, large bowl.
Let rise in a warm place about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down.
Roll dough and shape into rolls.
Place on a large baking sheet.
Let rise until almost doubled.
Bake in a 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: floothy peach
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mash peaches in food processor or by hand.
Beat peaches into the egg whites; put into sherbet glasses.
Chill.
Yield: 6 servings.
Carbohydrate 8 g, protein 3 g, fat .1 g, calories 40.
One serving = 1 fruit exchange.

title: portuguese potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in skins and cube.
Put in large casserole dish. Sprinkle cubed cheese over the potatoes.
Add onions, pimentos, parsley, paprika, and butter.
Pour over casserole.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: baked french toast
directions: Stir brown sugar, butter and corn syrup on medium heat for 5 minutes or until bubbly. Pour into a 13 x 9 baking dish. Put slices of bread on top of it. Whisk together eggs, milk, vanilla and salt. Pour over bread slices and chill for 8 hours. Mix sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over bread. Then dribble 1/4 cup melted butter over it. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cottage cheese cake
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions. Put in the refrigerator until partially set. Crush crackers and mix with melted butter. Line pan with cracker mixture. Whip the whipping cream and then mix with drained pineapple and partially set Jell-O. Pour over graham crackers. Refrigerate until firm.

title: veterans dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into jars.
Makes about 2 to 3 quarts.
Refrigerate. Serve on green salads.

title: mayme's white frosting
directions: Scald evaporated milk.
Set aside to cool.
If you burn it, throw it away and start again!

title: coconut pie(makes its own crust.)
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: cream filling
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch or flour in top of double boiler. Stir in milk.
Add beaten egg yolks before mixture gets too hot. Cook over boiling water until mixture comes to desired consistency.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Add meringue and bake until brown.
This filling can be used to make old fashioned banana pudding.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Beat eggs and whisk oil into eggs.
Sift dry ingredients. Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients and pour in the egg mixture.
Mix and then add strawberries and mix well.
Bake in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan at 350° until done, about 1 hour.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour, milk and vanilla; beat well. Bake at 350° for about 40 to 50 minutes.
Frost with your favorite frosting.
A Divinity Frosting is good or we would slice fresh oranges and put them in 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup orange juice; cook just until sugar melted.
Put this on cake layers, then frost with a Cream Frosting.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In medium saucepan, cook celery and onion in oil until wilted. Add all ingredients except milk and Parmesan cheese.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer until broccoli is tender.
Puree before adding milk and cheese.
Reheat.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Combine pumpkin, evaporated milk, sugar, eggs and cinnamon. Pour over the pressed cake mix.
Add to the cake mix, oleo, nuts and sugar.
Mix like for pie dough.
Crumble on top of pumpkin. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: orange pork
directions: Place pork on cooking rack, fat side up.
Coat with pepper. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove form oven, coat with marmalade and return to oven; cook until well done.
Watch carefully. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix flour, sugar, pineapple and cheese together.
Pour in casserole.
Cover casserole with Ritz crackers and melted butter.

title: wings
directions: Combine seasonings together.
Melt margarine in small saucepan. Cover wings in flour and spice mixture.
Tap off loose flour and spices, lay wings in deep cast iron or other deep pot with lid.

title: eggplant caponata
directions: Peel and cube eggplant; saute with garlic and onion in olive oil until golden.
Add celery and tomato paste; cook for 3 minutes.
Add olives, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Serve hot or cold with a loaf of Italian bread.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in blender (low speed) until combined well, then add vanilla.
In a large bowl, sift dry ingredients together, adding wheat germ and nuts, then mix in ingredients from blender until combined well.
Pour into Bundt pan which has been greased or sprayed with nonstick pan spray.
Recipe may be cut in half for loaf pan size.
Original recipe.

title: 5 layer delight
directions: Mix and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: country brunch(strata)
directions: Place half of the bread cubes in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put half of sausage on top, followed by half of cheese. Repeat layers.
Beat eggs with milk and seasonings.
Pour over layers, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover; bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: citrus punch
directions: Stir all together until sugar dissolves.
Serve icy cold.

title: potato biscuits
directions: Mix in enough flour to make a dough.
Roll and pat out biscuits.
Bake on greased pan at 400° until done.

title: green bean fluff
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain grease.
Put in casserole along with soup and green beans.
Cover mixture with potatoes to seal it.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp and macaroni salad
directions: Combine shrimp, macaroni and sweet pickle in a large bowl. Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper; stir into macaroni mixture.
Serve on lettuce and garnish with olives.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Work softened margarine into flour, then add enough yogurt or sour cream to have dough consistency.
Roll on floured surface like regular biscuits.
Cut.
Bake in pan at 425° until slightly brown.
Quick and simple.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine sugar, salt, flavoring, butter, cinnamon and egg.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Add bread cubes and raisins. Mix thoroughly.
Pour into well buttered baking dish.
Set in pan of warm water and place in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.
Cool and serve.

title: beef casserole
directions: Combine all, except beef and carrots.
Stir.
Mixture will be lumpy.
Add beef and carrots.
Cook in covered casserole dish at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours until beef is tender.
Serve with white rice.

title: merry christmas applesauce cake
directions: Stir soda into applesauce; set aside.
Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add applesauce; mix well.
Sift flour, spices and salt; add to creamed mixture and beat well. Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Add spiced drops as desired.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: champagne punch
directions: Float thin orange slices.
This is also good substituting apple juice for orange juice.

title: all cheese ball
directions: Grind all ingredients together using food chopper and mix well (with hands).
Form in balls and roll in paprika.
Wrap in foil. This will keep in the refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks.
Balls will freeze for 2 to 3 months.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and set
aside.
In
skillet, over medium heat, cook bacon and crumble.
Stir soup, milk, vinegar and sugar into drippings.
In large bowl, combine soup mixture and remaining ingredients.
Pour	into
2 1/2-quart casserole. Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: ben's fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with enough mayonnaise to mix it well. Chill overnight for best flavor.

title: janet's pasta
directions: There is one brand of linguini called "Ronzoni" made by the Hershey Company in Pennsylvania.
It is made in limited amounts and to me it is the best.
If you find it, call me please.
I would buy a case.

title: tomato crown fish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Freshen fish several minutes in mixture of water and lemon juice.
Place in a greased baking dish.
Season lightly and spread tomato slices over fillets.
Sprinkle with green peppers and onion.
Mix bread crumbs, oil and basil; sprinkle evenly over the vegetables.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs. Mix in sugar, butter, cornmeal, buttermilk, vinegar, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: quick hot chocolate
directions: Place candies
in
blender container.
Add hot milk and whiz until smooth.
Pour into hot mugs.
Makes 2 servings.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: In bottom of large bowl, place 3 cups of the lettuce. Sprinkle with a little sugar, salt and pepper.
Layer eggs atop lettuce in bowl, standing some eggs on edge if desired.
Sprinkle with salt.
Next layer in order, peas, remaining lettuce, bacon and cheese.
Spread mayonnaise over top, sealing to edge of bowl. Cover and refrigerate 24 hours or overnight.
Toss before serving. Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: granger pie
directions: Mix together the molasses, baking soda and boiling water to form syrup.
Set aside.
Combine the flour, sugar and shortening to form a crumb mixture.
Divide the syrup between the three pies and top each with the crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: embutido
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients all together.
Place strips of bacon vertically in the middle of foil.
Spread half of the mixed ingredients on the bacon and place Chinese sausage and half of eggs in middle.
Place rest of the mixture on top to cover.
Wrap bacon around it and wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Open foil to brown bacon for 15 to 30 more minutes.
Remove excess fat while cooking.
Cool then slice.
Makes 2 to 3 rolls of Embutido.

title: caramels
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.

In a large saucepan, melt butter. Add sugar and syrup; bring to a boil. Add Eagle Brand and cook slowly, stirring constantly, until mixture forms a firm ball in cool water (244° to 248°). Add vanilla, salt and nuts.
Do not beat!
Pour into prepared pan. Cool and cut into strips. Wrap pieces individually in waxed paper.

title: surprise cherry brownies
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Fold in the cherry pie filling. Bake in oblong pan as directed on package.

title: cream of onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Gradually stir in chicken base or water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in cream just before serving.
Put in ovenproof bowls.
Add 1 slice toasted French bread.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: joe froggers
directions: Cream shortening with brown sugar.
Mix in molasses, then add water.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, salt, ginger, cloves and baking soda.
Add to molasses mixture.
Stir until well blended. Divide dough into 2 parts.
Wrap each part in waxed paper and chill in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.
Roll dough out on floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 4-inch rounds. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: allison's chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken, lemon pepper, salt and garlic powder until chicken is done. Leave the water and chicken in pot and cover with a lid. Let the chicken set in the water until completely cooled. When cooled, drain and tear chicken apart. Add celery and mayonnaise to taste.

title: blushing onion soup
directions: In a large kettle, cook onions and garlic in butter until tender.
Stir in tomato juice, water, bouillon and parsley. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: plain muffins
directions: Beat eggs, add milk, shortening and beat more.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to egg mixture.
Stir just enough to mix.

title: stuffing
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° until crusty.
Serve with chicken, turkey or pork.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Note:
Need 1 piece of foil (12 x 15-inches).

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Place cottage cheese in large bowl.
Mix in Jell-O mix gradually until dissolved.
Add in Cool Whip, pineapple (drain first) and walnuts.
Mix thoroughly, cover and chill at least 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Wash sassafras roots.
Cut into pieces.
Place in a pan with cold water, enough to cover roots.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Strain and
serve hot with lemon or sugar.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cook, skin and bone chicken; cut in bite-size pieces. In large fry pan over medium heat add chicken and brown slightly. Add onion, green pepper, celery and snow peas. Cook about 5 minutes. Add sugar, soy sauce and vinegar, then add drained carrots; toss gently. Then add pineapple and juice; toss gently.

title: spanish rice
directions: Place brown rice in skillet with Crisco; cook until golden brown.
Add onion, tomato sauce and garlic.
Cook for 1 minute. Add broth; bring to a simmer.
Cover and cook for about 35 minutes or until tender.
Makes about 3 cups cooked rice.

title: christmas applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs. Dissolve soda in applesauce.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with applesauce to creamed mixture.
Add nuts, raisins, dates and cherries.

title: savory focaccia
directions: Mix 2 cups of the flour, onions, 1 tablespoon oil, 1 teaspoon rosemary, salt, pepper and yeast in a large bowl.
Add warm water. Beat on low speed 1 minute, scraping bowl frequently. Stir in enough of the remaining flour, one cup at a time, to make dough easy to handle.

title: salmon deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Combine yolks with other ingredients and fill egg whites.

title: easy chicken noodle soup
directions: In a large soup kettle or dutch oven bring water and bouillon to a boil.
Add noodles and cook until done, about 8 minutes.
Do Not Drain!
Add 2 cans of cream of chicken soup and stir until smooth.
Add shredded chicken to soup and noodles and let simmer about 15 minutes.
Stir in sour cream shortly before serving.
Add salt & pepper to taste.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage and water chestnuts.
Make medium sized meatballs. Bake in oven 1 hour at 375°.

title: cream pie
directions: Put milk in a heavy saucepan over medium high heat.
Combine sugar and flour.
Pour a little hot milk in sugar and flour mixture to make syrup consistency.
Just as milk is about to boil, pour sugar and flour mixture in milk, stirring quickly.
Bring to boil for about 1 minute.
Beat egg yolks.
Pour about 1/2 pudding in, stirring well.
Pour in remaining pudding.
Return to heat and bring just to a boil.
Remember to stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and butter.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Beat egg whites until peaks.
Add 6 tablespoons of sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients except peas in crock-pot and mix thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low 12 hours (high 5 to 6 hours). Add peas in the last 1/2 hour of cooking.

title: crock-pot pork chops(serves 6)
directions: Dredge chops
in mixture of flour, mustard, garlic salt and pepper.
Brown in oil.
Place in crock-pot and layer onion slices and parsley between and over chops.
Pour soup over; do not stir. Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and other ingredients.
Fold in pecans last.
Cook in greased Pyrex pan (9 x 12-inch) or larger pan at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until done.
With a fine straw or toothpick, punch in top of brownies.
Cover brownies with a cloth when you take them out of the oven.

title: mimosa
directions: Mix champagne and orange juice just before serving.
Pour into champagne glasses (flutes).
Add a strawberry or 1/2 orange slices per glass.
Serve.
Use more or less champagne as desired.
Makes 24 servings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Marinate carrots in sauce; refrigerate.
Let stand several hours or overnight if possible.

title: iced cocoa
directions: In a small bowl, with rotary beater, beat cold milk with cocoa syrup until well combined.
If desired, add creme de cacao.

title: party mints
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding sugar slowly.
Mold in mint molds. Yield:
Approximately 60 to 75 mints depending on mold size.

title: starlight sugar crisps
directions: Soften cake yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
(You may substitute 1 package dry yeast softened in 1/4 cup very warm, not hot, water.)
Sift together 3 1/2 cups flour and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt into a mixing bowl.
Cut in the butter and Crisco until the particles are the size of small peas.
Blend in the beaten eggs, sour cream, 1 teaspoon vanilla and the softened yeast.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Combine in a bowl 1 1/2 cups sugar and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Set aside.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef over medium high heat. Drain beef.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: angel biscuit
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk with dissolved yeast.
Cover tight and chill in refrigerator.
Roll out and let rise an hour.
Bake at 400° on lightly greased pans for 20 minutes.

title: danish meatballs
directions: Roll the meatballs in 2/3 cup flour, seasoned with the salt and pepper.
Brown on all sides.
Add 1 cup condensed beef bouillon and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove meatballs.
Blend in 3 tablespoons flour and brown for gravy. Stir in 1 1/2 cups condensed beef bouillon.
Cook, stirring constantly, until medium thick.
Serve meatballs and gravy with mashed potatoes.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable cream cheese pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out on cookie sheet and bake.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, dill weed and onion together and spread over baked roll dough.
Top with chopped raw vegetables (example: broccoli, carrots, cauliflower, mushrooms, tomatoes).
Sprinkle Cheddar or Mozzarella cheese over top.
Chill, cut and eat.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all together, except butter, until just blended.
Leave rough on top.
Put in a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drizzle with butter; cool on rack.

title: ratatouille
directions: Saute onions in oil until transparent, then add tomatoes and simmer slowly for 15 minutes.
Add zucchini, eggplant, pepper and salt.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Or, after sauteing onions and tomatoes, place all ingredients into heavy casserole and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend peanut butter and sugar well.
Add egg and vanilla and beat.
Form 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Make crisscross marks with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 18 cookies.

title: easy butterscotch bars
directions: Over low heat, cook together butter and brown sugar.
Cool. Add eggs, vanilla, flour, baking powder, nuts or coconut.
Spread into 2 (10 x 15-inch) pans, lightly greased.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: old fashioned molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Stir in beaten egg and molasses.
Sift flour (measured) with baking soda, salt and spices.
Add to creamed mixture, stirring until blended.
Chill in refrigerator several hours.
Shape into balls the size of marbles. Dip balls in sugar and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: mexican dish
directions: Salt, pepper and flour steak.
Brown in oil.
Add tomato sauce, picante sauce and enough water to cover steak.
Simmer until meat is tender and sauce is thick, 30 to 45 minutes.
Stir often.

title: mom's good corn dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Brown in oil.
Place in saucepan. Add onion, water, soup and catsup. Simmer on low for 45 minutes or until steak is tender. Add bell pepper 15 minutes before removing from heat. Serve over rice. Serves 4.

title: jr's olive dip
directions: Place cream cheese in microwave until softened.
Dice as many green olives as you wish and add to cream cheese.
Crush two cloves of garlic and add to mix.
Start mixing very slowly and add milk (about 2 tablespoons at a time) until the dip reaches desired consistency.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator to allow ingredients a chance to combine.
It can be used with vegetables, chips or pretzels.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Brown meat in olive oil.
Add garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce mixed with spaghetti sauce mix.
Stir in thoroughly.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Boil lasagna noodles in salted water until tender. Drain and rinse.
Pour 1/3 of meat sauce into 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Cover with layer of lasagna noodles, then layer of Mozzarella cheese and spoonfuls of cottage cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs. Sift dry ingredients. Dissolve soda in water. Stir all together. Drop by tablespoons on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until done.

title: strawberry fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended smoothly.
Chill.
Serve with chilled strawberries or other fruit.

title: jalapeno peppers-stuffed
directions: Remove seeds from 1 can of peppers and stuff with filling.

title: cream cheese pudding
directions: Mix Jell-O and water until jello is dissolved.
Put in fridge until syrup stage.
Beat cream cheese and sugar together; add vanilla.
Whip canned milk, then mix with cream cheese.
Add Jell-O and mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple cake squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Fold in apples, walnuts and raisins (batter is very stiff).
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. While still hot, spread with glaze.
Serve warm.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Soak beans in water for 6 hours; drain.
Or for faster preparation, bring beans to a simmer; turn off and let sit for 1 hour, then drain.
Saute until tender the oil, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Add to drained beans.
Cover beans with water, just barely.
Add bouillon cubes, salt, pepper, crushed red pepper and wine vinegar.
Lamb shanks or pork can be added now (optional).

title: popcorn bars
directions: In large Dutch oven, melt oil, butter or margarine, marshmallows and caramels over low heat. Stir often. When melted and smooth, let cool 3 to 4 minutes. Keep stirring while cooling. Stir in 1/2 popcorn. Add candy and peanuts, then remaining popcorn. Stir until well mixed. Pack mixture into well oiled 11 x 15-inch pan. Let cool 2 to 3 hours. Cut bars. Makes 36 medium bars.

title: fudge pudding(cook while you are eating dinner to serve warm)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, measure flour, 2/3 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and next five ingredients.
With mixer, beat at low speed just until mixed.
Increase speed to medium and beat 4 minutes.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch square pan.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Thaw out rhubarb (squeeze out juice). Mix sugar and flour together.
Mix rhubarb into flour-sugar mixture.
Poke holes in bottom crust with fork.
Put mixture into crust.
Slice butter and put pats on top of pie filling.
Put top crust on and put steam holes in it.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Turn down oven to 350° and cook 1 hour.

title: cheese elbow dish
directions: Cook elbows 9 minutes (no salt in water); drain.
Cut up Cheddar cheese.
Grease 5-quart casserole.
Put "cut up" peeled tomatoes, tomato sauce and tomato paste in a bowl.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Mix and mash.
Layer in casserole:
sauce, elbows and Cheddar cheese (3 layers).
Top with sauce, then shredded cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes and serve.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in large pot until chicken comes off bone.
Save water in pot.
Debone chicken and put meat back in the pot.
Add salt and pepper.
Bring chicken and broth to a boil.
Pinch off biscuits in small pieces and add to pot.
Boil for 5 minutes. Simmer an additional 30 minutes.

title: lonie chappell's grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a buttered baking dish.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 30 minutes or until well browned, stirring occasionally.

title: sausage balls
directions: Allow sausage to soften at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together and form into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt, onion and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain. Place half of meat mixture in bottom of large casserole.
Place half of noodles over meat; add 1 cup of sour cream.
Repeat layers.
Spread cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: gram alice's oatmeal bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of water.
Soak the oats in the 4 cups boiling water with the salt for 1 hour.
Add molasses and melted shortening to oatmeal mixture as it cools.
Add yeast and flour until mixture is quite thick.
Let rise and bake as normal bread.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: molasses cake
directions: Soften the shortening.
Mix with sugar, eggs, molasses and spices.
Stir thoroughly.
Add coffee to soda until it's dissolved.
Mix in flour and beat.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Boil and dice chicken.
Mix well cans of soup and water. Layer in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Heat until all sugar is melted (on low) to almost boiling. Let cool to lukewarm and add drained, sliced dill pickles.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except crumbs.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove and cover top with crumbs.
Place back in oven for 15 minutes.

title: no fail chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet and bake for 7 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Microwave ground beef in casserole dish for 4 to 5 minutes on High.
Drain.
Add mushroom slices and onion soup mix.
Add flour, garlic powder and catsup to sour cream.
Blend well and add to ground beef mix.
Microwave for 4 to 6 minutes on High, stirring once.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Use a 1 1/2 to 2 quart casserole dish.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, milk and soup.
Add pimento, onion, mustard and drained, flaked tuna.
Mix well.
Add cooked macaroni and pour into casserole dish.
Top with mixed crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 375°
for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken zakopani
directions: Mix salad dressing, cranberry sauce and dry onion soup mix. Place chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking pan (greased).
Pour dressing mix over and marinate for 4 to 6 hours, turning once.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 3 to 4 per serving.
Low calorie recipe with 385 calories and low fat with 5 grams.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Place all ingredients in Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat until tender!

title: french rice salad
directions: Cook rice until tender, but not mushy.
Combine oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and tarragon.
While rice is hot, pour oil mixture over it and mix thoroughly.
Cool.
Fold in peppers, onion, peas and pimento.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips, Eagle Brand milk and butter over hot water; remove from heat and add flour, nuts and vanilla.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by teaspoon and bake 5 minutes at 300°.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Toast nuts at 325° for 10 minutes.
Add sugar to beaten egg whites.
Fold nuts into egg white mixture.
Melt butter in pan and spread nut mixture over butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°. Stir often.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder.
Layer half each of the meat mixture, chips and cheese in 2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomato if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: butter pecan crumb cake
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour and cinnamon in small bowl.
Cut in butter to make crumbs.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350°
for 50 minutes. Carefully remove partially baked cake from oven and sprinkle with crumb mixture.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until done (when cake pulls away from side of pan).

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Defrost frozen vegetables; squeeze out excess water.
Mix in sour cream and soup mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 4.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Put coconut and pecans in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix by directions on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt margarine and mix well with cream cheese and confectioners sugar; spoon on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan. Cut into squares and serve upside down.

title: yummy peanut butter chocolate chip bars
directions: In a large bowl, beat peanut butter and butter until smooth. Add sugar, eggs and vanilla. Beat until creamy. Blend in flour and salt. Stir in 1 cup of the chocolate chips. Spread into ungreased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Immediately sprinkle on remaining chocolate chips. Let stand until soft and shiny, then spread.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss lightly.
Refrigerate overnight. Drain before serving.
Keeps several days.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw frozen spinach and drain.
Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate.
Serve on crackers of your choice.

title: sour cream chocolate frosting
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and add sugar and beat until smooth.

title: venison jerky
directions: Mix ingredients in a large plastic bowl.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, sugar and margarine.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 6 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel crust.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in frozen strawberries to thicken.
Let set until thick and spread over cream cheese layer.
Chill thoroughly.

title: monkey cake
directions: Combine sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon in a large Baggie. Cut biscuits in fourths and shake in Baggie.
Drop dough pieces in a well-greased tube pan.
Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add 1 teaspoon cinnamon and brown sugar.
Bring to a full boil and boil for 1 full minute.
Add nuts and pour over dough pieces.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately turn upside down on a plate.
Remove pan and serve warm.

title: best yet cracker jacks
directions: Boil sugar, syrup, butter and cream of tartar together for 5 minutes and quickly stir in soda.
Pour over mixture of popcorn and salted peanuts.
Spread into lightly greased cookie sheet. Put in low oven (200°) for 40 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes. Store tightly covered.

title: neptune's beer batter
directions: Measure the flour into a bowl.
Make a well in the flour; add the egg yolk, beer and salt.
Stir until well blended.
Gradually add milk; stir until smooth.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg white. Makes enough to coat 1 pound of fish.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix all together and let stand overnight.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries, reserving juice.
Add enough orange juice to reserved juice to measure 1 cup.
Bring juice to a boil in saucepan.
Add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Pour into bowl. Chill until partially set.
Chop cherries.
Combine cherries and sugar in saucepan.
Cook for 2 minutes, stirring frequently. Cool.
Add cooled cherries, pecans and celery to gelatin; mix well.
Pour into large mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold onto lettuce-lined salad plate.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: zucchini mozzarella(microwave)
directions: Place zucchini and water in a 3-quart casserole.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook on High for 15 minutes.
Stir once during cooking time.
Drain.
Add salt.
Place slices of cheese over drained zucchini.
Pour tomato sauce and seasoning over cheese; top with Parmesan cheese.
Cook on High 3 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: In a skillet, saute the diced giblets and onion in the oil, until the onion is transparent and giblets are lightly cooked. Add seasonings and broth (or water with bouillon cubes dissolved in it).
Add the frozen vegetables; stir all together.
Bring to boil; simmer for 20 minutes.
The liquid should just cover the giblets and vegetables; if needed, add more liquid.
tags: cream of mushroom soup and chicken gumbo soup

title: arroz tapado a la peruana
directions: Heat oil in saucepan and brown 1/2 the garlic with a little salt.
Add water.
When water boils, add rice.
Cook slowly. Saute onion, remaining garlic and meat in shortening.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
When meat is browned, add raisins, eggs and parsley.

title: fruit kuchen
directions: Mix together 1 1/2 cups flour and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Cut in 1/4 pound cold butter until mixture is fine like meal.
Then with a fork, stir in 1 egg yolk and a pinch of salt.
Lay very thin into 12-inch flan pan with a removable bottom.
Combine 4 tablespoons breadcrumbs with 2 teaspoons of sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Sprinkle on the dough in the pan.
Cover the dough with sliced fruit (apples, pears, peaches, halved apricots or blue prunes). Mix together 6 tablespoons of sugar and 3/4 teaspoon of cinnamon. Sprinkle over the fruit.
Melt 6 tablespoons of butter.
Allow the butter to cool slightly and add to it 3 egg yolks and 6 tablespoons of whipping cream.
Pour over the fruit.
Bake 30 minutes in a 400° oven.
Check for doneness and continue baking another 15 to 20 minutes or until custard is set and browned and the pastry too. Cool 10 minutes before removing the sides of the pan.
When cool, glaze with melted red currant jelly or melted and strained apricot jam.

title: icebox pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, condensed milk and orange juice together.
Put it in the pie shell and refrigerate 2 hours.
Serve.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Place a layer of tomatoes in a shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add a layer of cracker crumbs, then one of cheese.
Dot with butter.
Repeat.
Bake in preheated 475° oven for 20 or 30 minutes, until brown and bubbly.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls in pan and bake.
Mix dressing, cream cheese and Miracle Whip.
Spread on rolls.
Add vegetables.
Top with 8 ounces low-fat shredded cheese.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour over 15 to 20 cups of popped corn.
Put in roaster and bake 1 hour at 250°; stir every 15 minutes.
Cool.
Put in an airtight container.

title: peanut butter treats
directions: In a large saucepan, stir together corn syrup, sugar and peanut butter over low heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal and toss well to coat. Spread into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Place broccoli in baking dish.
Heat together in a pan, soup, Cheez Whiz, butter and milk.
Stir in uncooked rice and pour over broccoli.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes.

title: rich cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9
x
13-inch pan.
Layer the rest of the ingredients in the order given.
Bake at 325° to 330° for 30 minutes.
Cut in small squares while still warm.
Remove from pan when cool.

title: oriental veggies
directions: In skillet, heat oil and cook sliced green beans, cauliflower, carrots and onion.
Combine sauce ingredients (water, chicken stock base, cornstarch and garlic powder).
Add to cooked vegetables.
Heat thoroughly until thickened.

title: summertime "tea"
directions: Combine lemon juice, water and sugar; let stand in refrigerator overnight or at least 3 hours.
(If lemons were used, strain liquid.)
Add Cokes no more than 2 hours before serving.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding with milk. Add 10x sugar. Add Cool Whip and continue to mix until blended.
Layer crackers with 1/2 of the pudding, crackers, pudding and ending with crackers in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Top with chocolate icing, Pillsbury or Duncan Hines. May also use instant chocolate pudding.
I microwave frosting for about 20 seconds for easier spreading.
Stir well before spreading.
This dessert can be made ahead.
Makes 16 to 18 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham crackers with 1 stick of melted butter.
Pack into cake pan.

title: swedish potatoes
directions: Repeat first layers, ending with the potatoes.
Add 1 cup half and half.
Put in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Add 1 cup half and half and reduce temperature to 350° and bake for approximately 1 more hour.

title: diabetic apple delight cake
directions: Mix well and bake 30 minutes at 350° in 6 x 9-inch pan.

title: summer shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Rinse with cold water and drain well.
Rinse and drain shrimp.
Sprinkle lemon juice over shrimp.
Carefully fold shrimp, onions, pepper, cucumbers, celery, olives and tomatoes into macaroni.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Blend salad dressing and cream and fold into salad.
Serve on lettuce leaves and garnish with grated Parmesan cheese.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: ham delights
directions: Mix first seven ingredients together.
Split rolls open. Spread mixture on rolls.
Place rolls back in trays.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: miss alice's microwave pralines
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients.
Cook in microwave for 13 to 15 minutes on High, stirring every 5 minutes.
After 13 minutes, check for softball stage.
Stir, then pour into buttered pan.
Break into pieces.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil broccoli until limp; boil chicken until almost cooked. Mix next 4 ingredients and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Melt butter and mix with bread crumbs; put on top.
Lastly, cover it with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Mix and blend softened cream cheese and sour cream in food processor or blender.
Add remaining ingredients and blend until smooth.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or more.
Serve as a dip for fresh fruit or cake squares.

title: raisin spice cake
directions: Combine raisins and water.
Boil gently for 5 minutes and pour over oleo or butter in a bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Sift together next 7 ingredients and add to cooled raisin mixture. Beat egg well; add and beat it in well.
Pour into a pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add sour cream and the eggs; blend well.
Add vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and a pinch of salt.
Sift into creamed mixture. (Dough will be soft and firm.)
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: grandma's date crumbles
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, flour and soda, then make a crumbly mixture and press 1/2 in an 11 x 15-inch pan.
Cook dates, milk, sugar and oleo.
Spread over 1/2 of the crumbly mixture.
Use the rest of the crumbly mixture on the top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: First pick out any shells. Mix all ingredients and make into patties.
Fry in hot oil, just a few minutes until brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Enjoy!

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Beat the egg and add the whipped topping.
Mix this and add the cake mix.
Use a spoon, not a mixer.
Roll into little balls. Dip top of balls in confectioners sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: breakfast or lunch casserole
directions: Brown crumbled sausage; drain all grease.
Break bread into bite size pieces; place into bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Spread crumbled sausage over bread, then the grated cheese over sausage.
Beat the eggs.
Add the milk, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Pour egg mixture over bread, sausage and cheese.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add water to beaten egg yolks, then pour into sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add pineapple and butter.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens.
Remove from heat.
When cool, add vanilla.
Pour into pie shells.

title: jubilee jumbles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
If dough is too soft, cover and chill. Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: kathleen's blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix crushed graham crackers with margarine, both sugars and cinnamon.
Sprinkle berries with lemon juice.
Spread graham cracker mixture in a greased casserole dish.
Spread blueberries on top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate and water on low heat.
Cream margarine, sugar, yolks, vanilla, flour and soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk, then add white chocolate.
Fold in egg whites.
Add coconut and nuts.
Pour into three 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix together and store in airtight container.
This recipe will serve 5 people.

title: gazpacho
directions: Place tomatoes, 1/2 cup peppers, 1/2 cup cucumbers, 1/2 cup croutons, 1/4 cup onion and remaining ingredients in blender or food processor.
Cover and blend on medium speed or process until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In bowl, combine milk, sour cream, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix well and chill.
In a large bowl, beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Mix in flour, oats and nuts until well blended.
On lightly oiled 12-inch pizza pan, press out dough, prick with fork and bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool completely, spoon filling over crust, then arrange fruit on top. Serve in pie-like slices.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: dusty's tortilla chips
directions: Cut tortillas with your choice of cookie cutter shapes.
Place tortilla shapes on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake in a 300° oven for about 15 minutes.
Tortillas will begin to curl when done.
You may choose to flavor the chip by sprinkling them before baking with seasoned salt or other seasoning.

title: copper penny relish
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator several hours.

title: bantoffi pie
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter.
Stir in crushed biscuits.
Press into a pie pan.
Place remaining butter and sugar in a pan and heat gently, stirring until butter melts.
Add milk and heat stirring continuously until simmering.
Simmer on low heat for exactly 5 minutes to make a light golden caramel.
Keep stirring.
Pour over biscuit base and allow to cool in refrigerator. Serve chilled or for a softer toffee, serve at room temperature.
Top with bananas and whipped cream.

title: layered toffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream just until it begins to thicken. Gradually add the ice cream topping and vanilla, beating until soft peaks form. Cut cake horizontally into three layers. Place the bottom layer on a serving plate. Spread with 1 cup cream mixture and sprinkle with 1/2 cup candy bar.
Repeat. Place top layer on cake. Frost top and sides with remaining cream mixture and sprinkle with the remaining candy bar. Store in refrigerator.

title: swiss steak
directions: Sprinkle flour on round steak and beat it.
Salt and pepper it and brown in hot oil.
Add water to cover, 2 beef bouillons; cook on medium heat for 30 minutes.
Then add onion, pepper and tomato and cook another 3 minutes or until meat is tender.
Remove meat and thicken gravy with flour.
Great!.
Serve with mashed potatoes and vegetable.

title: mom's sauce & meatballs
directions: In large pot, saute garlic in oil until lightly browned; remove from pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil, lower heat to low, cover and simmer at least 3 hours.
While cooking, make the meatballs.

title: mama's moist pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. In large mixing bowl, cream margarine, Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, alternating with flour. Add vanilla and lemon extracts. Mix until smooth and creamy. Pour into tube pound cake pan. Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until brown in creases on top.

title: cranberry fudge
directions: Butter sides of heavy saucepan.
Combine sugar, milk, cream, syrup and salt.
Stir over medium heat until boiling; cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat until mixture is stiff, about 5 minutes. Quickly stir in the cranberries.
Spread into a buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Cut into pieces when cool.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen pieces.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Coat chocolate chips and pecans in a spoon or so of the dry cake mix.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Fold in chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until done in a greased and floured tube pan.
Cool before frosting.

title: pear honey
directions: Grind pears.
Mix pears, sugar and pineapple immediately to prevent pears from turning brown.
Bring to a boil and boil about 30 minutes or until syrup clears, stirring constantly.
Pour in hot jars and seal.

title: mother's yeast bread
directions: Heat milk, butter, sugar and salt.
Set aside to cool. Sprinkle yeast in cup of warm water.
To first mixture, add egg, then flour and then yeast water.
Knead until smooth and elastic. Place dough in a warm place after brushing with melted shortening. Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Knead again and make into two loaves or rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 325° about 40 minutes for bread.
For rolls, bake at 375° until lightly brown.

title: cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers thinly.
Place in bowl with pepper and garlic salt.
Cover bowl and refrigerate for 2 hours, then add the sour cream and mix well.

title: low-calorie shrimp dip
directions: Blend the cottage cheese, lemon peel and juice, dill, salt, and hot sauce in a blender until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients. Serve sprinkled with additional parsley. Yield 2 cups.

title: german potato salad(hot potato salad)
directions: Cut bacon into 1 inch pieces.
Pan fry, slowly until almost cooked, add onion, and cook until transparent.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt, and paprika.
Pour in vinegar and water; cook until mixture thickens.
Pour in vinegar and water; cook until mixture thickens.
Pour mixture over potatoes and serve.
Serve hot.

title: old fashioned jewish pound cake(from brooklyn, new york via dot hoffmann)
directions: Use greased 10-inch tube pan.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies and save 1/4 cup on the side.
Add butter to the crushed cookies and blend.
Press into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan. Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Mix with sugar and half of the whipped cream.
Spread over crumb layer and refrigerate. For 30 minutes, prepare pudding.
Spread over cream cheese layer and chill for 1 hour.
Spread remainder of whipped cream and sprinkle with remainder of cookie crumbs.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in water.
Add to rhubarb and sugar.
Cook until thick.
Add coloring and vanilla.
Let set.

title: peach delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine, then add the flour; beat until smooth.
Add nuts.
Spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 minutes or until brown.
Cool completely.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In a large oblong Tupperware container, cut up lettuce, then spread the chopped celery, green pepper and green onions.
Drain peas.
Sprinkle with sugar, then spread on top of vegetables. Spread mayonnaise on top of that, then sprinkle cheese on top of all.

title: taco soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock pot and simmer 4-6 hours. Top with cheese and corn chips, if desired.

title: coast coconut custard pie
directions: Set coconut aside.
Put all ingredients into a blender for 3 minutes on medium.
Spray a 10 or 11-inch pie plate.
Pour into pie plate; sprinkle all coconut on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Let stand 5 minutes or cool until firm.

title: champagne salad
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in a large 8-inch square Tupperware container (or 9 x 12-inch Tupperware for double mix). Fold in Cool Whip.
Dessert can be frozen and taken out 1 hour before serving or serve as mixed.
Both ways are very good.

title: oven french fries
directions: Cut potatoes into thick strips.
(Peel if you want.)
Soak in bowl of ice cubes and water for about 20 minutes.
Drain potatoes and blot dry.
Toss lightly with salad oil to coat evenly.
Spread in single layer in shallow, nonstick pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake 30 minutes at 450°, turning frequently.
Season to taste.
Makes 4 servings about 100 calories each.

title: egg dumplings
directions: Add salt and milk to beaten egg and stir into flour to form a smooth batter.
Drop by teaspoon into boiling soup or soup beans. Cover tightly and cook for 15 minutes.
Do not lift the cover during this time.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Drain chicken and put into a bowl with cream cheese.
Add Ranch mix.
Mix all ingredients with a fork.
Shape into ball and roll in pecans and refrigerate.

title: raisin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain and add 2 sauces.
Simmer.
Cook shells; drain.
Put 1 cup sauce and meat in bottom of baking dish.
Then add some shells, cheese and pepperoni.
Keep layering until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: anniversary chiffon cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Make a well. Add oil, egg yolks, water and flavoring.
Beat with spoon until smooth.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in large mixing bowl until very stiff peaks form.
Pour egg yolk mixture gradually over beaten egg whites, gently folding in with rubber scraper until just blended. Gently fold in pecans.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes, then at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: nine bean soup
directions: Clean and wash beans; place in a large pan.
Cover with water and soak overnight.
Drain.
Add 2 quarts water, ham, onion, garlic and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat.
Simmer until tender, 1 1/2 hours.
Add both kinds tomatoes.
Simmer 30 minutes more.
Stir occasionally.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: muffin pizzas
directions: Heat tomato sauce.
Add oregano, garlic and a pinch of sugar. Spread on muffin halves.
Add cheeses and pepperoni.
Heat under broiler 2 to 3 minutes.

title: iced coffee latte
directions: Place coffee granules in medium bowl. Add boiling water and whisk together. Whisk in sweetened condensed milk and cold water until completely blended. Pour coffee mixture into 2 quart pitcher. Add chocolate milk; stir to mix. Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar and milk.
Sift together half of the flour with salt and baking powder.
Beat until smooth and add only as much more flour as needed.
Batter should be thin enough to run through a funnel.
Drop batter from funnel into deep hot fat (375°) using a swirling motion.
Control the flow of batter using your finger.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes until golden brown.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar or cinnamon sugar.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: grilled chicken fettucini alfredo for 2
directions: Cook fettucini in salted water until al dente (slightly hard). Saute mushrooms, broccoli and peppers in a little butter for about 2 to 3 minutes.
Season chicken with salt and pepper and grill on grill or cook in broiler.
When chicken is done, cut into long strips and add to vegetables.
Saute for 1 more minute.
Add heavy cream, grated cheese and butter to mixture.
Let cook and reduce until thick.
Add fettucini and mix well in pan.
Beat in egg yolk rapidly so egg doesn't cook.

title: date nut balls
directions: Cook oleo, dates and sugar until thick, stirring constantly, to keep from burning.
Add nuts, vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Roll in tiny balls when mixture has cooled.
Put powdered sugar in bag and shake balls in sugar.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Prepare corn muffin mix according to directions, including an additional 2 tablespoons of liquid to add moisture to the mix. Pour into a 9-inch square baking dish and bake according to the directions on the box.

title: peanut butter roll-up candy
directions: Mix sugar, vanilla, salt and egg whites.
Add sugar until it forms a ball.
Chill in refrigerator several hours.
Place on cutting board sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll out with rolling pin to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll into a rope shape.
Cut into slices 1/2-inch thick. Chill before serving.

title: great-grand ma owens' ambrosia
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl and chill.
Fold in cherries (optional).
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken molay
directions: Brown chicken.
Remove from skillet.
Add all other ingredients and simmer until chocolate has melted.
Replace chicken and add enough water to cover.
Cover pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and stir into eggs.
Add milk and pumpkin.
Line pie pan with pastry and pour in filling.
Bake in very hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to slow 325° and bake for 35 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions; let cool.
Mix strawberry Jell-O with boiling water; let cool.
Poke holes in cake with end of wooden spoon.
Pour Jell-O over top of cake. Frost cake with Cool Whip that has been mixed with chopped fresh strawberries.
Decorate cake with whole strawberries.

title: grandma's mexican hots
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand overnight.
Make into hamburgers the next day and fry or grill.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip with pudding thoroughly.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix and chill for 1 hour.
To decorate, garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: colored sugar
directions: Don't buy expensive colored sugar.
Put a small amount of sugar in plastic bag.
Add cake coloring in and mix.
Let dry on cookie sheet and put into small jars.
Keeps as long as sugar usually does and is much cheaper.

title: cabbage and rice
directions: Shred cabbage
and place in greased baking dish.
Place meat, onion,
salt
and
pepper
in skillet; fry until lightly browned. Drain
and mix in uncooked rice.
Spoon mixture over cabbage.
Mix soup
and	water
and
pour
over top.
Bake in tightly covered dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sango de camarones(shrimp stew)
directions: *Annato:
Coloring used for coloring oil a bright orange-yellow color.

title: guacamole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Serve as a dip or a topping for Mexican foods and snacks.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix ingredients, stirring, until chocolate chips are melted.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Saut the hamburger and garlic in the oil; add everything but the cheeses and simmer 20 minutes.

title: brisket
directions: Marinate overnight.
Turn over next morning.
Bake in Dutch oven or covered pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 4 hours.
Keep sauce.
(If desired, take out and put on charcoal grill for 1 hour.)

title: kahlua cake
directions: Make cake night before serving.
When cool, cut into small pieces and pour Kahlua over it.
Refrigerate; also make pudding night before and refrigerate.
To serve layer in order:
cake, pudding, cream and crushed Heath bars in glass bowl into as many layers as you want, usually 2 to 3 layers.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Combine 1st three ingredients thoroughly.
Blend in applesauce.
Combine remaining ingredients and blend with wet mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in cake pan.
Stir with fork.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sour cream chili bake
directions: In a large bowl, mix chili, 1 cup cheese, 3 cups corn chips, hamburger, 3/4 cup olives and bottle of sauce.
Stir well. Bake for 25 minutes at 375° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix in large bowl and refrigerate until ready to use.
Makes a large amount.

title: crackle top peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Blend in egg, peanut butter and vanilla.
Add flour, sifted with soda and salt; mix well.
Shape teaspoonful of dough into balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheets and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate-banana cake
directions: Place chocolate in top of a double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until chocolate melts.
Set aside to cool.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well with an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with banana, buttermilk and melted chocolate, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.

title: chicken 'n' noodles
directions: Cook egg noodles as directed; do not drain water.
Add chicken pieces and 2 cans creamy chicken soup.
Stir.
Cook on medium heat about 20 minutes.
Serve with bread and butter.

title: apple-cheese snowy treats
directions: Cut the apple into bite-size slices.
Spread the cheese on the apple slices.
Top each with the coconut.
Crunch away with your best friend.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix together.
Let stand overnight.
Roll 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: swiss fondue
directions: Bring water, wine, garlic powder and butter to a boil in a saucepan.
Add cheese.
Add Accent, dash of white pepper and nutmeg.
If not thick enough, you may thicken with cornstarch or wine to thin.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding mix, crushed pineapple and Cool Whip. Add pecans, coconut, marshmallows and cherries as desired.
Refrigerate until used.

title: salsa dip
directions: Stir Velveeta cheese and picante sauce in saucepan on low heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in cilantro.
Serve hot with tortilla chips or vegetable dippers.

title: scallop seviche
directions: Toss the bay scallops with the lime juice.
Place in a bowl with the remaining ingredients.
Cover; refrigerate overnight. The lime juice does all the cooking.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in a blender or food processor and blend on high for 1 minute.
Add the remaining ingredients and blend on high until frothy.
Pour in dish and chill until firm. This can be poured into a graham cracker crust, also.

title: carrot cake
directions: In mixing bowl, beat sugar and eggs until thickened; add oil. Sift flour; add baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt together.
Add to egg mixture.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Pour batter into prepared pans; bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Remove from pan; let get completely cold.
Serve with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: dill pickle
directions: Bring to boil apple cider vinegar, 2 quarts water and canning salt.
Put into sterilized quart jars garlic, pepper and dill. Pack jars full of small pickling cucumbers which have been thoroughly cleaned.
Pour boiling solution over cucumbers, filling jars and seal with hot sterilized lids.
Let stand a few weeks before serving.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon of milk and 1 tablespoon of sugar in a large bowl until smooth.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Spread on pie crust.

title: creamy pork chops and potatoes
directions: Place sliced potatoes and chopped onions in large baking dish. Mix the soup and milk.
Pour 1/2 into baking dish over potatoes. Top with pork chops.
Pour rest of soup mixture on top.
Cover with tinfoil; bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Combine blueberries, 1 cup of sugar and 1/2 cup of water in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until berries are soft.
Combine cornstarch and 3 tablespoons of water in bowl.
Add to blueberries.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute; cool.
Combine flour, margarine and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: crispy oven baked chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in Dijonnaise and spices for 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Mix cornflake crumbs, flour, salt and pepper.
Pour oil in pan; roll chicken in crumb mixture.
Place in large pan. Bake at 425° until done.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and Wesson oil, then mix other ingredients in. Bake at 350° in tube pan for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: summer eggplant
directions: Slice and coat eggplant with egg and milk mixture, then bread crumbs.
Put on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Layer sliced tomatoes in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish, then eggplant, then 1/2 of Parmesan cheese, then tomatoes.
Sprinkle the remaining Parmesan, then Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with foil. Bake 20 to 30 minutes more.

title: rosalyn's cheese ball
directions: Combine Cheddar, pecans, onion, and mayonnaise and mix until thoroughly blended.
Divide mixture in half and roll each into ball.
Place cheese balls on serving platter and press well into the center of the ball.
Spoon raspberry preserves into the depression.
Serve with Sociable crackers.	(Other crackers may be used.)
This cheese ball freezes well without the preserves.
Just thaw and put raspberry preserves on top.

title: creamy crescent bake
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Place 1 package crescent rolls on bottom. Cream together egg yolk, softened cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and vanilla. Spread on crescent rolls. Beat egg white until foamy. Spread egg white on rolls. Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar mixed with cinnamon on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour and salt together, then add alternately to other mixture with milk.
Add vanilla. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon butter snowbars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a 1 - 1/2 quart mixer bowl, combine crust ingredients.
Mix on low speed until blended, about 1 minute.
Pat into ungreased 8 inch square baking pan.
Bake near center of 350 degree oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown on edges.
Meanwhile, prepare filling.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Cream sugar, oleo, vanilla, milk and egg.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 10-inch ungreased pan. Sprinkle chips over it.
Smooth chips into batter with back of spoon.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: christmas tea
directions: Boil water.
Add tea bags.
Boil down to about 1/2 quart. Pour into crock-pot.
Add apple juice.
Simmer.
Garnish with oranges, cloves and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Cook zucchini for 12 to 15 minutes, until no water (clear), stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice, pineapple and sugar.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Add gelatin and stir.
Put in refrigerator or freezer.
Makes 6 pints.

title: potato cheese dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in oblong baking dish. Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put rice in 2-quart casserole.
Add both cans of beef consomme. Add onion rings.
Lay your pork chops on top.
Cover with foil. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: eggplant italian
directions: Peel eggplant; cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Dip slices into egg and coat with bread crumbs.
Saute in hot salad oil until lightly browned on both sides.
Overlap slices in a greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, oregano, parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Pour tomato sauce over eggplant slices. Cover with Mozzarella cheese slices.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, water and spices.
Let stand 1 hour.
Toss vegetables into dressing, 1/2 hour before serving. Serves 12.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix water, sugar and yeast and let stand while mixing other ingredients.
Mix together flour, soda, buttermilk and Crisco. When mixed well, add yeast mixture.
Roll out biscuits and bake at 400°.
Put in covered container and take out as needed.

title: yogurt poppy seed coffee cake(serves 12 to 15)
directions: Grease angel food cake pan and dust lightly with flour.
Soak poppy seed in yogurt.
Cream butter and add sugar.
Blend into yogurt mixture.
Beat egg yolks and add to mixture.
Add vanilla, sifted flour and baking soda.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or drizzle with lemon glaze.
Serve warm.
This is great for meetings and coffees.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and fry.
Remove from drippings. Saute onion until brown in drippings.
Remove onions from drippings and add seasonings.
Simmer for 15 minutes in skillet. Mix with beans, onions and bacon.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or simmer in crock-pot for several hours.
Freezes well.

title: lazy apricot preserves
directions: In food processor, process apricots until very finely chopped. Transfer to 3 1/2 quart electric slow cooker. Stir in sugar and water. Cover and cook on high, stirring occasionally, two hours, or until jam has thickened. Let cool and store in refrigerator up to three weeks or freeze up to three months.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Combine cream cheese, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Add onion and crabmeat.
Place in ovenproof serving dish. Top with almonds. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: raisin nut pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients (except pie shell).
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: kentucky hot browns
directions: Make toast and trim.
Make cheese sauce by melting margarine and stirring in flour.
Slowly add milk, grated cheese, Parmesan cheese, salt and Worcestershire.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Arrange thinly sliced turkey and ham slices on toast. Cover with hot cheese sauce.
Top with tomato slices and partially cooked bacon strips.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Broil in oven until brown.

title: danish tart
directions: In bowl, mix butter and sugar until thoroughly creamed.
Add 1 egg at a time; beat thoroughly.
Beat in lemon rind and 1 teaspoon juice.
Sift flour and salt; gradually add to batter and beat thoroughly.
Put into 9-inch spring-form pan.
Toss apple slices onto batter.
Add remaining lemon juice; drizzle melted butter over apples.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes, until apples are browned and cake pulls away from the sides of the pan.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in water.
Drain and add fresh water to cover beans about 2 inches.
Bring to a boil; turn to lower heat and simmer, covered, about 1 hour with the onion, garlic and pepper.
Add the taco sauce (and more water, if needed) and cook 1/2 hour longer or until beans are done.
Serve with cornbread for a complete protein.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together well and chill overnight before serving with an assortment of small pieces of fresh vegetables.

title: cherry frosting(serves 16, with cake)
directions: Cut each cherry into 3 pieces with knife or clean scissors. Place cherry pieces on paper towels to dry.
In saucepan, heat to boiling, stirring a few times, margarine, cocoa and milk.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add and beat until smooth, powdered sugar, cherry pieces and almond extract.

title: almond and ginger two-rice(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Prepare brown and wild rice in separate pans according to package directions.
Combine in a large bowl and allow to cool. Add peas, scallions and bell pepper.

title: butterscotch pound cake
directions: Use a small amount of the 2 1/2 cups flour to coat pecans and butterscotch bits.
Set aside.
Cream butter, sugar and softened cream cheese.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour gradually, continuing to beat well.
Add vanilla.
Fold in pecans and butterscotch bits.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Lower oven to 300° for another 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients into large microwave bowl or quart measuring cup.
Cook on High for 5 minutes.
Beat with a whisk and cook 5 more minutes or until thickened (mixture will be fairly thin).
Whisk again.
Let cool slightly.
Pour over layered bananas and vanilla wafers.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar and dash of salt until frothy.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar (one at a time); beat until stiff peaks form.
Spread on pudding and bake in a 425° to 450° oven until browned.
Watch closely.

title: slaw souffle
directions: Mix lemon jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup ice and refrigerate until slightly congealed.
Beat with mixer until foamy, then add remaining ingredients.
Congeal.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Press out on cookie sheet; let cool and cut in squares.

title: duck and sausage gumbo
