directions: Boil duck, using salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons Cajun seasoning.
Debone duck.
Use the liquid in gumbo.
Dissolve roux in water over medium heat.
Add salt, pepper, monosodium glutamate and chopped vegetables.
Add deboned duck and sausage.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat and cook until tender, 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Serve over cooked rice.
Add okra, if desired.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine in heavy pan over low heat. Be sure to sift powdered sugar.
When margarine and peanut butter are melted, remove from heat.
Add vanilla and powdered sugar; mix well.
Pour into square pan.
Pour chocolate chips on top while still warm.
Spread when melted.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Beat egg until light.
Add applesauce and sugar.
Beat together.
Add raisins and nuts.
Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and mace.
Add to applesauce mixture.
Beat well, then add melted butter.
Stir well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased and floured pan.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: aunt jenny's lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and cook until thick.
Add 3 egg yolks, 1/3 cup lemon juice and 1 tablespoon butter.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and bananas.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain well. Mash until smooth, add cream cheese, sour cream, onion salt, salt, pepper and butter.
Beat potatoes until smooth and fluffy. Place in refrigerator container.
Cool and cover.
May be stored in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into balls.
Chill well.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and peppers together.
Add other ingredients.
Mix and stir together.
In a baking dish, bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fat free banana pudding
directions: Pour 4 cups cold skim milk into a medium bowl.	 Add 2 pkg. pudding mix.
Beat at lowest speed for two minutes.
Combine cool whip and beat for about half a minute.
Pour 1/3 mixture into a round casserole dish.
Layer with banana.
Top with vanilla wafers.
Continue to make three layers.
Refrigerate overnight. Serves 8.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix sour cream and drain vegetable soup in medium-size bowl until well mixed.
Store in refrigerator for at least 1 hour before serving.
Great on a raw veggie tray or with crackers or chips.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Place chicken pieces in a single layer in a shallow, glass baking dish.
Combine garlic, brown sugar, soy sauce, molasses and pepper.
Pour marinade over chicken pieces and refrigerate several hours or overnight, turning pieces once.
Thread chicken, pepper squares, pineapple chunks and onions alternately on skewers.
Cook over medium coals 15 minutes, turning and basting frequently with marinade until chicken is golden brown and done.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate caramel cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom and side of 9-inch spring-form pan or 9-inch square baking pan.
Melt the chocolate mini morsels and margarine in a large saucepan over low heat; cool slightly.
Stir in the oats, flour and brown sugar.
Press firmly into bottom and 1 inch up the sides of the pan.
Bake for 10 minutes; cool completely.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: jim's blueberry muffins
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs slightly with a fork.
Add milk and oil. Mix in dry ingredients.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake in greased or paper lined muffin cups at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 8-9 muffins.

title: favorite lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream the butter, flour and sugar.
(Keep 1/2 cup sugar for egg whites.)
Add lemon juice and rind; mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold into first mixture gently.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate cream filled angel food
directions: Mix, bake and cool cake as directed on box.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar. Add eggs and beat. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda. Add to sugar mixture. Add oats, vanilla and chocolate chips. Dough will be crumbly. Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: red rice 3
directions: Cover bottom of pot in fried meat grease.
Add chopped onion and bell pepper.
Saute until tender.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, and water.
Add sugar, salt, pepper, and hot sauce.
Stir and cook until boiling.
Add rice and cook until
the mixture boils again. Turn down heat (low to medium).
Stir often so that the rice does not stick to the bottom of the pot and scorch.
Cook until rice is done but not completely dry (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Add more water if needed.

title: thai this salad
directions: Heat a small skillet until very hot.
Add peanuts.
Cook over dry heat until skin turns black, stirring constantly.
Remove peanuts to colander.
Let cool for several minutes.
Rub peanuts between hands to remove skins.
Chop peanuts and set aside.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add water.
Cook and stir until thick; cook 2 minutes more.
Add blueberries.
Return to boiling.
Chill.
This sauce is excellent served over lemon pie.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown ground chuck, then add onion, cabbage and celery.
Cook until vegetables are limp.
Add 1/2 cup water; cover and cook for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients in a large pan; cover and cook for 10 more minutes.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Beat peanut butter, butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in large mixer bowl until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Beat in flour.
Stir in 3/4 cup morsels.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Remove from oven immediately.
Sprinkle with remaining morsels.
Let stand for 5 minutes, then spread.
Cut into bars.

title: basic quiche
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Toss together cheese and flour and mix into egg mixture.
Add ham, bacon or sausage as desired.
Pour into unbaked pie crust (deep dish). Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil fryer; cool, take off bone and chop.
Melt oleo.
Add cream of chicken soup and chicken broth; heat until smooth. Layer meat, Veg-All and 2 sliced eggs.
Pour 1/2 soup over this, then repeat layer again with the remainder of soup on top. Separate each biscuit; put on top.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are brown.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Put half of the meal mixture in bottom of pan, then the meat mixture.
Cover meat with as much grated cheese as desired, then the other half of the meal mixture on top of cheese.
Bake 45 minutes in 400° oven.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and extract. Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 75 minutes or until brown.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Put brown sugar and butter in heavy saucepan.
Add 1/4 cup milk.
Start at low temperature.
Cook until it has a caramel look.
Add 1 1/2 cups milk, egg yolks and flour.
(I use an electric mixer to beat the mixture.)
I cook it until thick. Remove from heat and add vanilla. Pour in 9-inch pie pan.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except the last two listed. Pour into a buttered casserole dish; top with crushed potato chips and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Serves 6.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix thoroughly in brown paper bag.
Makes 1 gallon jar full. Use 1/2 cup for a cup of hot water.

title: hummingbird pie
directions: Combine lemon juice and sweetened condensed milk.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Place sliced bananas in bottom of pie crust. Spread milk and lemon juice mixture evenly over bananas.
Drain pineapple some, but not dry.
Spread pineapple and 1/4 cup pecans over banana-milk layers.
Spread whipped topping evenly over the top.
Garnish with remaining pecans, coconut and cherries.
If desired, also garnish top with grated chocolate or chocolate curls.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Place frozen rolls evenly in well-greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle the pudding over the rolls.

title: apple pie
directions: Pare apples and slice thin.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and spices and add to apples.
Fill pie shell; dot with butter or oleo.
Put on top crust.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 45 or 50 minutes.

title: golden cream soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine potatoes, 1 cup water, celery, carrots, onion, parsley flakes, bouillon cube, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grind cookies in food processor. Set aside.

title: pork chops plus
directions: Brown pork chops in a nonstick skillet.
Dissolve bouillon in cup of warm water.
Put rice mixed with mushroom soup and 1/2 cup bouillon into a casserole dish (13 x 8-inch) that has been sprayed with a vegetable spray.
Place pork chops on top of rice mixture. Garnish each chop with slices of onion.
Add pepper rings and tomato slices, if desired.
Cover with foil and bake one hour at 350°.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Cream the sugar, salt and shortening.
Add egg; mix well. Pour in lukewarm water; stir until yeast dissolves.
Add cold water and flour.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Make out rolls a few hours before baking.
Bake at 425°.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Lay meat in broiler pan.
Pour liquid smoke flavoring over meat; sprinkle generously with onion powder, garlic powder and celery salt.
Cover pan with foil; refrigerate overnight.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine the chilled ingredients in a punch bowl just before serving.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix, in a non-metallic bowl, sugar, cocoa, milk and melted butter. Mix well.
Cook for two minutes at full power in a microwave. Remove bowl, add vanilla and mix well.
Pour in well-buttered dish and cool.

title: cheese bars
directions: Blend cake mix, butter and one egg with a fork.
Press into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: quick zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased pie pan. Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: microwave baked custard
directions: Beat eggs lightly in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix in sugar, salt and vanilla.
Stir well.
Measure milk into 1-quart container. Microwave the milk 3 to 4 minutes (or until about to boil).
Stir into egg mixture.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place this casserole in an 8-inch baking dish (pie plate size).
Pour 1 cup very hot water into this baking dish.
Microwave 9 minutes on "6" or until custard is almost set.
Custard will become firm as it cools.
Serve chilled.

title: 2 double crust pies
directions: Mix flour, shortening, salt and baking powder until lumpy. Add water.
Will still be lumpy.
Mix and form 4 balls.
Stand a while in balls.
Cool in fridge or freezer.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg and molasses.
Mix well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add 1/4 of dry ingredients at a time, mixing until smooth each time.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll into balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Yields 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: quick sweet fix mix(low carb)
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Fold in 1 c. heavy cream beaten stiff. Put in bowl and chill.

title: houska
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients together and cool to lukewarm temperature.
Add cooled milk mixture to yeast and water mixture, then add eggs and flour.
Mix well!
Cover bowl and let mix raise about 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours; punch down.
Let stand covered 10 minutes.

title: cheese tarts
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and eggs with mixer until smooth. Grease well very small size muffin pan with butter.
Put graham cracker crumbs in pan and pat down.
Tap out excess crumbs.
Put cheese mixture into each cup, filling each cup.
Bake at 300° for about 12 to 14 minutes until they rise.
Cool completely in refrigerator.
Mix sour cream, vanilla and powdered sugar. Carefully remove tart from pan and spoon small amount of mixture on top.
Spoon cherry filling on top.
May be frozen or refrigerated.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish. Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onions in vegetable oil.
Add beef and cook until gray. Add next 6 ingredients; stir.
Put into greased casserole dish. Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Toss apples with lemon juice to coat thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and toss gently to combine.
Chill at least 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Serves 6.

title: black bean soup(great for mexican night; serve it with fajitas or tacos.)
directions: Wash beans; add water and bring to a boil. Cover and turn off stove. Let set overnight.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
In small mixing bowl, stir together eggs, milk, butter and brown sugar.
Add to flour mixture and stir until blended.
Pour batter onto grids of preheated waffle baker (lightly greased).
Do not open lid while baking.
Top with fruit or yogurt.
Baking time:
4 minutes per side.
Yield:
12 (4-inch) waffles; 6 servings.

title: herbed tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes in bowl; sprinkle with seasonings and herbs. Combine oil and vinegar and pour over tomatoes.
Cover and chill for 3 hours, spooning dressing over tomatoes several times.
Drain off dressing if you like.

title: hot chicken wings
directions: Cut wings into sections; discard the tips.
Add all the ingredients; cook until chicken is done.
Place the wings on baking sheet; coat with sauce.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted boiling water for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine soup and sour cream in mixing bowl.
Stir in carrots.
Fold in squash and onions.
In separate bowl, combine stuffing mix and butter.
Combine half of stuffing mixture in bowl with squash mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: my mother's salted peanut cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add beaten eggs, flour and baking powder.
Mix 1 teaspoon soda with small amount of hot water and add along with rolled oats and peanuts.
Drop by spoon.
Bake at 350°.
Makes a large batch.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: In a bowl, combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening and sweet potatoes until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in enough milk just until dough clings together.
Knead lightly on a floured surface.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter and place on a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 450° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: meal in one casserole
directions: Mix together corn, cream of mushroom soup, onion, frankfurters and potato chips.
Bake, uncovered, in a moderate 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ding bats
directions: Mix butter, sugar and dates.
Bring to a boil (about 1 minute). Remove from heat. Add pecans and Rice Krispies.
Make balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: copper pennies
directions: Peel and slice carrots. Cook until tender. Drain.
Mix and heat soup, Worcestershire sauce, oil, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper. Add carrots, bell pepper and onion.
Mix well. Cool and refrigerate.

title: stuffed pita bread
directions: Saute garlic, celery, green onion and green pepper in oil and margarine. Add ground meat; cook and stir until meat is browned. Drain. Add raisins, tomatoes and oregano. Cook until thick; season with salt and pepper. Stuff pita pockets and put slice of cheese on top. Broil until cheese is melted.
Good!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove bone and skin.
Mix each soup with 1/2 can broth.
Melt butter.
Mix with crumbs.
Start with layer of crumbs, then chicken.
Pour celery soup, layer of crumbs and layer of chicken.
Pour chicken soup over it.
Add last layer of crumbs. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Add enough milk to make quite moist.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at least 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Be sure it is hot through. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
A can of pimentos and mushrooms may be added to give flavor and color.

title: tuna macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs; fold in macaroni.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Combine bread crumbs with melted butter; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop the 10 quarts of popcorn and set aside.
Cook the butter, brown sugar, salt and white syrup for 5 minutes.
Add the baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over the popcorn and bake for 1 hour at 250 degrees.
Stir every 20 minutes.

title: crab quiche
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs; add mayonnaise, flour and milk.
Stir in crab, onions, parsley and cheese.
Spoon into pie shell.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Yield 6-8 servings.

title: lillian quester's butter tarts
directions: Mix all together and pour into 10 small pastry shells.
The secret is syrup and cream.
Any nice rich pastry is good for this recipe.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain cherries; reserve syrup.
Into a 2-quart casserole dish, layer vanilla wafers, cherries and marshmallows.
Pour reserved syrup evenly over marshmallows.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream or whip cream.

title: chicken rice hot dish
directions: Flour chicken and brown in a little oil and half of the margarine.
While it is browning, put the rice, salt and pepper into greased casserole and strew onion on top.
Put mushrooms (juice and all) on. Arrange chicken on top.
Pour bouillon over it.
Dot with rest of margarine.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham glaze
directions: 45 minutes before ham is done, put glaze on top.
Keep basting until thick.

title: easy mexi-dip
directions: In an 8 to 10-inch square microwavable dish, layer the cream cheese, then chili, then shredded cheese.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Serve with nacho chips. Good!

title: fruited mold
directions: Coat 8-cup mold with nonstick cooking spray.
Layer blueberries, strawberries and nectarine slices in mold.
Set aside.
In medium saucepan, combine cranberry apple juice, unflavored gelatin, honey and 1 1/2 cups water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cook juice-gelatin mixture over low heat for 5 minutes until gelatin is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Carefully pour mixture into mold with fruit.
Chill 3 hours until firm.

title: marinated pork tenderloin
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate pork tenderloin for at least 5 hours.
Cook on grill.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add nuts and garlic.
Roll in 2 long rolls.
Mix paprika (2 to 3 tablespoons) and chili powder (3 tablespoons).
Sprinkle on wax paper.
Roll cheese balls in mixture, wrap and chill.
Slice and place on Ritz crackers or corn chips.
Place sliced olives on top.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to boil.
Spray or brush on chicken over fire pit. Yields 25 to 50 halves.

title: irene's n.y. cheese cake
directions: Blend sugar, flour and salt with th softened cream cheese. Add heavy cream.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes in a spring-form pan.
Use graham cracker crumbs for the bottom of the cake.
Use red canned cherries for a topping, if you wish.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and margarine.
Add eggs and pecans.
Fill shell with mixture.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Pie should cool before cutting to ensure a good texture.

title: curried chicken soup
directions: Cut chicken into 3/4-inch pieces.
Marinate in soy sauce, sugar, some salt and pepper and 1 teaspoon cornstarch.
Let set 30 minutes.
Sprinkle carrots, potatoes and yellow onion with 1 teaspoon cornstarch.
Brown both sides of chicken until golden. Remove with strainer and drain on paper towel.
Brown vegetables and drain.

title: molasses cookies (brer rabbit)
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients well.
Add remaining ingredients. Roll dough into small balls.
Toss with sugar and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: breakfast scones
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine all ingredients with fork to make stiff dough.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls 1-inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in boiling water until tender (1/2 cup). Strain and add 2 cups sugar, lemon gelatin and remaining cup of boiling water.
When cool, add nuts, grapes and drained pineapple. Pour into mold and chill until firm.
(Use scant cup of boiling water).
Serves 12.

title: grandma's fudge brownies
directions: Let shortening cool and mix in sugar and vanilla.
Beat in the 4 eggs, one at a time, beating well after each is added.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Stir into wet mixture and add nuts.
Spread batter in greased pan and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: shannnon's cranberry orange muffins(fat-free)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Reconstitute cranberries in boilling water and drain. Combine dry ingredients in a large mixingbowl. In a separate bowl, combine wet ingredients; stir wet ingredients into dry ingredients. Mix in orange zest and cranberries. Pour batter into greased large muffin tins. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center of muffin comes out clean.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in water until tender.
Cool, peel and dice. Fry bacon in pan and drain on paper towels.
Saute onion in bacon drippings until golden.
Add onions and any bacon drippings to potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add mushroom soup, cheese and crumbled bacon.
Bake at 350° for at least 20 minutes or until thoroughly hot.
Serves 8.

title: cucumber salad *
directions: Peel, score and slice cucumbers, very thin.
Combine rest of ingredients and marinate cucumbers overnight.
Drain and serve as a side dish.

title: german potato salad
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain off excess fat.
In skillet, saute sliced onion until soft.
After boiling potatoes, cool, peel, slice and place with onions.
Add sugar, white vinegar, oil and broth.
Season with salt, garlic powder, nutmeg and white pepper.
Crumble bacon and add to potatoes. Steam and simmer until desired consistency.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Break up bread into small pieces and set aside.
In a bowl, beat eggs, sugar and melted butter; mix well.
Add pineapple with juice and mix well.
Add bread and stir to coat.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat egg and vanilla.
Mix in zucchini and stir in dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Drop on greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: golden nugget cookies
directions: Cream together butter and 1 1/4 cups sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Sift together flour, salt, soda and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Add to creamed mixture. Mix 1/4 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and walnut or pecan halves. Shape dough into small balls and roll in sugar mixture. Place on greased baking sheet. Press nut halves in each. Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: watermelon nectar
directions: Puree half of the watermelon with 1 cup of the water.
Pour into a pitcher.
Add the rest of the fruit, water, sugar and lime juice to the blender and puree.
Add this to the juice in the pitcher.
Pour over shaved ice and garnish each glass with a lime wedge. Serves 6.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Sprinkle salt, pepper, garlic, onion, oregano and sweet basil heavy once around the
pot.
Pour
some oil in bottom of pot; then add ingredients.
Add sausage and steak; add chicken later. Approximately 1 hour
before
sauce
is done, then add raw meatballs.
Should cook at
least
hours.
Skim off oil and excess occasionally while cooking.

title: raisin nut bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Set aside.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Add milk, oil, 2 eggs and 1/2 teaspoon lemon juice to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Pour 1/2 batter in pan.
Top with cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican sandwiches
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Add salt and pepper. Drain excess grease.
Add catsup, sugar and vinegar.
Mix well. Allow to simmer a few minutes.
Place on sliced bread or hamburger buns and serve.

title: unbelievable lasagna
directions: Brown ground turkey with onion and garlic.
Discard fat that cooks out of meat.
Mix together tomato sauce, red pepper, chili powder, parsley leaves, oregano, basil leaves and paprika.
Mix together cheeses.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, spread about 1 cup sauce mixture.
Arrange a layer of 3 uncooked lasagna strips; top with some sauce mixture, cheese mixture and ground turkey mixture.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs and blend thoroughly.
Chop nuts and fruits in medium pieces.
Mix with part of flour.
Sift together remaining flour and baking powder.
Fold into egg and butter mixture.
Add flavorings.
Mix, then add fruit and nuts, mixing well.
Pour into greased paper-lined tube pan. Place in cold oven and bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Cool.

title: super soup
directions: Cut and chop all vegetables into small chunks.
Boil in water with seasoning and salt and pepper to taste for at least 10 minutes.
Lower heat and simmer until desired consistency of vegetables is reached.
Increase or decrease water while cooking to get desired thickness or thinness of soup.
There are very few available calories in this soup, so you can eat it often.

title: yummy twinkie dessert
directions: Cut Twinkies in half the long way.
Make a layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix milk with pudding according to directions.
Pour over Twinkies.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle Heath bars over the top.
Cool at least 4 hours.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Soak beans overnight. Cook until tender (about 2 hours). Drain. Add rest of ingredients. Bake 1 hour or longer at 300°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Wash rice; place half in baking dish.
Spread 3/4-inch layer of raw ground meat over rice.
Wash and shred cabbage, spread 1/2 over ground meat.
Slice onion and place over cabbage; salt and pepper to taste.
Repeat second layer of all ingredients.
Place sliced bell pepper on top of onion slices.
Mix catsup with one bottle of water and pour over mixture.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 375° for one hour.
Serve with hot rolls and beverage.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil the first 2 ingredients until clear, then cool.
Mash the bananas to pulp (I use blender).
Add the bananas to the pineapple juice, juice of lemons and orange juice.
Add water to the orange juice as on can. Combine all juices and bananas with the syrup and freeze.
Before serving, thaw to slush and add 4 quarts of 7-Up.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo; add stuffing mix.
Mix well and line bottom of dish.
Sprinkle reserved stuffing over top. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
If desired, 2 cans of squash can be substituted for fresh squash.

title: root beer
directions: Mix together water, sugar and root beer extract.
Add dry ice slowly.
Use wooden spoon, not metal.
Mix in a large, plastic cooler.
Wait 20 minutes to serve.

title: sausage pie
directions: Cook sausage and then peel potatoes.
Boil until tender and mash with cooked sausage and all other ingredients.
Mix well. Put in casserole dish or pie plate.
Cook at 375° for 30 minutes. Serve with bread or in pastry.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash and cut squash in 1/4-inch slices crosswise.
Add onion and cook together until tender in small amount of water.
Drain and add crackers, beaten egg, cheese, soup, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour mixture into greased baking dish and bake at 350° until brown.

title: chili beef dip
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain drippings.
Add tomatoes, onion flakes, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, salt and chili powder. Cover and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove garlic.
Serve with tortilla chips as an appetizer or add your favorite beans and serve as a main course.

title: beef brisket
directions: Put soup on meat.
Put coffee, beer and carrots around sides of meat.
Cover tightly and bake at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine sugar and cranberries; set aside.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Chill until partly set.
Add last 3 ingredients and chill until firm.

title: creamy dreamy fudge
directions: Sift cocoa and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Set aside.	In heavy saucepan, melt margarine and cheese.	Add sugar mixture to cheese mixture and stir constantly until mixed well. remove from heat.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased or buttered 9x13 pan.
Cool and cut in pieces.
Freezes well.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: Cook asparagus in 1 cup water until tender; drain, reserving liquid.
Saute onions in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk, 1 cup water, reserved cooking liquid and bouillon gradually.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in asparagus.
Heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and roll in chopped nuts and a little parsley (optional).
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Note:
For a heartier salad, you may add salad shrimp, cubed salami or any other meat.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, 1 1/4 cups water and butter; heat until sugar dissolves.
Add cornstarch, blended with remaining water. Cook slowly until clear, about 8 minutes.
Add 6 tablespoons lemon juice and rind; cook 2 minutes.
Slowly add egg yolks, beaten with milk; bring to boiling.
Cool.

title: sweet potato-banana casserole
directions: Clean, cook and cool sweet potatoes.
Slice into 1/4-inch thick circles.
Slice bananas into 1/4-inch thick circles.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Cream 1/2 cup sugar, margarine and crumbs.
Line a 9 x 12-inch pan with mixture.
Beat eggs; add cream cheese.
Beat well.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and the vanilla.
Spread over crumb mixture and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Cool!

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and place in a baking dish.
Top with 1/2
stick
of
butter and cover mixture with 1/2 cup of Ritz crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Saute in the oil the vegetables (heavy on vegetables).
Remove vegetables; saute sliced kielbasa; add vegetables.
Add tomato puree, water, onion soup mix, bouillon packets, salt and pepper. Simmer for at least 1 to 2 hours.
Add any leftover vegetables. Add cooked elbow macaroni or pasta of your preference.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: homemade country style vanilla ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Slowly add sugar, beat until thickened.
Add cream, vanilla and salt and mix well. Pour into can.
Add milk to fill line on can and stir well.
Churn in freezer per instructions.
Makes approximately 4 quarts.

title: chocolate ribbon pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and 1 tablespoon milk in large bowl until smooth. Gently stir 1/2 of Cool Whip. Spread on bottom of crust. Pour 2 cups milk into large bowl. Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk for 2 minutes or until mixture is thick. Pour over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate for 4 hours or until set. Spread remaining Cool Whip on pie just before serving.

title: quick ham casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese according to package directions.
Add ham and English peas and mix well.
Pour into ungreased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken pileau
directions: *Onion may be added and sauteed with bacon.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Place vegetables in large mixing bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Stir to mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 or 3 hours before serving.

title: london broil
directions: Trim excess fat from steak and wipe with damp paper towel. Combine remaining ingredients.
Brush half of mixture over one side of steak; let stand 45 minutes.
Place steak, oil side up, on lightly greased broiler pan.
Broil 4-inches from heat for 5 minutes.
Turn steak; brush with remaining mixture and broil 4 to 5 minutes longer.
Remove steak to board or platter and slice thinly on the diagonal across the grain.
This steak will be rare, the only way London Broil should be served.
Serves 4.

title: chunky tomato soup
directions: Mix all together and heat.

title: peanut butter krispies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Add Rice Krispies slowly.
Shape and chill.
Coat with chocolate.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Saute pepper, onions and garlic in oil.
Add mushrooms and cook 1 minute.
Add shrimp and cook 5 to 7 minutes, turning once. Remove from heat.
Add butter and lemon juice.
Serve on rice or pasta.

title: fresh coconut sheet cake
directions: Make up cake mix by package directions with the addition of 1 teaspoon vanilla and all but 1/2 cup of the coconut; reserve 1/2 cup.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan and 3 inches deep by package directions. Meanwhile heat together, but do not boil milk, sugar and remaining teaspoon vanilla.
Stick the cake with a wooden pick to make holes.
Pour the hot mixture over the hot cake.
Allow milk to run down into the holes.
Let cake cool completely.
Spread thawed whipped topping over the top; sprinkle with reserved coconut.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Dip fillets into Italian dressing.
Place into a greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and salt to taste.
Mix chips and cheese; spread mixture over fish.
Bake in oven at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: cheryl bell's potatoes and carrots
directions: Spray roaster with Pam.
Fill with potatoes and carrots.
Mix couple of sticks of melted butter with as much onion and pepper as you like. (I use couple tablespoons of onion and 1 cup of green peppers.)
Mix with butter and pour over carrots and potatoes. Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Don't peek.

title: grapefruit in brandy
directions: Cut off all the peel and pith from grapefruit and carefully poke out the pithy core with the little finger.
Slice the fruit into 1-inch rounds.
Put the sugar in large saucepan with 1/2 cup cold water and cinnamon.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently until the sugar has dissolved, then boil for 2 minutes.
Lower the heat.
Add grapefruit slices.
Poach for 6 minutes, turning once. Arrange slices on serving dish.
Pour brandy over them and serve hot or chilled.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed until smooth. Gradually add sugar, beating until blended. Gently fold in the Cool Whip. Place 1/2 of cake cubes in a large glass bowl. Top with 1/2 of cheese mixture. Spread 1/2 of cherry filling over cheese mixture. Repeat layers with remaining cake cubes, cheese mixture and cherry filling. Cover and chill. Yield: 12 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients in large saucepan and heat to simmer. Do not boil.
Pack cucumber mixture in hot jars.
Cover with vinegar mix and seal jars.
Let stand for a couple of weeks before eating.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Spread bean dip in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread avocado dip over bean dip.
Make a mix with mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread over avocado dip.
Top with vegetables and serve with tortilla chips.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind vegetables, using coarse blade.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Add all other ingredients. Heat to boiling; simmer 3 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.
Makes 8 or 9 pints.

title: chocolate icebox torte
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler.
Add water and blend until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat vigorously until blended.
Add powdered sugar; blend.
Fold in stiff egg whites and whipped cream.

title: currant cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat on medium until well mixed. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll dough as thin as possible. Sprinkle with sugar.
Cut into 2-inch circles.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: polish potato soup
directions: Wash potatoes; cover with water and boil until soft.
Peel and pulverize potatoes.
Add other ingredients and simmer to a creamy consistency.

title: swiss chard
directions: Clean and boil Swiss chard in a pot of salted water.
Cook until tender.
Drain and squeeze out water.
Put Swiss chard in a casserole pan.
Drizzle oil over Swiss chard.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover with tinfoil and bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Serve with your favorite meat or fish meal.

title: missouri meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Pat into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Layer ingredients in large oblong baking pan.
Shake dry cake mix on top of apples.
Pour melted margarine on top of cake mix. Sprinkle cinnamon sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together.
Chill well.
Allow time for flavors to mix. Add more dill if needed.
Good with fresh vegetables and chips.

title: pepperoni and cheese rolls
directions: Follow directions on bread for thawing and rising when that is done.
Pull off pieces of dough and roll out.
Put 4 slices of pepperoni and grated cheese and roll up.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: italian pepper steak
directions: Slice beef across grain into thin strips.
In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat in 1 tablespoon hot oil, cook half the beef until browned, stirring often.
Remove; set aside.
Repeat with remaining beef.
Reduce heat to medium.
In same skillet, in remaining 1 tablespoon hot oil, cook sweet pepper, onion, oregano, garlic powder and pepper until vegetables are tender, stirring often.
Stir in soup and water.
Heat to boiling.
Return beef to skillet; simmer 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve over fusilli or spaghetti.

title: baked celery loaf
directions: Put bread crumbs, celery, parsley, pecans, onion and green pepper through food chopper with medium knife.
Mix in rest.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° to 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: plum cake
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together.
Add pecans and vanilla. Bake in tube pan on 350° for 45 minutes.
Check to see if done.

title: rainbow jello
directions: Divide ice cream into 4 sections.
Soften each section for each layer.

title: stromboli
directions: Defrost frozen dough 1 day head of preparation day in the refrigerator.
Spread flour on work area.
Roll one loaf of dough out at a time with rolling pin.
Spread pizza sauce to cover rolled out dough surface.
Then spread slices of cheese and then pepperoni.
Roll dough and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
